./sources/sources_index.jsonl:110:{"created_at": "2026-05-26T17:05:00-07:00", "notes": "U.S. Surgeon General advisory on loneliness, isolation, social connection, belonging, health risk, and community repair. Use as a grounding source for teachings and practices aimed at disconnection, feeling unneeded, social withdrawal, and the loss of ordinary belonging.", "path": "notes/source-cards/modern-human-condition-surgeon-general-social-connection-advisory.md", "source_id": "modern-human-condition-surgeon-general-social-connection-advisory", "source_type": "report", "title": "Our Epidemic of Loneliness and Isolation", "tradition": "modern-human-condition", "url": "https://www.hhs.gov/sites/default/files/surgeon-general-social-connection-advisory.pdf"}
./sources/sources_index.jsonl:115:{"created_at": "2026-05-26T17:05:00-07:00", "notes": "American Psychological Association report on stress, uncertainty, money, work, politics, safety, and the future. Use as grounding for modern overload, exhaustion, vigilance, helplessness, and teachings that must fit people living under real pressure.", "path": "notes/source-cards/modern-human-condition-apa-stress-in-america-2024.md", "source_id": "modern-human-condition-apa-stress-in-america-2024", "source_type": "report", "title": "Stress in America 2024", "tradition": "modern-human-condition", "url": "https://www.apa.org/news/press/releases/stress/2024/stress-in-america"}
./sources/sources_index.jsonl:116:{"created_at": "2026-05-26T17:05:00-07:00", "notes": "World Health Organization definition of burn-out as a workplace phenomenon involving exhaustion, mental distance or cynicism, and reduced professional efficacy. Use as grounding for teachings and practices about work, effort, responsibility, recovery, and the danger of spiritualizing overwork.", "path": "notes/source-cards/modern-human-condition-who-burn-out-occupational-phenomenon.md", "source_id": "modern-human-condition-who-burn-out-occupational-phenomenon", "source_type": "website", "title": "Burn-out as an Occupational Phenomenon", "tradition": "modern-human-condition", "url": "https://www.who.int/standards/classifications/frequently-asked-questions/burn-out-an-occupational-phenomenon"}
./sources/sources_index.jsonl:117:{"created_at": "2026-05-26T17:05:00-07:00", "notes": "Pew Research Center study on where Americans say they find meaning, including family, career, money, spirituality, faith, friends, and health. Use as grounding for meaning loss, purpose, belonging, and how teachings should meet the actual places people already look for significance.", "path": "notes/source-cards/modern-human-condition-pew-where-americans-find-meaning-in-life.md", "source_id": "modern-human-condition-pew-where-americans-find-meaning-in-life", "source_type": "report", "title": "Where Americans Find Meaning in Life", "tradition": "modern-human-condition", "url": "https://www.pewresearch.org/religion/2018/11/20/where-americans-find-meaning-in-life/"}
./sources/sources_index.jsonl:121:{"created_at": "2026-05-26T17:05:00-07:00", "notes": "World Happiness Report edition with attention to age, wellbeing, social support, and declines among younger people in several countries. Use as grounding for generational distress, belonging, loneliness, future anxiety, and the need to write teachings for the modern person.", "path": "notes/source-cards/modern-human-condition-world-happiness-report-2024.md", "source_id": "modern-human-condition-world-happiness-report-2024", "source_type": "report", "title": "World Happiness Report 2024", "tradition": "modern-human-condition", "url": "https://worldhappiness.report/ed/2024/"}
