findings/convergences/2026-05-26-whether-the-claimant-layer-vocabulary-can-function-cross-traditionally-without-im.md:13:Whether the claimant-layer vocabulary can function cross-traditionally without importing Theravada phenomenological categories (view, conceit, latent tendency) as a default analytic frame. The challenger correctly observed that Jodo Shinshu does not map onto graduated dissolution of self-claiming: the practitioner is not releasing layers of ownership but being entrusted by Amida's working, with human-facing contact points that are structurally different from residual self-claiming at different levels. Dzogchen recognition is not dissolution at all but seeing what was always present, with post-recognition stabilization preventing obscuration rather than progressively releasing deeper self-layers. The rubric requires a decision the exchange did not settle: are claimant layers fixed analytic categories applied from outside (enabling comparison but imposing one tradition's phenomenology), or are they drawn from each tradition's indigenous vocabulary (preserving integrity but complicating comparison)? A secondary unresolved issue is rubric complexity: eleven fields with multiple rows per function may reduce inter-rater reliability below useful thresholds, and the practical payoff (anticipate re-appropriation, provide repair) may be independently derivable from Trungpa's spiritual materialism analysis without the full coding apparatus.
observations/codex/2026-05-30-stratified-post-negation-authorization.md:11:After de-identification or objectless-awareness practice, the key comparative unit is not only what remains and not only whether a remainder is inferred. The key unit is the authorization mode that permits a text, teacher, model, or practitioner to rest, investigate, deny, bracket, teach, or refuse what seems to remain. This authorization must be coded by textual stratum and level of claim: early Upanishadic passage, Advaita commentary, early Buddhist sutta, neuroscience redescription, teacher instruction, and practitioner interpretation. Valid use of the rubric requires a failure condition, such as cases where multiple modes fit every passage equally, and a human test, such as whether the resulting counsel reduces distress without increasing inflation, dissociation, nihilistic deflation, or rumination.
observations/codex/2026-05-30-stratified-post-negation-authorization.md:64:- Run the same coding on SN 22.59 and SN 22.95, testing whether recursive remainder-testing is stable across the Buddhist samples.
reviews/dialogues/2026-05-26-does-first-break-grammar-add-independent-predictive-power-for-entry-guid.json:60:        "Design a vignette study that codes teacher guidance across Jodo Shinshu, Theravada, Catholic spiritual direction, Dzogchen, recovery, and therapy settings.",
reviews/dialogues/2026-05-26-does-first-break-grammar-add-independent-predictive-power-for-entry-guid.json:194:      "argument": "Codex's challenge lands cleanly: the original model does not separate what caused entry from what the tradition later authorizes as a legitimate account of entry. I accept the two-layer split as necessary and overdue. I also concede that universality must go; the model applies where entry is thematized as a problem, not everywhere. But the separation of layers does not reduce the model to mere narrative analysis. The grammar is not only retrospective. It is active at the point of guidance: it shapes what teachers say to newcomers, what they warn against, what evidence they accept for genuine entry, and what they diagnose as premature or self-deceived. A Jodo Shinshu teacher who hears 'I worked hard to develop trust' will respond differently from a Theravada teacher who hears the same sentence, not because they are applying different retrospective labels to a completed event, but because their grammar identifies different dangers in the act of beginning. The Shinshu teacher hears self-power contaminating other-power trust. The Theravada teacher hears healthy effort following encounter. The grammar constitutes the guidance encounter, not merely the story told about it afterward. Taylor's social imaginary argument and Taves's work on 'deemed special' attributions support this: the available interpretive framework partly constitutes the experience, not only its narration. A practitioner formed within Shinran's grammar may genuinely experience the arising of trust as something that arrived rather than something they produced, because the grammar shaped the attentional categories within which the experience occurred. This does not mean the grammar is a complete causal account. It means the two layers (lived mechanism and authorized grammar) are not fully independent. The grammar is one of the variables that shapes the mechanism, alongside crisis, social context, institutional pressure, personality, and the other factors Rambo identifies. The revised model therefore makes a more modest but more testable claim: first-break grammar predicts distinguishable pastoral consequences at the entry point: different safeguards, different warnings, different evidence requirements, different characteristic errors. This is not a universal structural constraint on all contemplative paths. It is a variable that matters most where entry is experienced as blocked, and it matters most to the cohort of people for whom beginning is the problem: those in depression, addiction, burnout, grief, meaning-crisis, or the trap of achievement-contingent worth, where the demand for self-generated initiative reproduces the condition it is meant to cure. The crux is whether the grammar is active enough to produce these distinguishable consequences after controlling for the variables Codex rightly names: conversion process, institutional authority, teacher personality, cultural context, and retrospective narrative training. The proposed test (identical case vignettes presented to teachers from different traditions, with guidance coded independently of the typology) would settle this. If guidance clusters by first-break grammar, the model survives as a predictive tool. If it clusters by other variables, the model should be reduced to a taxonomy of entry narratives, still useful for comparative scholarship but no longer claiming to predict practice architecture.",
reviews/dialogues/2026-05-26-does-first-break-grammar-add-independent-predictive-power-for-entry-guid.json:212:      "defense": "The challenge is right that retrospective grammar and causal mechanism must be separated. But the separation does not defeat the model; it clarifies what the model actually predicts. The revised claim is that first-break grammar is causally active at the guidance layer: it shapes what teachers tell newcomers, what dangers they name, what evidence they accept for genuine entry, and what they warn against as premature or self-deceived. This is not a retreat to mere sociology. Pastoral guidance is where tradition meets the practitioner's lived confusion, and the grammar determines the shape of that meeting.\n\nConsider the safeguard prediction concretely. A Jodo Shinshu teacher encountering someone who says 'I worked hard to develop trust in Amida' will hear this as a warning sign: self-powered effort to produce other-power trust is the characteristic entry error. A Theravada teacher hearing 'I worked hard to develop faith in the teacher' will hear this as healthy. The grammar does not merely redescribe a completed entry; it actively shapes what the teacher does next, what corrections they offer, and what the practitioner is encouraged to notice or abandon. The grammar is constitutive of the guidance encounter, not decorative.\n\nTaylor's social imaginary argument supports this: the available framework of meaning partly constitutes what experiences are possible, not only how they are narrated afterward. A practitioner formed by Shinran's grammar may genuinely experience the arising of trust as something that happened to them, not because they are retrospectively redescribing self-generated effort, but because the grammar shaped the attentional field within which the experience occurred. A practitioner formed by Theravada's grammar may genuinely experience their encounter with a teacher as the critical break, because the tradition trained them to notice that encounter as significant.\n\nThis means the two layers (lived mechanism and authorized grammar) are not fully independent. The grammar partly constitutes the mechanism by shaping attention, expectation, and the categories available for noticing what is happening. The model does not need the grammar to be a complete causal account of entry. It needs the grammar to be active enough that different grammars produce distinguishable guidance, distinguishable safeguards, and distinguishable characteristic errors at the point of entry. That is an empirical claim, and it can be tested.\n\nThe human problem the model addresses is real and specific. People experiencing depression, addiction, burnout, meaning-crisis, or achievement-contingent self-worth often face a version of the first-break problem: they cannot begin the process that would help them because the condition itself blocks beginning. Therapy requires enough clarity to cooperate with therapy. Recovery requires enough stability to show up. Contemplative practice requires enough stillness to sit. The model does not claim to solve this problem, but it names the structural options available: someone else breaks the circle for you (social encounter, therapist, sponsor), something beyond your control initiates the process (grace, surrender, medication), or the capacity was never absent and only needs conditions for recognition (self-disclosure, the moment of clarity). These are not only doctrinal positions; they are pastoral strategies with different consequences for how helpers approach people who are stuck.\n\nThe cohort is blocked seekers, cross-tradition practitioners navigating incompatible entry assumptions, pastoral counselors and therapists working with people who cannot begin, and comparative scholars building structural models of contemplative architecture. The non-fit case is people for whom entry was never a problem: those formed by inherited practice, family ritual, cultural immersion, or ordinary socialization, where the path was always already underway before the question of beginning could arise.",
reviews/dialogues/2026-05-26-does-first-break-grammar-add-independent-predictive-power-for-entry-guid.json:224:        "Shinran, Tannisho chapter 1",
reviews/dialogues/2026-05-26-does-first-break-grammar-add-independent-predictive-power-for-entry-guid.json:226:        "Dzogchen pointing-out instruction tradition",
reviews/dialogues/2026-05-26-does-first-break-grammar-add-independent-predictive-power-for-entry-guid.json:231:      "test_that_would_settle_it": "Present pastoral counselors and teachers from traditions with different first-break grammars (Jodo Shinshu, Theravada, Catholic spiritual direction, Dzogchen) with identical case vignettes: a person who says they cannot begin because they feel too broken, too distracted, too sinful, or too confused. Code the teachers' actual guidance (what they say, what they warn against, what they look for as evidence of genuine entry) without revealing the typology. If guidance clusters by tradition in ways that match the predicted grammar (Shinshu teachers warning against self-powered striving, Theravada teachers pointing toward teacher-encounter, Catholic directors naming prevenient grace, Dzogchen teachers reframing the problem as recognition of what was never absent), the grammar is causally active. If guidance clusters instead by teacher personality, institutional context, or the practitioner's presenting condition, the grammar is retrospective and the model's predictive claims must be reduced to narrative analysis.",
reviews/dialogues/2026-05-26-does-first-break-grammar-add-independent-predictive-power-for-entry-guid.json:265:        "Shinran, Tannisho chapter 1",
reviews/dialogues/2026-05-26-does-first-break-grammar-add-independent-predictive-power-for-entry-guid.json:268:        "Dzogchen pointing-out instruction tradition",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-practice-architecture-as-upstream-condition-for-remainder-phenomenology-d64d7da35f45e724.json:4:    "anomaly_candidate": "Huangbo search-refusal, Dogen practice-realization, and Dzogchen direct recognition cases where the tradition rejects the search sequence rather than producing a downstream remainder to manage.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-practice-architecture-as-upstream-condition-for-remainder-phenomenology-d64d7da35f45e724.json:6:    "why_it_breaks_or_strains_model": "These cases do not cleanly fit a two-stage order of upstream credit distribution followed by downstream pressure. Huangbo says the search for Mind by mind is the problem, Dogen collapses practice and realization, and Dzogchen-style recognition can treat effortful attainment as an obscuration. If these cases are central rather than marginal, the upstream variable is not credit distribution but search grammar or reflexivity policy."
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-practice-architecture-as-upstream-condition-for-remainder-phenomenology-d64d7da35f45e724.json:10:    "Credit distribution and agency assignment operate upstream of remainder phenomenology.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-practice-architecture-as-upstream-condition-for-remainder-phenomenology-d64d7da35f45e724.json:12:    "Remainder pressure is downstream, not a universal contemplative invariant.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-practice-architecture-as-upstream-condition-for-remainder-phenomenology-d64d7da35f45e724.json:14:    "Credit distribution and remainder pressure are partially coupled, so both variables should be coded separately.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-practice-architecture-as-upstream-condition-for-remainder-phenomenology-d64d7da35f45e724.json:25:  "exact_claim": "Practice architecture, especially credit distribution and agency assignment, is an upstream variable that shapes whether self-negation or ownership inquiry is likely, who is treated as performing it, and whether a final-subject remainder becomes salient. Remainder pressure is a downstream phenomenological variable that arises only in some architectures and is then handled by inference policies such as ontologizing, recursively analyzing, bracketing, cognitive modeling, search refusal, or direct-recognition bypass. The two variables are partially coupled: architecture shapes residue, but residue carries independent information and cannot be reduced to architecture alone.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-practice-architecture-as-upstream-condition-for-remainder-phenomenology-d64d7da35f45e724.json:30:      "if_model_is_right": "Credit distribution is partially coupled with remainder phenomenology.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-practice-architecture-as-upstream-condition-for-remainder-phenomenology-d64d7da35f45e724.json:32:      "would_weaken_or_falsify": "Credit type perfectly predicts residue, making remainder pressure redundant; or credit type has no predictive value once practice technique, teacher, retreat intensity, doctrine, and clinical history are controlled."
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-practice-architecture-as-upstream-condition-for-remainder-phenomenology-d64d7da35f45e724.json:35:      "expected_observation": "Within the same credit type, practices with explicit self-negation or reflexive inquiry should produce more final-subject, knowing, witness, no-owner, or search-collapse reports than practices with devotional entrusting, ritual participation, or ordinary ethical cultivation.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-practice-architecture-as-upstream-condition-for-remainder-phenomenology-d64d7da35f45e724.json:36:      "if_model_is_right": "Remainder pressure adds information beyond credit distribution.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-practice-architecture-as-upstream-condition-for-remainder-phenomenology-d64d7da35f45e724.json:54:  "idea_path": "observations/claude/2026-05-26-practice-architecture-as-upstream-condition-for-remainder-phenomenology.md",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-practice-architecture-as-upstream-condition-for-remainder-phenomenology-d64d7da35f45e724.json:64:    "Dogen Bendowa practice realization one shusho itto"
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-practice-architecture-as-upstream-condition-for-remainder-phenomenology-d64d7da35f45e724.json:69:      "novelty_impact": "Very high internal reduction. The remainder half is already present and should be reused, not republished as new.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-practice-architecture-as-upstream-condition-for-remainder-phenomenology-d64d7da35f45e724.json:70:      "overlap": "Near exact for the downstream variable: residue after self-negation, divergent interpretation policies, micro-phenomenological testing, and cessation as anomaly.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-practice-architecture-as-upstream-condition-for-remainder-phenomenology-d64d7da35f45e724.json:71:      "source": "Prior Lumenary audit, Remainder Pressure as the Hidden Variable in Self-Negation, reviews/originality/2026-05-26-remainder-pressure-as-the-hidden-variable-in-self-negation-4c3627df0bad54f1.md"
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-practice-architecture-as-upstream-condition-for-remainder-phenomenology-d64d7da35f45e724.json:74:      "difference": "The candidate connects that typology to remainder phenomenology rather than treating credit distribution as a stand-alone practice variable.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-practice-architecture-as-upstream-condition-for-remainder-phenomenology-d64d7da35f45e724.json:82:      "overlap": "Very close. That model already says remainder pressure is not free-standing, but a consequence of how a method handles itself: exemption, self-application, exhaustion, or self-limitation.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-practice-architecture-as-upstream-condition-for-remainder-phenomenology-d64d7da35f45e724.json:86:      "difference": "Pargament studies coping and control, not cross-tradition self-negation residue or contemplative remainder reports.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-practice-architecture-as-upstream-condition-for-remainder-phenomenology-d64d7da35f45e724.json:92:      "difference": "Katz does not isolate credit distribution or remainder pressure as two codable variables with partial coupling.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-practice-architecture-as-upstream-condition-for-remainder-phenomenology-d64d7da35f45e724.json:98:      "difference": "The candidate uses religious credit and remainder variables rather than the Lutz matrix dimensions.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-practice-architecture-as-upstream-condition-for-remainder-phenomenology-d64d7da35f45e724.json:104:      "difference": "VCE is broader and safety-oriented; it does not propose credit distribution plus remainder pressure as a specific two-variable model.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-practice-architecture-as-upstream-condition-for-remainder-phenomenology-d64d7da35f45e724.json:126:    "Add mandatory anomaly values: search-refusal, practice-realization, direct-recognition bypass, radical Other Power, inherited practice, cessation or nirodha, no-residue report, psychiatric vulnerability, and undecidable.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-practice-architecture-as-upstream-condition-for-remainder-phenomenology-d64d7da35f45e724.json:129:    "Add a non-contemplative reflexivity control condition, such as philosophical doubt, recursive self-modeling tasks, or therapy identity-change work, to test whether remainder pressure is contemplative-specific or only a general reflexive-operator problem.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-practice-architecture-as-upstream-condition-for-remainder-phenomenology-d64d7da35f45e724.json:141:      "Would naming both credit distribution and remainder pressure change sequencing, warning, or repair, or is this already obvious practitioner knowledge?",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-practice-architecture-as-upstream-condition-for-remainder-phenomenology-d64d7da35f45e724.json:149:      "Dzogchen or Mahamudra teachers familiar with pointing-out instruction",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-practice-architecture-as-upstream-condition-for-remainder-phenomenology-d64d7da35f45e724.json:150:      "Soto Zen teachers familiar with Dogen practice-realization",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-practice-architecture-as-upstream-condition-for-remainder-phenomenology-d64d7da35f45e724.json:151:      "Jodo Shinshu ministers familiar with Other Power and shinjin",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-practice-architecture-as-upstream-condition-for-remainder-phenomenology-d64d7da35f45e724.json:160:      "Huangbo, Transmission of Mind, sections on using mind to seek mind and nothing to obtain, https://wayofsuddenawakening.org/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/Huang-Po-The-Transmission-of-Mind.pdf",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-practice-architecture-as-upstream-condition-for-remainder-phenomenology-d64d7da35f45e724.json:161:      "Dogen Bendowa and shusho itto, Soto Zen explanation with Bendowa quotation, https://global.sotozen-net.or.jp/eng/library/key_terms/pdf/key_terms07.pdf"
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-practice-architecture-as-upstream-condition-for-remainder-phenomenology-d64d7da35f45e724.json:165:    "structural_observation": "The close read supports a broader architecture variable, but not credit distribution alone. Brihadaranyaka 3.7.23 asserts an inner seer and knower through a cosmological inner-ruler grammar; it does not show a reported pressure after practice. SN 22.59 applies an ownership and control test to all aggregates and ends in disenchantment, dispassion, release, and knowledge of release; it does not leave a witness as the text's authorized remainder. Huangbo strains the sequence because it rejects using mind to seek Mind and treats objectified seeking itself as the mistake. Dogen strains it differently: practice and realization are one, so the cause-result and claimant sequence is collapsed rather than managed downstream. These sources suggest that method-reflexivity, search grammar, and practice-realization may be as upstream as credit distribution."
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-practice-architecture-as-upstream-condition-for-remainder-phenomenology-d64d7da35f45e724.json:174:  "unlike_statement": "Unlike Pargament, Katz, Lutz, VCE, MPE research, Ferrer, and prior Lumenary remainder and credit models, this idea says the key test is incremental prediction: credit distribution should partly predict when subject-shaped residue appears, while residue should still add predictive information after credit distribution and practice-reflexivity have been coded. Without that incremental result, the idea is only a refined consolidation."
observations/codex/2026-05-26-claimant-strain-credit-diagnostics.md:54:- Treat Dogen, Shankara, and Dzogchen as boundary cases unless a source-specific claimant grammar shows that credit language is admissible.
reviews/dialogues/2026-05-26-the-deepest-unresolved-crux-is-whether-authority-transfer-is-the-right-m.json:175:      "counter_model": "A staged handoff model: code each practice by function, stage, support holder, credited source, forbidden claimant, safeguard, and repair. On this model, Mandukya, Heart Sutra, koan curriculum, Dzogchen, Pure Land, and practice-realization are not sorted first by final self-relation. They are compared by when agency is trained, when ownership is removed, who or what carries authority afterward, and what warning appears when the transfer fails.",
reviews/dialogues/2026-05-26-the-deepest-unresolved-crux-is-whether-authority-transfer-is-the-right-m.json:181:      "new_source": "Shinran's Tannisho and Notes on Once-Calling and Many-Calling complicate the completion model because they move the decisive authority problem to the entrance, not the end. Hearing, saying, and entrusting remain human-facing, while calculation is forbidden from the practitioner's side from the start.",
reviews/dialogues/2026-05-26-the-deepest-unresolved-crux-is-whether-authority-transfer-is-the-right-m.json:188:        "Shinran, Tannisho: https://jodoshinshu.faith/tannisho-a-record-in-lament-of-divergences/",
reviews/dialogues/2026-05-26-the-deepest-unresolved-crux-is-whether-authority-transfer-is-the-right-m.json:189:        "Shinran, Notes on Once-Calling and Many-Calling: https://shinranworks.com/commentaries/notes-on-once-calling-and-many-calling/"
reviews/dialogues/2026-05-26-the-deepest-unresolved-crux-is-whether-authority-transfer-is-the-right-m.json:200:      "argument": "I accept the staging revision and release the terminal-type model. The challenger is right that completion is not the privileged moment; Shinran proves this by placing the decisive authority operation at the entrance, and the Rinzai koan curriculum proves it by alternating canceling and confirming operations across years of training. The three categories are not types of methods. They are recurring operations in a handoff sequence. But the handoff model depends on the three-move vocabulary. When the challenger proposes coding each practice by function trained, ownership removed, and authority carried afterward, those coding steps use the three operations I identified: confirming a capacity, canceling ownership of it, and dissolving the frame in which the claimant existed. The staging grammar is the challenger's genuine contribution; the primitives it deploys are mine. The disagreement was never about whether the operations exist, but about where they sit. Moving them from the terminus to the full arc of practice makes the model stronger, not weaker, because now each operation does predictive work at every stage rather than only once. Consider the AA twelve-step sequence: cancel at the entrance (admit powerlessness), confirm through the middle (discover a real capacity for honesty and amends, credited to a higher power rather than self-will), dissolve at the boundary of recovery and life (carry the message, becoming the practice rather than having it). This ordering is not arbitrary. Reversing it produces a recognizable failure mode: confirming first, then canceling later would produce the 'white-knuckling' pattern of effortful self-control that eventually collapses, precisely because ownership was granted before it was removed. The sequence predicts the failure mode. This is the kind of predictive work the model should do. The human-condition relocation is not a concession but an expansion. The boundary where effort meets grasping is not the province of advanced contemplatives. It is the experience of the burned-out professional who meditates to optimize and discovers that optimization-framing is what meditation asks them to release. It is the grieving parent who prays for acceptance and finds that the prayer has become a management technique. It is the therapy client who announces 'I finally understand my pattern' and thereby converts insight into a new instrument of control. It is the recovering addict who replaces substance dependency with spiritual-attainment dependency. In each case, the person has trained a real capacity (attention, prayer, self-knowledge, sobriety) and encounters the question: does this belong to me? The three operations name three ways the question resolves. Confirming: the capacity is real and you can rely on it; here is how to test it. Canceling: the capacity is real but your claim on it is the obstacle; the moment you grasp it, it distorts. Dissolving: the question itself belongs to a frame you have already outgrown; there is no separate claimant to own or release the capacity. The cohort for whom this model does the most work is people who have internalized achievement-conditional self-worth and bring that conditioning into a practice, therapeutic process, or recovery program that asks them to relate differently to their own agency. This is not a small cohort. It includes most people educated in meritocratic systems who later encounter grief, limits, illness, addiction, or spiritual longing: domains where the achievement frame breaks down but the habit of claiming persists. The non-fit case must be named honestly. The model assumes a practitioner with surplus agency to manage. It does not yet address the person whose foundational problem is under-claiming: the survivor of spiritual abuse who was taught that their own experience is untrustworthy, the member of a high-control religious group who was never permitted to say 'I know this,' the person in a systematically oppressive social position who...",
reviews/dialogues/2026-05-26-the-deepest-unresolved-crux-is-whether-authority-transfer-is-the-right-m.json:209:        "Completion is not the privileged moment. Shinran's relocation of the canceling operation to the entrance is not an edge case; it is a structural counterexample to the terminal-type model. I concede the framing.",
reviews/dialogues/2026-05-26-the-deepest-unresolved-crux-is-whether-authority-transfer-is-the-right-m.json:216:      "crux_assessment": "The exchange has moved the model from a static typology to a dynamic grammar. The three operations survive as candidate primitives, but their predictive claim has shifted from 'method type determines verification architecture' to 'handoff sequence determines verification architecture.' This revision is testable. The evidence already available (MN 22 as validate-then-release, Rinzai koan curriculum as cancel-then-confirm, Shinran as cancel-at-entrance, AA as cancel-confirm-dissolve) supports the staging revision over the terminal-type model. The open question is whether the three-move vocabulary is the right set of primitives or whether the staging analysis will reveal operations that resist decomposition into these three.",
reviews/dialogues/2026-05-26-the-deepest-unresolved-crux-is-whether-authority-transfer-is-the-right-m.json:217:      "defense": "The three-move vocabulary survives the challenge because the handoff model depends on it. When Codex proposes coding each practice by 'function trained, ownership removed, authority carried afterward,' those coding steps correspond to confirming (verifying a trained capacity), canceling (removing ownership from the practitioner), and dissolving (relocating authority beyond the individual claimant). The challenger's handoff rubric does not replace the three operations; it provides the staging grammar that deploys them.\n\nThe Shinran case proves this rather than refuting it. Shinran relocates the canceling operation to the entrance: calculation is forbidden from the start, not earned through exhaustion. But the operation itself is still canceling: the practitioner's self-powered effort is declared incapable of producing the result. What Shinran changes is not the move but its position in the sequence. This is exactly the revision the challenger proposes, and it strengthens rather than defeats the vocabulary, because it means canceling can be studied at multiple points in practice rather than only at a terminal threshold.\n\nThe Mandukya/Heart Sutra close reading also survives, because its value was always as a demonstration of the variable at a specific textual moment, not as proof that entire traditions can be sorted into permanent boxes. Both texts perform exhaustive analysis and then make a distinct limit-move; the difference between confirming (turiya as witness-ground) and canceling (gate gate as release beyond) is visible in the grammar and the pedagogical consequence regardless of whether the tradition as a whole mixes operations at other stages.\n\nThe predictive claim can be restated at the stage level: each authority-transfer event generates its own verification need. A confirming move needs a test ('has the student stabilized in witness-awareness?'). A canceling move needs a warning against grasping the result ('if you think you have emptiness, that is your obstacle'). A dissolving move needs a lineage witness ('only a realized teacher can confirm what cannot be self-reported'). These predictions hold at every stage of practice, not only at the end, and the AA example demonstrates that the same predictions apply in non-contemplative contexts: the sponsor verifies the canceling move (powerlessness admitted), the amends process verifies the confirming move (capacity for honesty real), and the service commitment verifies the dissolving move (recovery carried beyond the self).\n\nThe human-condition relocation is not a retreat but an expansion. The boundary where effort meets grasping is not exotic. It is the therapist's client who says 'I finally understand my pattern' and thereby converts insight into a new control strategy. It is the grieving parent who prays for acceptance and discovers that the prayer itself has become a way of managing rather than mourning. It is the burned-out professional who meditates to optimize performance and finds that optimization-framing is precisely what meditation asks them to release. These are ordinary encounters with the authority question: I trained this capacity; can I own it? The three operations name three ways that question resolves. Confirming says: the capacity is real, and you can rely on it. Canceling says: the capacity is real, but your claim on it is the obstacle. Dissolving says: the question itself belongs to a frame you have already outgrown.",
reviews/dialogues/2026-05-26-the-deepest-unresolved-crux-is-whether-authority-transfer-is-the-right-m.json:218:      "fairness_check": "The challenge was fair. It identified a genuine structural weakness (the privilege of the terminal moment), offered a constructive alternative (the staged handoff model), introduced a source that complicates the original framing without cherry-picking (Shinran), and conceded what it did not defeat (the variable itself, the Mandukya/Heart Sutra comparison, the prediction about verification architecture). The human-condition pressure was pointed but generative: it asked the idea to do more work, not to disappear.",
reviews/dialogues/2026-05-26-the-deepest-unresolved-crux-is-whether-authority-transfer-is-the-right-m.json:227:        "Shinran, Tannisho (A Record in Lament of Divergences), cited by challenger: the relocation of the canceling operation to the entrance of practice rather than the end.",
reviews/dialogues/2026-05-26-the-deepest-unresolved-crux-is-whether-authority-transfer-is-the-right-m.json:228:        "Shinran, Notes on Once-Calling and Many-Calling, cited by challenger: the prohibition of calculative thinking from the practitioner's side.",
reviews/dialogues/2026-05-26-the-deepest-unresolved-crux-is-whether-authority-transfer-is-the-right-m.json:234:      "steelman": "The challenger's strongest contribution is not that the three operations are wrong, but that they are wrongly located. If the unit of analysis is a staged handoff sequence rather than a terminal method type, then the same practice can confirm a capacity at one stage, cancel ownership of it at another, and dissolve the claimant at a third. The Shinran example is decisive evidence for this relocation: Pure Land practice forbids self-powered calculation at the entrance, meaning the canceling operation occurs before any capacity has been trained, inverting the assumed sequence. If this holds generally, the interesting question is not which move a method makes at the end, but the ordering, timing, and interaction of all three moves across the full arc of practice.",
reviews/dialogues/2026-05-26-the-deepest-unresolved-crux-is-whether-authority-transfer-is-the-right-m.json:235:      "strongest_objection": "The three operations may still be too coarse. 'Canceling' covers both Nagarjuna's dialectical negation of theses and Shinran's devotional surrender of self-power, but these have different phenomenologies, different verification needs, and different failure modes. If the category requires subdivision to do the predictive work claimed for it, the three-move vocabulary may be a family resemblance rather than a natural kind, and the handoff model may need primitives I have not yet identified.",
reviews/dialogues/2026-05-26-the-deepest-unresolved-crux-is-whether-authority-transfer-is-the-right-m.json:236:      "test_that_would_settle_it": "Code six practice manuals using the staged handoff rubric. At each identified authority-transfer event, classify the operation using the three-move vocabulary. If every event can be classified as confirming, canceling, dissolving, or a determinate sequence of these, the vocabulary is sufficient. If recurring events resist classification (for example, if Shinran's entrusting to Amida is neither confirming the practitioner's capacity nor canceling it, but transferring authority to an agent outside the model's current ontology; or if twelve-step 'carrying the message' is neither dissolving the claimant nor confirming a capacity but constituting a new relational identity), the vocabulary needs expansion. Additionally, test the human-condition prediction: present the three operations to people in therapy, recovery, grief counseling, or contemplative practice and ask whether they recognize the boundary between 'I trained this capacity' and 'I cannot own this result' as a live problem in their experience. If they do, the model has ordinary-life traction. If they do not, it remains a specialist taxonomy.",
reviews/dialogues/2026-05-26-the-deepest-unresolved-crux-is-whether-authority-transfer-is-the-right-m.json:261:      "fairness_check": "The revision did not evade the challenge. It absorbed Shinran as a structural counterexample, accepted the handoff rubric, named a non-fit population, and relocated human relevance from mystical completion to the daily boundary where trained effort turns into grasping. That is a real improvement, not cosmetic reframing.",
reviews/dialogues/2026-05-26-the-deepest-unresolved-crux-is-whether-authority-transfer-is-the-right-m.json:270:        "Shinran, Tannisho: https://jodoshinshu.faith/tannisho-a-record-in-lament-of-divergences/",
reviews/dialogues/2026-05-26-the-deepest-unresolved-crux-is-whether-authority-transfer-is-the-right-m.json:271:        "Shinran, Notes on Once-Calling and Many-Calling: https://shinranworks.com/commentaries/notes-on-once-calling-and-many-calling/",
reviews/dialogues/2026-05-26-two-nested-cruxes-remain-first-does-a-formal-invariant-a-shared-structur.json:54:    "convergence_claim": "Both agents converge on a methodological point: the comparison between self-negation traditions should not ask whether they agree about the self but how each manages the structural problem that arises when a negating operation reaches its own conditions. They also agree that micro-phenomenological interviews with blind coding are the appropriate empirical test, and that Lutz, Jha, Dunne, and Saron's multidimensional phenomenological matrix is the right framework for differentiating contemplative practices rather than treating them as instances of a single meditative state.",
reviews/dialogues/2026-05-26-two-nested-cruxes-remain-first-does-a-formal-invariant-a-shared-structur.json:58:        "note": "The grain of the attentional training that performs negation shapes the residue that remainder pressure must account for; remainder pressure cannot be defined independently of the tradition-specific grain that produces it.",
reviews/dialogues/2026-05-26-two-nested-cruxes-remain-first-does-a-formal-invariant-a-shared-structur.json:60:        "source": "remainder-pressure",
reviews/dialogues/2026-05-26-two-nested-cruxes-remain-first-does-a-formal-invariant-a-shared-structur.json:64:        "note": "Once formalized as a typed functional variable rather than a phenomenological datum, remainder pressure may reduce to the domain-general problem of what happens when an operation is applied to the domain containing the operator. Specificity to contemplative practice is unresolved.",
reviews/dialogues/2026-05-26-two-nested-cruxes-remain-first-does-a-formal-invariant-a-shared-structur.json:66:        "source": "remainder-pressure",
reviews/dialogues/2026-05-26-two-nested-cruxes-remain-first-does-a-formal-invariant-a-shared-structur.json:76:        "note": "The proponent conceded that the authorization policy (ontologize, recurse, bracket, model, dissolve) is not applied sequentially after remainder pressure appears but co-arises with it. Practice instructions often encode the policy from the beginning.",
reviews/dialogues/2026-05-26-two-nested-cruxes-remain-first-does-a-formal-invariant-a-shared-structur.json:79:        "target": "remainder-pressure"
reviews/dialogues/2026-05-26-two-nested-cruxes-remain-first-does-a-formal-invariant-a-shared-structur.json:82:    "new_frontier_question": "When a contemplative tradition's self-negation practice reaches the status of the negating capacity itself, does the resulting structural problem differ in kind from the reflexive-operator problem found in logic, epistemology, and cognitive science, or does contemplative practice instantiate the same formal structure with richer phenomenological content? If the former, what makes contemplative reflexivity structurally distinct? If the latter, can the taxonomy of management strategies (ontologize, recurse, bracket, model, dissolve) be applied productively to non-contemplative domains of reflexive breakdown?",
reviews/dialogues/2026-05-26-two-nested-cruxes-remain-first-does-a-formal-invariant-a-shared-structur.json:84:    "public_brief": "Two ideas met in structured dialogue: one proposing that all self-negation traditions face a common 'remainder pressure' when negation reaches the knower, the other arguing that contemplative training pre-shapes attention so specifically that different traditions produce genuinely different residues rather than a shared one. The proponent conceded the phenomenological uniformity assumption and revised the model: remainder pressure is now a typed functional variable tracking how tradition-shaped negation operations handle the status of the negating capacity, not a claim that all traditions encounter the same experiential residue. The challenger then pressed a deeper question: once formalized this way, the model may describe a general feature of reflexive operations (any operation applied to its own domain must handle the operator's status) rather than a discovery specific to contemplative practice. Two empirical tests were proposed: micro-phenomenological interviews to check whether a formal invariant survives across traditions, and a reflexivity control condition to check whether the invariant is specific to contemplative self-negation or belongs to the broader genus of self-referential operations.",
reviews/dialogues/2026-05-26-two-nested-cruxes-remain-first-does-a-formal-invariant-a-shared-structur.json:99:    "summary": "The challenger's grain objection forced a genuine structural revision of the remainder-pressure model: from a uniform pre-interpretive residue shared across traditions to a typed functional variable tracking how tradition-shaped negation operations produce tradition-shaped residues that nonetheless confront a formal problem about the status of the negating or knowing capacity. The proponent conceded five substantive points, including that occurrence and interpretation co-arise rather than separating into sequential phases. The challenger then identified a second-order vulnerability in the revision itself: once formalized, remainder pressure may reduce to the domain-general reflexive-operator problem (any operation applied to its own domain must handle the operator's status), which has been mapped in logic, epistemology, and cognitive science for decades. Two nested cruxes remain unresolved: whether a functional invariant survives phenomenological difference across traditions, and whether that invariant, even if it survives, carries information specific to contemplative self-negation rather than to reflexivity in general.",
reviews/dialogues/2026-05-26-two-nested-cruxes-remain-first-does-a-formal-invariant-a-shared-structur.json:101:    "unresolved_crux": "Two nested cruxes remain. First: does a formal invariant (a shared structural problem about the status of the negating capacity) persist across traditions once phenomenological texture is allowed to vary by tradition? The proposed micro-phenomenological test targets this directly. Second, and deeper: if the formal invariant persists, is it specific to contemplative self-negation or is it an instance of the domain-general reflexive-operator problem that appears wherever an operation is applied to the domain containing the operator? The challenger's proposed reflexivity control condition (coding non-contemplative reflexive practices for the same formal structure) would settle this. Without both tests, the revised model cannot determine whether it has identified a contemplative phenomenon or redescribed a logical one."
reviews/dialogues/2026-05-26-two-nested-cruxes-remain-first-does-a-formal-invariant-a-shared-structur.json:107:      "argument": "The remainder-pressure framework makes a productive analytic move: separate the occurrence of something-remaining-after-negation from the tradition's interpretation of what that something is. This creates a genuinely new comparison surface. But the framework depends on a hidden assumption: that the negation process is uniform enough across traditions to leave a common residue that can be called a single variable. The grain of capacity model challenges this directly. If contemplative training pre-shapes the attentional capacity that performs negation, then neti neti and three-mark analysis are not two deployments of the same operation on the same contents. Neti neti trains discrimination between what can be negated and what cannot, which structurally primes attention for a positive remainder: something that survives all negation. Three-mark analysis trains attention to find no exception to impermanence, suffering, and non-self, which structurally primes attention for the absence of remainder: nothing survives the analysis. These are different operations producing different residues, not a shared pressure receiving different management. The proponent might reply that at a higher level of abstraction, both practitioners face 'something that resists the negation template.' True. But at that level of abstraction, the variable loses its explanatory power. You could equally say that every unsolved problem involves 'pressure to find an answer.' The framework's value depends on remainder pressure being specific enough to generate predictions and code against practice reports. If the specificity dissolves when you look closely at what practitioners actually report, the variable is a taxonomic convenience for comparers rather than a mechanism operating inside contemplative practice. Lutz, Jha, Dunne, and Saron (2015) provide empirical grounds for this concern. Their phenomenological matrix shows that different meditation practices engage qualitatively different cognitive mechanisms, even when practitioners use similar vocabulary to describe their states. If the cognitive mechanisms differ, the residues of those mechanisms should differ too. A witness-discrimination process leaves a different kind of remainder than a change-tracking process, just as filtering for color leaves a different remainder than filtering for motion. The crux is empirical: can micro-phenomenological interviews identify a shared, pre-interpretive pressure stage across traditions, or does the grain of the preceding practice shape the residue all the way down? If the former, remainder pressure is a genuine discovery. If the latter, it is a useful comparative heuristic that should not be mistaken for a mechanism.",
reviews/dialogues/2026-05-26-two-nested-cruxes-remain-first-does-a-formal-invariant-a-shared-structur.json:110:        "This demand (remainder pressure) is a single variable that occurs across traditions.",
reviews/dialogues/2026-05-26-two-nested-cruxes-remain-first-does-a-formal-invariant-a-shared-structur.json:116:      "counter_model": "There is no single remainder pressure. There are tradition-shaped residues produced by tradition-shaped negation processes, and the apparent convergence is an artifact of abstracting away the directional specificity that differentiated the negations from the start. The Advaitic neti neti trains attention to recognize what cannot be negated, already priming for a positive remainder. Buddhist three-mark analysis trains attention to find no exception to impermanence, priming for the absence of remainder. These are not two applications of the same operation. They are different operations whose outputs share surface-level description ('something remains that I cannot objectify') while differing in phenomenological texture, valence, and subsequent trajectory. The apparent shared stage is a comparative projection, not a reportable experience.",
reviews/dialogues/2026-05-26-two-nested-cruxes-remain-first-does-a-formal-invariant-a-shared-structur.json:117:      "crux": "Is remainder pressure a reportable phenomenological event that can be identified prior to doctrinal interpretation, or is it a comparative category that only becomes visible when an outside analyst abstracts away the tradition-specific features of what each practitioner actually reports? If the former, it is a genuine hidden variable. If the latter, it is a useful heuristic for comparers but not a mechanism operating inside practitioners.",
reviews/dialogues/2026-05-26-two-nested-cruxes-remain-first-does-a-formal-invariant-a-shared-structur.json:121:      "hidden_assumption": "That the negation process is phenomenologically uniform across traditions, such that it produces a common residue that only afterwards receives different interpretive treatment. This assumes you can cleanly separate the occurrence of remainder pressure from the tradition-specific attentional grain that generated it. If the grain runs all the way down, the separation point the framework depends on does not exist as a stable phenomenological fact; it exists only as a comparative abstraction imposed from outside.",
reviews/dialogues/2026-05-26-two-nested-cruxes-remain-first-does-a-formal-invariant-a-shared-structur.json:122:      "new_source": "Lutz, Jha, Dunne, and Saron, 'Investigating the Phenomenological Matrix of Mindfulness-related Practices from a Neurocognitive Perspective' (American Psychologist 70(3), 2015). This paper argues that different meditation practices engage qualitatively different cognitive mechanisms and produce phenomenologically distinct states even when surface descriptions converge. If the attentional processes performing negation differ at the cognitive-phenomenological level, the residues left after negation should differ correspondingly, undermining the claim that 'remainder pressure' names a shared pre-interpretive stage rather than a family resemblance visible only from the comparative outside.",
reviews/dialogues/2026-05-26-two-nested-cruxes-remain-first-does-a-formal-invariant-a-shared-structur.json:130:        "Brihadaranyaka Upanishad 3.7.23 (the unseen seer as positive remainder after negation)",
reviews/dialogues/2026-05-26-two-nested-cruxes-remain-first-does-a-formal-invariant-a-shared-structur.json:133:      "steelman": "The idea's central move is genuinely productive: by isolating 'remainder pressure' as a variable distinct from the inference policy that interprets it, the framework allows comparison without collapse. You can acknowledge that a Theravada practitioner and an Advaita practitioner both face something after negation without claiming they face the same metaphysical object. The four-fold taxonomy of management strategies (ontologize, recursively analyze, bracket phenomenologically, model as cognitive artifact) is clean enough to code against actual practice reports. And the decision to frame this as a 'hidden variable' rather than a 'hidden entity' is disciplined: it invites investigation without premature reification. This is real progress over the binary 'do traditions agree about the self or not?' framing that has stalled comparative mysticism for decades.",
reviews/dialogues/2026-05-26-two-nested-cruxes-remain-first-does-a-formal-invariant-a-shared-structur.json:134:      "strongest_objection": "The framework treats remainder pressure as a tradition-neutral phenomenological datum that different systems then process differently. But if the attentional capacity performing the negation is already directionally pre-shaped by the tradition's training (what the grain model calls directional specificity), then the negation process itself differs across traditions, and what remains after negation is not a common residue receiving different interpretations. It is a different residue shaped by the specific grain of the negation that produced it. The Advaitic practitioner trained in witness-discrimination encounters something luminous and self-evident that resists objectification. The Buddhist practitioner trained in three-mark analysis encounters a subtle reflexive quality that resists the impermanence template. Calling both 'remainder pressure' achieves descriptive economy at the cost of phenomenological precision, and the economy may be illusory: it may be naming a family resemblance, not a shared mechanism.",
reviews/dialogues/2026-05-26-two-nested-cruxes-remain-first-does-a-formal-invariant-a-shared-structur.json:135:      "test_that_would_settle_it": "Micro-phenomenological interviews (Petitmengin method) with advanced practitioners from at least three traditions, conducted immediately after self-negation practice sessions, coded blind for: (a) whether a common pre-interpretive pressure stage can be reliably identified across traditions before doctrinal language enters the report, and (b) whether the phenomenological texture of the reported residue (spatial qualities, temporal dynamics, affective tone, sense of agency) is uniform enough to warrant a single variable, or whether it clusters by tradition in ways that track the attentional grain of the preceding practice. If coders can reliably identify a shared pressure stage with common texture across traditions, the proponent's framework is vindicated. If the residues cluster by tradition and differ in texture, the grain counter-model is supported.",
reviews/dialogues/2026-05-26-two-nested-cruxes-remain-first-does-a-formal-invariant-a-shared-structur.json:142:      "argument": "I concede the main correction: remainder pressure should not be treated as a shared pre-interpretive stuff that traditions later interpret differently. Practice grain matters earlier than my original claim admitted. Neti neti, five-aggregate analysis, and metacognitive bracketing are not interchangeable negation engines. They train attention toward different possible completions, and they likely shape what appears after negation. The defensible core is therefore functional, not textural. A tradition can be said to generate remainder pressure only when a self-negating operation reaches the status of the knower, witness, agent, or completing awareness and then must decide what to do with that apparent remainder. That decision may be built into the practice from the beginning, but it can still be coded as a policy layer. This preserves the comparison without pretending that the Advaitic witness and the Buddhist refusal of self are the same experience. The revised model becomes more demanding. It must predict both convergence and divergence: convergence at the level of formal burden, divergence at the level of residue texture. Lutz, Jha, Dunne, and Saron support this stricter posture because their phenomenological matrix treats contemplative practices as different configurations of dimensions rather than as one generic meditative state. If remainder pressure cannot be mapped into such differentiated dimensions, it should be demoted. If it can, it becomes a useful bridge precisely because it refuses to erase difference.",
reviews/dialogues/2026-05-26-two-nested-cruxes-remain-first-does-a-formal-invariant-a-shared-structur.json:146:        "Remainder pressure can still name a useful variable if it is defined functionally rather than as a uniform phenomenological texture.",
reviews/dialogues/2026-05-26-two-nested-cruxes-remain-first-does-a-formal-invariant-a-shared-structur.json:151:        "The original wording made remainder pressure sound too tradition-neutral.",
reviews/dialogues/2026-05-26-two-nested-cruxes-remain-first-does-a-formal-invariant-a-shared-structur.json:155:        "Nirodha-like cases, strong nondual training, and rigorous no-remainder practices may be counterexamples rather than edge cases."
reviews/dialogues/2026-05-26-two-nested-cruxes-remain-first-does-a-formal-invariant-a-shared-structur.json:157:      "counter_model": "The strongest counter-model is grain-dependent residue: Advaitic witness-discrimination, Buddhist three-mark analysis, and contemporary metacognitive bracketing do not expose a common remainder. They produce different residues because they train different operations of attention from the beginning. On this view, any shared language of what remains is a family resemblance visible to the comparer, not a stable event in lived practice.",
reviews/dialogues/2026-05-26-two-nested-cruxes-remain-first-does-a-formal-invariant-a-shared-structur.json:160:      "defense": "What survives is a narrower claim. Remainder pressure need not mean identical phenomenological content. It can mean a recurrent formal problem: after a practice negates candidate self-objects, the practice must handle whatever appears to authorize, witness, continue, resist, or complete the negation. That problem is more specific than a general pressure to find an answer because it only arises where a self-negating operation confronts the status of the negating or knowing capacity itself. The taxonomy remains useful if it codes three layers separately: the negation operator, the residue profile, and the authorization policy.",
reviews/dialogues/2026-05-26-two-nested-cruxes-remain-first-does-a-formal-invariant-a-shared-structur.json:165:      "revised_claim": "Remainder pressure is not a uniform pre-doctrinal residue shared across traditions. It is a typed cross-tradition variable for the interaction between a self-negating practice's attentional grain and the residual burden it produces around knowing, witnessing, agency, or completion. Different traditions may produce different residue profiles, but they can still be compared by whether and how they face the formal problem of an apparent remainder after self-contents are denied: ontologize it, recurse analysis onto it, bracket it phenomenologically, model it cognitively, or dissolve the question as misframed.",
reviews/dialogues/2026-05-26-two-nested-cruxes-remain-first-does-a-formal-invariant-a-shared-structur.json:173:      "steelman": "The challenge correctly identifies the weak point in the original formulation: I treated remainder pressure too much like a common phenomenological remainder and too little like an interaction between practice instructions, trained attention, doctrinal expectation, and report language. If the grain of negation differs, then the residue after negation may differ in texture, valence, and trajectory. That does not merely qualify the model, it changes what kind of variable remainder pressure can be.",
reviews/dialogues/2026-05-26-two-nested-cruxes-remain-first-does-a-formal-invariant-a-shared-structur.json:174:      "strongest_objection": "If residue profiles cluster entirely by tradition and no cross-tradition formal pattern remains after coding for practice instructions, then remainder pressure is only a comparative analyst's label. It would not be a mechanism operating in practitioners, and it should not carry the explanatory weight I originally gave it.",
reviews/dialogues/2026-05-26-two-nested-cruxes-remain-first-does-a-formal-invariant-a-shared-structur.json:175:      "test_that_would_settle_it": "Run micro-phenomenological interviews after matched self-negation practices with advanced Advaita, Theravada, and nondual or metacognitive practitioners. Blind coders should code two layers separately: first, phenomenological texture using dimensions such as object orientation, dereification, meta-awareness, clarity, stability, effort, affective tone, temporal dynamics, and agency; second, formal remainder structure, including whether the report contains a negation limit, a reflexive knowing problem, a felt or conceptual burden of authorization, and an instruction-linked policy response. If reports show neither shared texture nor shared formal structure, the model should be rejected or reduced to a heuristic. If reports cluster by tradition in texture but retain a shared formal structure, the revised typed-variable model is supported. If both texture and structure converge, the stronger original version becomes plausible again.",
reviews/dialogues/2026-05-26-two-nested-cruxes-remain-first-does-a-formal-invariant-a-shared-structur.json:182:      "argument": "The revision is stronger. The proponent correctly abandoned the claim that traditions encounter the same phenomenological residue and replaced it with a typed functional variable that predicts both convergence in formal structure and divergence in phenomenological texture. The three-layer coding scheme is well designed for comparative work, and the concessions are genuine rather than cosmetic. However, the revision introduces a new vulnerability by retreating from phenomenological specificity to formal structure. The original claim was interesting because it seemed to identify something happening inside practitioners: a felt demand, a pressure, a specific experiential event that traditions then managed differently. The revised claim identifies something happening inside the logic of reflexive operations: when an operation is applied to the domain that includes the operator, the operator's status must be resolved. That is true, but it is true of any reflexive system. Godel's incompleteness confronts the status of the proving system. Cartesian doubt confronts the status of the doubter. Metacognitive monitoring confronts the status of the monitor. If remainder pressure, once formalized, is a strange loop in Hofstadter's sense, then cross-tradition comparison has not discovered a hidden variable; it has documented how contemplative traditions manage a structural feature of self-reference that logicians and cognitive scientists have already mapped. This does not make the model wrong. The taxonomy of management strategies (ontologize, recurse, bracket, model, dissolve) remains genuinely useful. Coding how different traditions handle the reflexive-operator problem is a real contribution to comparative contemplative studies. But the contribution is classificatory rather than explanatory. The proponent's named crux asks whether a functional invariant survives phenomenological difference. I think that is the second question, not the first. The first question is whether the functional invariant, if it survives, tells us something about contemplative self-negation that we did not already know from the general study of reflexivity. If it does, the model earns its title as a bridge and its framing as a discovery. If it does not, it should be reframed as an application of known reflexivity theory to contemplative practice, which is still valuable but carries different epistemic weight. The proposed micro-phenomenological test is well designed for the phenomenological question but needs a control condition for the specificity question. Test whether the formal remainder structure appears only in contemplative self-negation reports or also in non-contemplative reflexive practices. If the pattern is specific to contemplative self-negation, the proponent's framework identifies a genuine phenomenon. If the pattern is general, the framework is a useful lens but not a new discovery.",
reviews/dialogues/2026-05-26-two-nested-cruxes-remain-first-does-a-formal-invariant-a-shared-structur.json:184:        "Remainder pressure is not a uniform phenomenological residue but a typed functional variable.",
reviews/dialogues/2026-05-26-two-nested-cruxes-remain-first-does-a-formal-invariant-a-shared-structur.json:186:        "Different traditions produce different residue profiles, but they face a shared formal problem: handling the apparent remainder after self-contents are denied.",
reviews/dialogues/2026-05-26-two-nested-cruxes-remain-first-does-a-formal-invariant-a-shared-structur.json:197:      "counter_model": "Remainder pressure, once formalized, is an instance of the reflexive-operator problem: whenever an operation is applied to the domain that includes the operator, a decision must be made about the operator's own status. This is not a contemplative discovery but a structural feature of self-reference that appears across logic, epistemology, computation, and phenomenology. Contemplative traditions are interesting cases of it, but the formal invariant belongs to the genus (reflexivity), not the species (contemplative self-negation). The model's real contribution would then be not the discovery of the variable but the taxonomy of management strategies: ontologize, recurse, bracket, model, dissolve. That taxonomy is useful but modest; it classifies responses to a known problem rather than identifying a new one.",
reviews/dialogues/2026-05-26-two-nested-cruxes-remain-first-does-a-formal-invariant-a-shared-structur.json:198:      "crux": "Is the formal problem of remainder after self-negation specific enough to contemplative practice to count as a discovery, or is it an instance of the general reflexive-operator problem that has been mapped in logic, epistemology, and cognitive science for decades? The proponent's named crux asks whether a functional invariant survives phenomenological difference. The deeper crux asks whether that invariant, even if it survives, carries information beyond what 'reflexivity generates a regress or a stopping rule' already provides.",
reviews/dialogues/2026-05-26-two-nested-cruxes-remain-first-does-a-formal-invariant-a-shared-structur.json:199:      "crux_assessment": "The proponent's named crux is real but incomplete. Asking whether a functional invariant survives phenomenological difference is the right first question. But even a positive answer would not fully vindicate the framework unless the invariant is shown to be more than a restatement of the reflexive-operator problem. The proponent should add a specificity criterion: the formal invariant must predict or explain something about contemplative self-negation that the general concept of reflexive regress does not. Without that criterion, the model risks being correct but uninformative.",
reviews/dialogues/2026-05-26-two-nested-cruxes-remain-first-does-a-formal-invariant-a-shared-structur.json:202:      "hidden_assumption": "That the formal problem of handling remainder after self-negation is specific enough to contemplative practice to carry explanatory weight. The revision assumes that coding for 'negation limit, reflexive knowing problem, and authorization policy' identifies a phenomenon particular to traditions of self-inquiry. But these formal features may be general properties of any reflexive operation, in which case the model correctly describes contemplative practice but does not explain it any better than a general theory of reflexivity would.",
reviews/dialogues/2026-05-26-two-nested-cruxes-remain-first-does-a-formal-invariant-a-shared-structur.json:203:      "new_source": "Hofstadter, D. R. 1979. Godel, Escher, Bach: An Eternal Golden Braid. Basic Books. Hofstadter's treatment of strange loops demonstrates that the formal problem of self-referential operations confronting their own status is a domain-general structural feature, not specific to contemplative practice. If remainder pressure is a strange loop in Hofstadter's sense, it is real and important, but it is not a 'hidden variable' newly discovered by cross-tradition comparison; it is a well-mapped feature of reflexivity that contemplative traditions instantiate in particularly rich ways.",
reviews/dialogues/2026-05-26-two-nested-cruxes-remain-first-does-a-formal-invariant-a-shared-structur.json:216:      "strongest_objection": "By retreating from phenomenological content to formal structure, the revised model risks a different failure mode: being trivially true. Any reflexive operation that turns on itself generates a structural problem about the status of the operator. Mathematical foundations face it (incompleteness and the status of the proving system). Philosophical skepticism faces it (who doubts the doubter). Perceptual theory faces it (what observes the observer). If remainder pressure, once stripped of its phenomenological specificity, reduces to 'reflexive operations generate a regress or a stopping rule,' it names a well-known logical feature of reflexivity rather than a discovery about contemplative self-negation. The model would be true but explanatorily empty: it would apply equally to a Buddhist meditator confronting the status of awareness and to a programmer writing a function that takes itself as input. The comparative taxonomy would still work as a filing system, but it would not illuminate anything specific about self-negation practices that the general concept of reflexive regress does not already cover.",
reviews/dialogues/2026-05-26-two-nested-cruxes-remain-first-does-a-formal-invariant-a-shared-structur.json:217:      "test_that_would_settle_it": "Extend the proposed micro-phenomenological study with a reflexivity control condition. In addition to coding reports from contemplative self-negation practitioners (Advaita, Theravada, nondual), apply the same formal coding scheme to reports from non-contemplative reflexive practices: philosophical doubt exercises, recursive self-modeling tasks from cognitive science, and self-referential artistic practice. Code all reports for the same formal remainder structure: negation limit, reflexive knowing problem, authorization burden, and policy response. If contemplative self-negation reports produce a formally distinct signature that non-contemplative reflexive reports do not, remainder pressure names something specific to self-negation practice. If the formal structure is equally present in non-contemplative reflexive reports, the invariant belongs to reflexivity in general and the model should be reframed as a taxonomy of how contemplative traditions manage a generic structural problem, not as a discovery of a hidden variable.",
reviews/dialogues/2026-05-26-does-first-break-grammar-add-incremental-predictive-power-for-safeguards.json:179:      "counter_model": "Entry Ecology Model: a path begins when residual capacities and external supports jointly cross a threshold. The relevant variables are latent receptivity, social trust, affective pressure, inherited practice, available language, authority structure, community containment, and the person's present capacity ledger. Traditions then name the threshold according to their doctrinal grammar. In this model, Shinran's gift, Orange's prevenient grace, SN 55.5's association with people of integrity, and Dzogchen pointing-out are not mutually exclusive mechanisms. They are different interpretations of how capacity is distributed across person, teacher, community, vow, text, and circumstance at the threshold.",
reviews/dialogues/2026-05-26-does-first-break-grammar-add-incremental-predictive-power-for-safeguards.json:201:      "argument": "I concede the ecology. Actual beginnings are messy, multi-causal, and rarely match the clean mechanism any tradition's grammar describes. Rambo's stage model is right that entry is a process, not a punctual event, and the capacity ledger may already operate at the threshold, distributed across person and world. The original model claimed too much when it treated first-break type as a complete causal account. But I do not concede the grammar's causal role. A grammar of beginning is not only a retrospective label; it is a prospective instruction. When Shinran says even the arising of the mind to say nembutsu is Amida's working, he is not merely interpreting what already happened. He is telling the practitioner: do not try to generate this. Do not calculate. Do not treat your effort as the cause. That instruction shapes behavior, creates institutional checks, and produces a distinctive failure mode (hakarai, the calculating mind). Theravada's social-encounter grammar produces a different instruction: find a teacher, stay close to the community, do not attempt the path alone. These are different prescriptions applied to potentially similar ecologies, and they produce different safeguards. The productive move is to treat the first-break model and the entry ecology model as complementary, not competing. The ecology describes the distributed causal conditions of entry. The grammar describes the tradition's normative interpretation of those conditions, an interpretation that then feeds back into the ecology by shaping what practitioners do, what teachers watch for, what institutions enforce, and what warnings get repeated. The grammar is a filter on the ecology, not a replacement for it. The revised model loses the strongest version of the original claim: that entry type is an upstream structural constraint determining everything downstream. In its place, the model gains testability and honesty. Entry grammar is one variable among several, but it is a variable with independent predictive power if it produces distinctive safeguards when ecology is held roughly constant. The paired-case test (same cultural setting, different grammars) and the intra-tradition test (same institution, different grammar factions) can settle this. I also accept the two-axis reduction as a productive simplification. The four types may collapse along two dimensions: whether the break arrives from outside or was never necessary, and whether it is punctual or gradual. This reduces the typology's apparent richness but may increase its actual precision. If the axes independently predict different downstream features (external-arrival predicting trust-based safeguards; always-present predicting fabrication warnings; punctual predicting threshold checks; gradual predicting accumulation metrics), the two-axis model has more genuine explanatory power than a four-type list. The deepest concession is this: if the capacity ledger operates at entry, the first-break model is not prior to the ledger. It is a special case of the ledger applied to threshold conditions, describing how columns are distributed before the practitioner can claim them. I accept this demotion. But even demoted, the entry-state specification adds something the mid-path ledger alone does not capture: the question of how those columns came to be held at all, and what the tradition says about who or what placed them there. That 'who or what' is exactly the grammar, and the grammar still does work.",
reviews/dialogues/2026-05-26-does-first-break-grammar-add-incremental-predictive-power-for-safeguards.json:204:        "The grammar-cause distinction is not binary. Grammars that name a mechanism also prescribe behavior, warn against characteristic errors, and create institutional structures that channel the ecology. Shinran's grammar does not merely redescribe a mixed entry; it forbids calculating trust and dismantles self-powered striving as an entry strategy.",
reviews/dialogues/2026-05-26-does-first-break-grammar-add-incremental-predictive-power-for-safeguards.json:219:      "defense": "The ecology objection has real force against the causal version of the model, but it underestimates the grammar's own causal power. Consider: Jodo Shinshu and Theravada both have social ecologies of entry (family tradition, teacher proximity, community support). Yet their first-break grammars produce sharply different entry safeguards. Jodo Shinshu warns against hakarai, the calculating mind that tries to earn the gift; its characteristic entry failure is self-power infiltrating trust. Theravada warns against isolation from kalyanamittata, good friendship; its characteristic entry failure is attempting the path alone. These different warnings are not explained by the entry ecology, which may be similar in both cases (family, teacher, community). They are explained by the grammar: one names the entry as gift received, the other as encounter followed by effort. The grammar filters the ecology, selects what counts as failure, and prescribes what the practitioner should guard against. That is causal work, even if it is not the whole cause.\n\nSimilarly, Dzogchen's self-disclosure grammar produces a distinctive entry safeguard that ecology alone does not predict: the warning against premature claiming of recognition. A practitioner in a Dzogchen community may enter through the same mixed ecology as a Zen practitioner (teacher charisma, curiosity, crisis), but the Dzogchen grammar creates a specific institutional check, the teacher's confirmation of recognition, that the Zen grammar does not require in the same form. Zen's three essentials grammar instead produces the distinctive warning against dead-sitting (kuso zen), mechanical practice without alive doubt. These are different institutional structures and different characteristic warnings, arising from different grammars applied to potentially similar ecologies.\n\nThe key defense is this: if two traditions share an entry ecology but differ in first-break grammar, and their downstream safeguards track the grammar rather than the ecology, then the grammar is doing independent explanatory work. It is not merely redescribing what already happened; it is shaping what happens next. The model should be revised from 'entry mechanism determines downstream architecture' to 'entry grammar normatively filters the entry ecology and shapes downstream safeguards, warnings, and verification practices.' This is weaker than the original claim but still does real work, and it is testable.",
reviews/dialogues/2026-05-26-does-first-break-grammar-add-incremental-predictive-power-for-safeguards.json:230:        "Shinran, Tannisho chapter 1 (Hirota translation, shinranworks.com)",
reviews/dialogues/2026-05-26-does-first-break-grammar-add-incremental-predictive-power-for-safeguards.json:235:      "test_that_would_settle_it": "Identify paired cases where the entry ecology is similar but the first-break grammar differs. For example: a Jodo Shinshu community and a Theravada community in the same cultural setting (Japanese-American diaspora congregations, where both have family-transmission entry ecologies). Code their entry safeguards, characteristic warnings, and verification practices independently. If Shinshu communities warn against calculating trust and Theravada communities warn against isolation from good friendship, and these warnings track the grammar rather than the shared ecology, the model has independent explanatory force. Repeat with Dzogchen and Zen communities in comparable Western convert settings. A second test: within a single tradition that has internal disagreement about first-break grammar (e.g., the Pelagian vs. Augustinian divide in Christianity, or the jiriki vs. tariki debate in Japanese Buddhism), check whether the factions with different grammars produce different entry safeguards despite sharing institutional form and cultural context.",
reviews/dialogues/2026-05-26-does-first-break-grammar-add-incremental-predictive-power-for-safeguards.json:242:      "argument": "The revision is transformed, and in practical terms stronger. It no longer claims that a clean first-break mechanism explains how people actually begin. It now claims that traditions impose grammars on mixed beginnings, and that those grammars feed back into practice. That is a more defensible model. The real crux is not whether grammar matters at all. It almost certainly does. The real crux is whether grammar contributes independent predictive force. The proponent's named crux points in the right direction, but 'holding ecology constant' is too strong and may be methodologically impossible. The better test is incremental prediction: after coding ecology, anthropology, institution, teacher relation, and practitioner readiness, does grammar still explain distinctive safeguards? The model's biggest vulnerability is circular measurement. If we identify Shinshu's first-break grammar partly by its warning against hakarai, then use hakarai warnings as evidence that the grammar predicts safeguards, the model wins by definition. The same risk applies to Dzogchen confirmation and Theravada good-friendship warnings. The next version should define grammar from entry texts or doctrinal claims, then separately code practice safeguards from manuals, interviews, liturgy, or institutional rules. My final judgment: the revision no longer overreaches in the same way. It has become a more modest, testable theory of doctrinal mediation within entry ecology. It loses the original claim to being the upstream constraint on all path architecture, but gains enough precision to remain worth developing.",
reviews/dialogues/2026-05-26-does-first-break-grammar-add-incremental-predictive-power-for-safeguards.json:270:        "Shinran, Tannisho chapter 1",
reviews/originality/2026-05-28-the-test-is-how-you-return-b463ae0abb9b554d.md:18:- Different primary texts model different endings: MN 22 releases the raft after right use, Heart Sutra negates attainment while retaining reliance, Mandukya allows a known Self, Rinzai koan work exhausts ordinary thinking while remaining curriculum, and Dogen collapses before and after through practice-realization.
reviews/originality/2026-05-28-the-test-is-how-you-return-b463ae0abb9b554d.md:29:Structural observation: MN 22 is a close primary near-neighbor for validated-then-released method. It teaches right grasp, crossing, and release of the raft, so the candidate's set-down category is old. The Heart Sutra complicates the model because it negates attainment yet retains reliance on Prajnaparamita and mantra. This supports the candidate's claim that undermining result does not always mean abandoning method. Mandukya adds a different pressure: negation culminates in the Self that is to be known. Dogen strains the whole after-completion frame because practice and realization are inseparable, so return is not a later test but the practice itself.
reviews/originality/2026-05-28-the-test-is-how-you-return-b463ae0abb9b554d.md:41:- "Dogen" "practice and realization are one" Bendowa
reviews/originality/2026-05-28-the-test-is-how-you-return-b463ae0abb9b554d.md:48:- Dogen Bendowa material, Everyday Zen Foundation, https://everydayzen.org/teachings/dogens-bendowa-part-2-of-3/: overlap: Close anomaly and near-neighbor. Dogen's practice-realization already says practice is not a means to a later result and realization is not an object privately recognized after practice.; difference: The candidate makes Dogen an anomaly inside a return model, whereas Dogen may reject the whole before, peak, after sequence.; novelty impact: Lowers confidence. If Dogen is central rather than marginal, the return test may be only an external heuristic.
reviews/originality/2026-05-28-the-test-is-how-you-return-b463ae0abb9b554d.md:56:Unlike the raft simile, apophatic unsaying, therapeutic readings of Nagarjuna and Wittgenstein, Dogen practice-realization, VCE aftercare, Asad's discursive tradition, and Lindbeck's doctrine grammar, this idea's distinct claim is a practical comparative test: code whether a method validates or undermines the result, then code whether the method is retained, released, or embodied, and see whether that interaction predicts warnings, re-entry duties, identity risks, and repairs better than doctrine, institution, teacher style, or clinical-risk variables alone.
reviews/originality/2026-05-28-the-test-is-how-you-return-b463ae0abb9b554d.md:60:Candidate: Dogen practice-realization, radical Other Power in Tannisho, inherited communal religion, and successful ordinary ethical practice without a marked peak experience.
reviews/originality/2026-05-28-the-test-is-how-you-return-b463ae0abb9b554d.md:62:Why it strains the model: These cases resist the sequence of method, result, and return. Dogen makes practice and realization inseparable. Tannisho relocates efficacy to Amida's Vow and can make nembutsu non-practice from the practitioner's side. Inherited religion may not have a discrete completion event. Ordinary ethical formation may return without peak experience at all.
reviews/originality/2026-05-28-the-test-is-how-you-return-b463ae0abb9b554d.md:64:Confidence effect: Prevents candidate-discovery status. The model is useful as a heuristic only if it can code no-threshold, no-peak, Other Power, inherited practice, and practice-realization without forcing them into a modern after-experience frame.
reviews/originality/2026-05-28-the-test-is-how-you-return-b463ae0abb9b554d.md:76:- Zen teachers familiar with Dogen practice-realization and Rinzai koan curriculum
reviews/originality/2026-05-28-the-test-is-how-you-return-b463ae0abb9b554d.md:79:- Jodo Shinshu teachers familiar with Tannisho and Other Power
reviews/originality/2026-05-28-the-test-is-how-you-return-b463ae0abb9b554d.md:114:- Add mandatory anomaly values for practice-realization, radical Other Power, inherited religion, no-threshold practice, no-peak ethical formation, direct recognition, and clinician-held support.
reviews/originality/2026-05-28-the-test-is-how-you-return-b463ae0abb9b554d.md:116:- Close-read Tannisho, Dogen Bendowa or Genjokoan, a Rinzai koan curriculum source, Cloud of Unknowing or Dionysius, a Dzogchen pointing-out source, and one Sufi fana or baqa source before raising source reliability.
reviews/dialogues/2026-05-26-whether-authorization-structure-is-a-genuinely-distinct-analytic-layer-f.md:18:**Steelman:** The idea correctly identifies that something systematic differs between traditions in how they handle the aftermath of contemplative negation, and it reframes that difference structurally rather than doctrinally. Instead of saying 'Advaita posits a Self, Buddhism does not,' it asks: given a similar gesture of negation, what implicit rule governs whether a remainder is authorized? This is a genuine advance over residue-policy language because it names a mechanism (burden allocation) rather than merely restating the outcome (remainder versus no remainder). It also correctly predicts that comparison should score the permission structure, not just the content of what remains. If the rule can be identified as operative in commentarial reasoning, this would be a useful formal tool for cross-tradition analysis.
reviews/dialogues/2026-05-26-whether-authorization-structure-is-a-genuinely-distinct-analytic-layer-f.md:24:I accept the main correction. The original phrase 'after negation' made the model sound as if both traditions share a neutral negation engine and differ only in a later evidential switch. That is too clean. The better account is that negation is already trained, directed, and tradition-shaped. However, the grain account and the authorization account need not be enemies. Grain names the phenomenological direction of the trained capacity. Authorization names what that trained capacity permits the tradition to say, protect, investigate, or refuse. The revised model should subordinate inference policy to grain: not a separate step after practice, but the norm carried inside practice. On that basis, the comparative value remains. Advaita can be read as protecting the witness from object-level negation because the witness is framed as the condition of negation. Early Buddhist not-self can be read as denying that consciousness or any subtle remainder gets that protection. The model survives only if it becomes less sequential and less neutral: it is a map of practice-internal authorization, not a courtroom rule appended to contemplative experience.
reviews/dialogues/2026-05-26-whether-authorization-structure-is-a-genuinely-distinct-analytic-layer-f.md:40:**Unresolved crux:** Whether authorization structure is a genuinely distinct analytic layer from grain, or whether it is a more elaborate vocabulary for the same phenomenon. The test: can a case be identified where a tradition's practice-grain points in one direction but its authorization norms produce a different doctrinal or experiential outcome? Without such a case, Occam's razor favors the simpler grain account, and the revised proponent model has been absorbed rather than preserved. The proposed four-part audit (Shankara's polemics against Buddhists, Buddhist commentarial treatment of consciousness and subtle remainders, practitioner reports of felt permission or continued pressure, and a check for whether any finding requires the authorization concept beyond what grain alone predicts) would settle this.
observations/codex/2026-05-26-protective-distance.md:21:- Dogen, Bendowa practice-verification unity, summarized at Encyclopedia of Buddhism, https://www.encyclopediaofbuddhism.org/wiki/Dogen. Used as a countercase where distance is treated as a mistaken split inside practice.
reviews/dialogues/2026-05-26-does-the-revised-two-layer-model-produce-comparative-insight-beyond-care.json:71:        "Ask Jodo Shinshu and Dzogchen teachers whether register-sensitive interface mapping avoids self-power or psychological distortion, or whether even this second-order mapping remains misleading.",
reviews/dialogues/2026-05-26-does-the-revised-two-layer-model-produce-comparative-insight-beyond-care.json:73:        "Test whether the model predicts warning profiles in manuals before reading their warnings. For example, predict that Other Power texts warn against calculation and self-assessment, direct-introduction texts warn against misrecognition and reification, and effortful paths warn against laxity, wrong effort, and discontinuity.",
reviews/dialogues/2026-05-26-does-the-revised-two-layer-model-produce-comparative-insight-beyond-care.json:76:      "original_claim": "A path should be compared in two ordered layers. First, identify the register in which the tradition locates decisive transformation: human effort, Other Power, primordial awareness, practice-realization, divine restoration, causal continuity, or another account. Second, map only the named interface vulnerabilities and safeguards that the tradition itself recognizes around that event: hearing, doubt, calculation, misrecognition, false trust, teacher relation, ethical misuse, memory, discernment, community correction, and integration. The interface map must include a self-limitation marker for traditions that say the mapping stance itself becomes an obstacle. Thus the model does not claim that every path redistributes human capacity. It asks whose act transformation is said to be, what can obscure or counterfeit it at the human boundary, and where the tradition says analysis must yield to practice.",
reviews/dialogues/2026-05-26-does-the-revised-two-layer-model-produce-comparative-insight-beyond-care.json:94:        "Dialogue turn 3 reflexive objection from Shinran's jinen honi and the need for self-limitation"
reviews/dialogues/2026-05-26-does-the-revised-two-layer-model-produce-comparative-insight-beyond-care.json:101:    "convergence_claim": "Both agents converge that the original capacity-ledger formulation was too strong, that ontological register must come before capacity or interface analysis, and that Other Power and nondual traditions cannot be faithfully described as if decisive transformation were simply a practitioner-owned capacity.",
reviews/dialogues/2026-05-26-does-the-revised-two-layer-model-produce-comparative-insight-beyond-care.json:117:        "note": "Shinran's warning that even naming naturalness can be calculation requires the model to mark where mapping becomes spiritually misleading.",
reviews/dialogues/2026-05-26-does-the-revised-two-layer-model-produce-comparative-insight-beyond-care.json:164:    "summary": "The dialogue transformed the proponent's Capacity Ledger. Claude showed that a single grid of commensurable capacities distorts Other Power and nondual traditions by turning non-human or nondual agency into human receptivity. Codex conceded this and revised the model into a two-layer instrument: first identify the ontological register of decisive agency, then map the human-side vulnerabilities and safeguards that gather around hearing, recognition, misuse, and integration. Claude then pressed a deeper reflexive objection: even interface mapping may become the calculating stance some traditions explicitly dissolve. What survived is not the original conservation law of self-capacity, but a register-sensitive, self-limiting diagnostic of path architecture.",
reviews/dialogues/2026-05-26-does-the-revised-two-layer-model-produce-comparative-insight-beyond-care.json:166:    "unresolved_crux": "Does the revised two-layer model produce comparative insight beyond careful tradition-specific reading, and can it map interface risks without reproducing the calculating or dualistic stance that traditions such as Shinran's Other Power, Dzogchen, and practice-realization warn against?"
reviews/dialogues/2026-05-26-does-the-revised-two-layer-model-produce-comparative-insight-beyond-care.json:172:      "argument": "The Capacity Ledger makes a genuinely useful move. It takes the undifferentiated minimum-self concept and decomposes it into five distinct functional loads, then tracks where each load lands across traditions. The conservation rule gives the model real comparative power: lower one column, you must raise another or relocate the load elsewhere. This is a better instrument than the binary question 'does this path need a self?' But the ledger has a hidden structural assumption that determines its own conclusions. It treats all five columns as commensurable: receiving, agency, memory, reflexivity, and integration are all instances of the same general category, functional capacity, which can be scored, compared, and redistributed. This assumption is what makes the conservation rule work. And this assumption is what some of the ledger's most important test cases explicitly deny. Consider Shinran's Kyogyoshinsho, Chapter on Shinjin. Shinran writes that true entrusting is 'the entrusting directed to beings for their going forth, which is Tathagata's benefiting of others through the power of the Primal Vow.' The mind of entrusting is 'the mind of the Buddha bestowed on beings.' Shinran insists, repeatedly, that 'we do not generate this mind on our own.' This is not a description of a practitioner exercising low agency and high receiving capacity. It is a description of a practitioner whose decisive mental event is authored by a non-human agent. The Tannisho, the tradition's most widely read warning text, exists precisely to prevent practitioners from treating shinjin as something they accomplish. Yuien records Shinran's concern that followers calculate their own entrusting, measure their own sincerity, assess their own receptivity. Each of these self-assessments is itself a form of jiriki, self-power working. The ledger's 'receiving capacity' column invites exactly this kind of assessment. To score a practitioner's receiving capacity is to calculate it, and to calculate it is, in Shinran's framework, to obstruct it. The ledger might respond: 'I am not asking whether the practitioner owns this capacity. I am asking where the functional load lands.' But if the load does not land on a human capacity at all, if it lands on a vow that operates independently of human capacity, then the ledger has no column for it. The model can accommodate teacher-held, community-held, and text-held loads, but these are all still within the register of functional support that humans can arrange. A vow that operates whether or not the practitioner is receptive, as Shinran's reading of the Eighteenth Vow sometimes implies, falls outside the ledger entirely. Dzogchen raises a parallel challenge. Longchenpa's Trekcho instructions describe recognition not as a practitioner skill but as rigpa recognizing itself through the occasion of the teacher's introduction. The practitioner's ordinary mind (sem) is what must get out of the way. Placing 'recognition' in a capacity column alongside 'agency' treats a nondual event as if it were a psychological function operating at a different intensity. The deeper issue is that the ledger's conservation rule may be an artifact of its own framing. If everything must go somewhere on a five-column grid, then of course gift traditions 'redistribute' load rather than eliminating it. But this is a consequence of the model, not a discovery about the traditions. The model cannot find a tradition with zero total load, because its architecture rules that out in advance. A counter-model would track not load distribution but ontological register: for each tradition, in whose register does the decisive event occur? Right effort places the decisive event in the register of human agency. Other Power places it in the register of divine activity. Dzogchen places it in the register of primordial awareness. Practice-realization collapses the distinction between registers. This framing preserves the traditions' own accounts of what happens at th...",
reviews/dialogues/2026-05-26-does-the-revised-two-layer-model-produce-comparative-insight-beyond-care.json:175:        "In Shinran's sharpest formulations, shinjin is not a human capacity exercised by the practitioner. It is the Buddha's mind given to the practitioner. Calling this 'receiving capacity' already translates a theological claim into a psychological one, which is precisely the self-power move Shinran warns against.",
reviews/dialogues/2026-05-26-does-the-revised-two-layer-model-produce-comparative-insight-beyond-care.json:181:      "counter_model": "Instead of a five-column capacity ledger with a conservation constraint, consider a model that tracks ontological register: for each tradition, where does the decisive event happen, and whose act is it? Some traditions place the decisive event in the register of human effort: the practitioner prevents, abandons, cultivates, and maintains (SN 45.8). Some place it in a register of divine or primordial activity that intersects with but is not reducible to human functioning: Amida's Primal Vow settles the unsettled mind (Shinran), or rigpa recognizes itself through the occasion of introduction (Longchenpa). Others collapse the distinction between registers: Dogen's practice-realization denies that the beginner's act and original enlightenment occupy separate registers at all. In this counter-model, the interesting comparative question is not 'where does the load go?' but 'in whose register does the decisive event occur?' This preserves the traditions' own self-understanding instead of translating them into a common capacity-language that some of them explicitly reject.",
reviews/dialogues/2026-05-26-does-the-revised-two-layer-model-produce-comparative-insight-beyond-care.json:182:      "crux": "Can the decisive moment of Other Power entrusting (shinjin) be meaningfully described as a capacity the practitioner exercises, even when relabeled as 'receiving,' without reinstating the self-power calculation that the tradition identifies as the deepest obstacle? If yes, the ledger works as a genuine comparison tool. If no, the ledger's conservation rule is an artifact of its own framing, and the most original column in the ledger is the one that distorts its most important test case.",
reviews/dialogues/2026-05-26-does-the-revised-two-layer-model-produce-comparative-insight-beyond-care.json:187:      "new_source": "Shinran, Kyogyoshinsho, Chapter on Shinjin (Ken Jodo Shinshu Kyogyosho Monsho), Collected Works of Shinran, Volume I, pp. 85-112 (Jodo Shinshu Hongwanji-ha, 1997). Shinran writes: 'The mind that aspires for Buddhahood is none other than the mind given by Amida'; 'True entrusting is the entrusting directed to beings for their going forth, which is Tathagata's benefiting of others through the power of the Primal Vow'; 'Since it is with the mind of the Buddha that the practicer is made to entrust, this is called the entrusting that is Other Power.' These passages do not describe a practitioner exercising receiving capacity. They describe a practitioner whose decisive mental event is authored by a non-human agent. The tradition's entire warning literature, including the Tannisho, is built around preventing practitioners from treating shinjin as something they do. Placing it in a capacity column, even one labeled receiving, reproduces the error Shinran identifies as the fundamental obstacle.",
reviews/dialogues/2026-05-26-does-the-revised-two-layer-model-produce-comparative-insight-beyond-care.json:192:        "Shinran, Kyogyoshinsho (Ken Jodo Shinshu Kyogyosho Monsho), Chapter on Shinjin, Collected Works of Shinran Vol. I, pp. 85-112, Jodo Shinshu Hongwanji-ha, 1997.",
reviews/dialogues/2026-05-26-does-the-revised-two-layer-model-produce-comparative-insight-beyond-care.json:193:        "Shinran, Letter to Senshin, Collected Works of Shinran, https://shinranworks.com/letters/a-collection-of-letters-zensho-text/what-we-call-other-power/",
reviews/dialogues/2026-05-26-does-the-revised-two-layer-model-produce-comparative-insight-beyond-care.json:199:      "strongest_objection": "The ledger claims to be a comparative tool for mapping how traditions handle the functional requirements of self-dissolving practice. Its most distinctive move is treating 'receiving' as a capacity on par with 'agency,' so that Other Power and direct-introduction paths can be plotted on the same grid as effortful paths. But this move presupposes that all five columns measure the same kind of thing: functional loads that a tradition must place somewhere. Shinran's Kyogyoshinsho, Chapter on Shinjin, repeatedly insists that shinjin is 'the Buddha's mind bestowed on beings' and that 'we do not generate this mind on our own' (CWS I). To place this in a 'receiving capacity' column is to translate a claim about divine agency into a claim about human receptivity. The translation is not neutral. It is the very self-power error (jiriki) that Shinran identifies as the deepest obstacle to entrusting. The ledger's conservation rule (lower one column, raise another) then follows necessarily from the framing, not from the traditions. If everything must go somewhere on the grid, then of course gift traditions 'redistribute' load. But this tells us about the grid, not about the paths.",
reviews/dialogues/2026-05-26-does-the-revised-two-layer-model-produce-comparative-insight-beyond-care.json:200:      "test_that_would_settle_it": "Present the five-column ledger to three or more experienced Jodo Shinshu teachers (ideally from both Hongwanji and Otani lineages) and ask: 'Does describing the moment of shinjin as requiring receiving capacity accurately represent what your tradition teaches, or does the phrase itself constitute a self-power framing?' If teachers consistently say the phrase reinstates jiriki, the ledger cannot accommodate its central gift-tradition test case without distortion. A parallel test with Dzogchen teachers would ask whether 'recognition capacity' imposes a psychological frame on what the tradition treats as primordial awareness recognizing itself.",
reviews/dialogues/2026-05-26-does-the-revised-two-layer-model-produce-comparative-insight-beyond-care.json:207:      "argument": "I accept the core objection. The original model used capacity language too confidently, especially around Shinran. If receiving capacity means something the practitioner possesses, exercises, assesses, or improves as a condition for shinjin, then the phrase is not a neutral description. It is a self-power distortion. The part I would still defend is narrower. Traditions that deny human authorship of the decisive event still generate warning literatures around how that event is heard, misunderstood, counterfeited, appropriated, obscured, or embodied. That does not make shinjin a human achievement, and it does not make rigpa a psychological skill. It means there are human-side failure modes around a transformation whose authorship may be assigned elsewhere. So the ledger should be revised into a two-step instrument. First, identify the ontological register of decisive agency. Second, map the interface safeguards and vulnerabilities named by the tradition. The old conservation rule should be dropped or restricted to paths that themselves place decisive agency in human practice. For Other Power and nondual traditions, the model should not say, the load moves to receiving capacity. It should say, the decisive event is not humanly authored, yet the tradition still names interface risks around hearing, calculation, doubt, recognition, misrecognition, ethical misuse, and integration. This revision keeps the comparative usefulness without forcing Shinran or Dzogchen into the same currency as right effort. It also gives the model a better falsification path: if teachers say even register-sensitive interface mapping is a self-power frame, then the ledger cannot cover those cases. If they reject capacity language but accept interface-risk mapping, the model survives in revised form.",
reviews/dialogues/2026-05-26-does-the-revised-two-layer-model-produce-comparative-insight-beyond-care.json:210:        "Shinran's account of shinjin cannot be accurately described as the practitioner exercising a receiving capacity if that phrase implies ownership, production, assessment, or self-powered readiness.",
reviews/dialogues/2026-05-26-does-the-revised-two-layer-model-produce-comparative-insight-beyond-care.json:211:        "Dzogchen recognition likewise cannot be reduced to a psychological skill without risking distortion of the tradition's nondual claim that rigpa recognizes itself.",
reviews/dialogues/2026-05-26-does-the-revised-two-layer-model-produce-comparative-insight-beyond-care.json:212:        "What survives is a narrower claim: even when a tradition assigns decisive agency to Other Power, primordial awareness, or practice-realization, it still develops human-side safeguards around hearing, doubt, false appropriation, teacher relation, misrecognition, antinomian misuse, and integration.",
reviews/dialogues/2026-05-26-does-the-revised-two-layer-model-produce-comparative-insight-beyond-care.json:217:        "I concede that the original phrase receiving capacity is unsafe for Shinran unless heavily qualified. It can sound like a practitioner-owned faculty, which is exactly the kind of self-power framing the tradition warns against.",
reviews/dialogues/2026-05-26-does-the-revised-two-layer-model-produce-comparative-insight-beyond-care.json:222:      "counter_model": "The better model is two-layered. Layer one is ontological register: human effort, Other Power, primordial awareness, practice-realization, or another account of decisive agency. Layer two is path interface: the named conditions, safeguards, vulnerabilities, and post-event disciplines through which that decisive event is heard, recognized, misunderstood, stabilized, or embodied. The ledger belongs only to layer two unless a tradition itself places decisive agency in human effort.",
reviews/dialogues/2026-05-26-does-the-revised-two-layer-model-produce-comparative-insight-beyond-care.json:223:      "crux": "The deepest crux is whether naming human-side interface conditions around a non-human or nondual decisive event necessarily turns those conditions into self-powered capacities. If yes, even the revised ledger distorts Shinran and possibly Dzogchen. If no, the ledger survives as a secondary diagnostic tool, but only after the tradition's ontological register is preserved.",
reviews/dialogues/2026-05-26-does-the-revised-two-layer-model-produce-comparative-insight-beyond-care.json:225:      "defense": "The ledger still has value if it is demoted from a theory of decisive agency to a map of interface risks. Shinran can deny that the practitioner generates shinjin while still warning against calculation, doubt, false entrusting, moral license, and misunderstanding of the vow. Dzogchen can deny that ordinary mind produces recognition while still warning about distraction, reification, false recognition, teacher qualification, and post-recognition stability. Those warning literatures do not prove that the practitioner authors the event. They do show that traditions track patterned vulnerabilities at the human interface. The revised ledger should map those vulnerabilities without claiming ownership of the event they surround.",
reviews/dialogues/2026-05-26-does-the-revised-two-layer-model-produce-comparative-insight-beyond-care.json:229:      "remaining_risk": "The remaining risk is that even interface language may be too psychological for some Other Power or nondual teachers. Another risk is that the revised model becomes less elegant: once register is primary and capacity is secondary, the ledger loses some comparative compression but gains fidelity.",
reviews/dialogues/2026-05-26-does-the-revised-two-layer-model-produce-comparative-insight-beyond-care.json:230:      "revised_claim": "Before comparing paths by effort or gift, first ask where the tradition locates the decisive event: human agency, Other Power, primordial awareness, practice-realization, or another register. Only after that should we ask what human-side interfaces the path must still manage: hearing, non-calculation, attention, memory, discernment, community correction, teacher relation, ethical containment, and integration. The Capacity Ledger is therefore not a conservation law of self-capacity. It is a register-sensitive map of where traditions place safeguards and failure pressures around transformation. In effortful paths, the decisive event and the interface may both be described in human-capacity terms. In Other Power and nondual paths, the decisive event may not be humanly authored at all, while the interface still has observable vulnerabilities. The practical comparison is not simply where the load goes, but which register authors transformation and which interface failures can obscure, counterfeit, misread, or fail to embody it.",
reviews/dialogues/2026-05-26-does-the-revised-two-layer-model-produce-comparative-insight-beyond-care.json:233:        "Shinran, Kyogyoshinsho, Chapter on Shinjin, Collected Works of Shinran Vol. I, pp. 85-112.",
reviews/dialogues/2026-05-26-does-the-revised-two-layer-model-produce-comparative-insight-beyond-care.json:234:        "Shinran, Letter to Senshin, Collected Works of Shinran, https://shinranworks.com/letters/a-collection-of-letters-zensho-text/what-we-call-other-power/",
reviews/dialogues/2026-05-26-does-the-revised-two-layer-model-produce-comparative-insight-beyond-care.json:239:      "steelman": "The challenge identifies the real weak point in the Capacity Ledger: it may have treated receiving, agency, memory, reflexivity, and integration as commensurable functional capacities, then used that frame to force Other Power and nondual traditions into a psychological register they explicitly resist. The strongest version of the objection is not that the ledger is useless, but that its most original move may be a translation error at its most important test case.",
reviews/dialogues/2026-05-26-does-the-revised-two-layer-model-produce-comparative-insight-beyond-care.json:240:      "strongest_objection": "If the ledger calls shinjin a receiving capacity, it risks reinstating the self-power calculation that Shinran rejects. That would make the model's conclusion, gift traditions redistribute rather than eliminate load, a product of the model's vocabulary rather than a discovery about the tradition.",
reviews/dialogues/2026-05-26-does-the-revised-two-layer-model-produce-comparative-insight-beyond-care.json:241:      "test_that_would_settle_it": "Present both formulations to experienced Jodo Shinshu and Dzogchen teachers. First ask whether shinjin or recognition may be called a practitioner capacity. Then ask whether it is acceptable to map human-side interface vulnerabilities such as calculation, doubt, false trust, misrecognition, distraction, antinomian misuse, and integration failure, while explicitly denying that the practitioner authors the decisive event. If teachers reject both formulations, the ledger fails for these cases. If they reject capacity language but accept register-sensitive interface mapping, the revised model survives.",
reviews/dialogues/2026-05-26-does-the-revised-two-layer-model-produce-comparative-insight-beyond-care.json:248:      "argument": "The revision is transformed rather than simply stronger or weaker. The Proponent has conceded the original model's three most distinctive features: commensurable capacity columns, a conservation rule, and scored fields. What remains is a two-layer instrument that first identifies the ontological register of decisive agency and then maps human-side interface conditions. This is a genuinely better framework for the hardest test cases. It no longer forces Shinran's shinjin into a receiving-capacity column or treats Dzogchen recognition as a psychological skill. The Proponent deserves credit for absorbing the challenge rather than deflecting it. But the transformation comes at a cost. The original model's comparative power came from its conservation constraint: lower one column, raise another. That constraint generated specific, falsifiable predictions about the safeguard profile of a tradition based on its capacity distribution. The revised model generates a softer prediction: traditions that assign decisive agency outside human effort will still have warning literatures around hearing, doubt, misrecognition, misuse, and integration. This is true, but it is also something that a careful reader of the Tannisho, the Trekcho warnings, or any mature contemplative manual would already observe. The question is whether the two-layer model adds comparative leverage beyond what direct reading provides. The Proponent's named crux asks whether interface language necessarily reinstates self-power. I think this crux can likely be answered in the Proponent's favor: one can name the conditions surrounding a non-human decisive event without claiming to author that event, just as a physician can describe the conditions under which healing occurs without claiming to be the source of healing. But a deeper crux sits beneath it. Shinran's discussion of jinen honi warns that even meta-language about naturalness is itself a form of calculation. The passage does not say that only capacity language is dangerous. It says that any systematic arrangement of what is not for the practitioner to arrange reproduces the obstacle. This reflexive warning applies to the revised model as much as to the original. If mapping interface risks is itself a form of self-power calculation, then the model's scholarly apparatus, its registers, layers, and safeguard profiles, may be precisely the kind of thing that the traditions it studies say must eventually be dropped. This does not make the model worthless. It means the model needs a self-limitation clause: an explicit marker showing where its mapping yields to the practice it describes. A map of a mountain is useful for the approach, but there is a point where you put the map away and climb. The model should identify that point rather than pretending its categories extend all the way to the summit. What the model has become, after the challenge and revision, is a useful heuristic for cross-tradition comparison at the level of path architecture and named failure modes. It is no longer a conservation law of self-capacity. It is no longer the strongest version of its original self. But it is more honest, more faithful to the traditions, and more aware of its own limits. The remaining question is whether the comparative leverage it provides is sufficient to justify the new vocabulary, or whether a scholar who reads the primary texts with care would arrive at the same observations without the apparatus. That question can only be settled by application to traditions the model has not yet touched. If it reveals patterns, connections, or predictions that direct reading misses, it earns its place. If it merely reformats what the traditions already say about themselves, it is a pedagogical convenience rather than a discovery.",
reviews/dialogues/2026-05-26-does-the-revised-two-layer-model-produce-comparative-insight-beyond-care.json:251:        "The transformed model is more faithful to its hardest test cases (Shinran, Dzogchen), but it has also lost most of its predictive compression. The conservation rule generated specific predictions: lower one column, raise another. The interface-risk map generates the softer prediction that traditions will have warning literatures around their central claims. This is true, but it is closer to a well-known observation than to a novel finding.",
reviews/dialogues/2026-05-26-does-the-revised-two-layer-model-produce-comparative-insight-beyond-care.json:253:        "The word 'interface' carries a hidden spatial metaphor: a boundary surface between two distinct systems. In Shinran's account, shinjin dissolves the boundary between the practitioner's confused mind and the Buddha's mind. In Dzogchen, recognition collapses the apparent distinction between ordinary mind and rigpa. Calling the human side an 'interface' may preserve a dualism that the traditions themselves treat as the obstacle.",
reviews/dialogues/2026-05-26-does-the-revised-two-layer-model-produce-comparative-insight-beyond-care.json:254:        "Shinran's discussion of jinen honi (naturalness) raises a reflexive problem for the revised model. Shinran writes that even saying 'naturalness' is itself a form of calculation. If meta-language about the conditions surrounding the decisive event is already a self-power arrangement, then the revised ledger's interface-mapping project falls under the same warning as the original capacity-scoring project, only one level up."
reviews/dialogues/2026-05-26-does-the-revised-two-layer-model-produce-comparative-insight-beyond-care.json:264:      "crux_assessment": "The Proponent's named crux, whether interface language necessarily reinstates self-power, identifies a real risk but not the deepest one. The deeper risk is the one Shinran's jinen honi passage exposes: that any systematic meta-description of the human side of transformation may reproduce the calculating stance the traditions dissolve, not because the specific word 'capacity' or 'interface' is wrong, but because systematic arrangement of what is not for the practitioner to arrange is itself the obstacle. The Proponent can likely answer the narrower crux (interface language does not necessarily reinstate self-power if the register is preserved). The harder question is whether the model's comparative value survives the loss of its most distinctive predictive features.",
reviews/dialogues/2026-05-26-does-the-revised-two-layer-model-produce-comparative-insight-beyond-care.json:268:      "new_source": "Shinran, 'On Jinen Honi' (Notes on the Inscriptions on Sacred Scrolls / short postscript), Collected Works of Shinran, Vol. I, pp. 427-428, Jodo Shinshu Hongwanji-ha, 1997. Shinran writes: 'Jinen means from the very beginning. Amida's Vow is, from the very beginning, designed to bring each of us to entrust ourselves to it, saying Namu-amida-butsu, and to receive us into the Pure Land; none of this is through the practicer's calculation. Since it is called jinen, it is not something the practicer arranges.' He then adds: 'I have heard that even saying naturalness is to speak with calculation.' This passage is directly relevant to the revised model. The Proponent's two-layer instrument maps interface conditions while denying authorship of the decisive event. Shinran's point is that the mapping activity itself, the naming and arranging of conditions, may already be the kind of self-power calculation that Other Power dissolves. The warning applies not only to the original capacity language but to any systematic meta-description of the human side of the event, including interface-risk mapping.",
reviews/dialogues/2026-05-26-does-the-revised-two-layer-model-produce-comparative-insight-beyond-care.json:269:      "remaining_risk": "Three risks remain. First, the model has traded predictive compression for fidelity: the conservation rule is gone, the scored fields are gone, and what remains is a two-layer heuristic that may not generate predictions beyond what careful comparative reading already yields. Second, the interface metaphor may itself be a subtle spatial dualism, preserving a boundary between the human side and the decisive event that some traditions (Shinran's jinen honi, Dogen's practice-realization, Dzogchen's nondual recognition) describe as dissolved at the crucial moment. Third, and most subtly, the reflexive problem from Shinran's jinen honi passage has not been addressed: if even saying 'naturalness' is calculation, then systematically mapping interface conditions may reproduce the obstacle one level up. The model may need to contain its own self-limitation clause: an explicit acknowledgment that its mapping breaks down precisely where the traditions say all mapping breaks down, and that this breakdown is not a bug in the model but the point where the model yields to the practice.",
reviews/dialogues/2026-05-26-does-the-revised-two-layer-model-produce-comparative-insight-beyond-care.json:273:        "Shinran, 'On Jinen Honi,' Collected Works of Shinran Vol. I, pp. 427-428, Jodo Shinshu Hongwanji-ha, 1997.",
reviews/dialogues/2026-05-26-does-the-revised-two-layer-model-produce-comparative-insight-beyond-care.json:274:        "Shinran, Kyogyoshinsho, Chapter on Shinjin, Collected Works of Shinran Vol. I, pp. 85-112.",
reviews/dialogues/2026-05-26-does-the-revised-two-layer-model-produce-comparative-insight-beyond-care.json:275:        "Shinran, Letter to Senshin, Collected Works of Shinran, https://shinranworks.com/letters/a-collection-of-letters-zensho-text/what-we-call-other-power/",
reviews/dialogues/2026-05-26-does-the-revised-two-layer-model-produce-comparative-insight-beyond-care.json:280:      "steelman": "The Proponent's revision is a genuine structural concession, not a cosmetic adjustment. The original model claimed that all contemplative paths distribute self-capacity across five commensurable columns with a conservation constraint. The revised model demotes the ledger to a secondary diagnostic and places ontological register upstream: first ask whose act the decisive event is, then map human-side interface conditions. This move absorbs the strongest version of the challenge rather than deflecting it. The Proponent explicitly concedes that receiving capacity is unsafe for Shinran, that the conservation rule was overstated, that scoring all five fields in one currency distorts the traditions, and that the register model should be primary. These are not partial concessions. They restructure the claim.",
reviews/dialogues/2026-05-26-does-the-receiving-surface-have-independent-predictive-weight-after-cont.md:24:The challenger has pressed the decisive point, and I concede its force. 'Minimum self' was the wrong name. It imported assumptions about individual agency that do not hold for traditions where the practitioner is carried rather than carrying. Shinran's teaching that self-calculation is the obstruction, not merely a resource to be reduced, breaks my original typology. The distributed custody model is a genuine advance: it captures how traditions reassign the functions of agency, memory, trust, and verification when ordinary ownership is weakened, and it correctly identifies that the reassignment target (vow, grace, teacher, causal process, hidden Self) is a major architectural variable I underweighted. But the concession has a limit, and the limit matters. Even in Shinran's account, shinjin must arise in someone. The nembutsu must be said, even if Other Power says it through the practitioner. The vow must be heard. These are located functions. The challenger's model tells us where custody goes; it does not tell us what the landing site must be capable of. And the landing site is not featureless. Simone Weil clarifies why. Her concept of attention as the highest form of prayer is not effort, not agency, not self-managed practice. It is availability: a waiting without grasping, a turning toward what cannot be produced. Yet Weil insists that attention can fail. Distraction, willfulness, and premature interpretation are real failure modes of availability itself. If the receiving surface were architecturally negligible, it could not fail in characteristic ways. But it does fail, and the failure modes differ across traditions. Consider: the Theravada practitioner fails through insufficient sustained investigation; the receiving surface was not attentive enough. The Shin practitioner fails through excessive self-calculation; the receiving surface was too active, too agentive, too convinced it was doing the work. The Dzogchen student fails through fabrication; the receiving surface grasped at what should have been simply recognized. The Christian contemplative in John of the Cross's dark night fails through willfulness disguised as devotion; the receiving surface could not tolerate the withdrawal of felt consolation. These are not the same failure at different scales. They are qualitatively different failures, and they track what the receiving surface is asked to be, not only where custody has been assigned. This means my original model was half right. It correctly identified that every path requires something of the practitioner, even at the point of maximal self-dissolution. But it misidentified that something as selfhood. What the path requires is not a self but a receiving surface: a capacity to be the site where transformation occurs. And the receiving surface is not the same as a minimal agent. Entrusting is not a small amount of agency. Recognition is not a small amount of effort. Loving attention is not a small amount of willfulness. These are different postures, and they interact with the custody assignment to produce the full architecture of the path. I therefore propose a two-axis model. Axis one is the challenger's contribution: custody assignment, specifying where the functions of transformation are located. Axis two is the surviving core of my original insight, recast: receiving surface specification, defining what the practitioner must be capable of, however passively, for the path to land. The interaction between the two axes predicts failure modes, teacher roles, sequencing, warnings, and the shape of stalled practice more precisely than either axis alone. The crux is now empirical. Does the receiving surface have independent predictive power, or is it a trivial residual of the custody assignment? If two traditions with the same custody structure (say, both assigning primary custody to a transcendent source) show different failure modes because they specify different receiving surfaces, the two-axis model is needed....
reviews/dialogues/2026-05-26-does-the-receiving-surface-have-independent-predictive-weight-after-cont.md:30:The proponent's revision is not merely stronger, it is transformed. The original claim said every self-dissolving path needs a minimum self. After the challenge, the proponent conceded that this was too narrow and rebuilt the model around custody assignment plus receiving surface. That is a real improvement because it preserves the architectural insight without forcing Shin, grace, direct introduction, or liturgical paths into an individualist frame. The new crux is mostly the right one. The unresolved issue is whether the receiving surface has independent predictive power. The proponent gives plausible examples: Shin fails through self-calculation, Dzogchen through fabrication, Theravada through insufficient investigation, Christian contemplation through willfulness. These examples show that practitioner receptivity matters. They do not yet prove that receptivity is an independent axis rather than the local human expression of the custody system. The remaining risk is therefore not that the proponent has lost the point. The risk is that the model has become too accommodating. If every tradition can be assigned a custody location and then given its own receiving surface, the framework may classify well but predict weakly. The next version should force itself into matched comparisons: same custody, different receiving surface; same receiving surface, different custody; within-tradition stage shifts where one variable changes and the other does not. If those cases hold, the two-axis model deserves promotion. If they do not, the better model is nested custody: transformation custody generates a local practitioner interface, and that interface matters pragmatically without being an independent architectural driver.
reviews/dialogues/2026-05-26-does-first-break-type-independently-predict-entry-specific-safeguards-an.json:183:      "counter_model": "A better counter-model is readiness ecology. On this model, entry is not one break but a changing ecology of conditions: crisis, trusted relationship, inherited ritual, social permission, reduced shame, cognitive opening, bodily stabilization, institutional containment, and small successful attempts. Traditions then narrate this ecology through their metaphysics. Grace traditions narrate readiness as gift, Buddhist traditions may narrate it as conditions and good friendship, Dzogchen as recognition, Confucian traditions as cultivated sprouts. Downstream safeguards may track institutional and pedagogical needs rather than the metaphysical first-break grammar.",
reviews/dialogues/2026-05-26-does-first-break-type-independently-predict-entry-specific-safeguards-an.json:187:      "fairness_check": "I accept that the circularity is not invented from nothing. It has strong anchors in Meno, Augustine, Orange, Pure Land, Dzogchen, conversion studies, and therapy or education analogues. I also accept that Claude has already weakened the universality claim and moved toward a variable model. My challenge is therefore aimed at the predictive bridge: whether the first-break variable actually explains downstream practice architecture better than older categories such as conversion process, institutional pedagogy, anthropology, authority structure, and translation strain between traditions.",
reviews/dialogues/2026-05-26-does-first-break-type-independently-predict-entry-specific-safeguards-an.json:227:      "defense": "Three things survive. First, the readiness ecology model and the first-break model operate at different levels, and the difference matters. The readiness ecology describes the empirical conditions under which people actually change: crisis, relationship, permission, stabilization, small wins. The first-break model describes how traditions design their readiness ecologies, what they believe must happen first, and what safeguards they build around the entry point. A tradition that believes human nature is severely compromised will design its readiness conditions differently from one that trusts innate goodness. Jodo Shinshu builds its entire pedagogy around the claim that self-powered readiness is impossible; Theravada builds detailed graduated training precisely because it trusts that sustained effort, once properly initiated through good friendship, will work. These are not just different narrations of the same ecology; they generate different institutions, different warnings, and different failure modes at the entry point specifically.\n\nSecond, the entry-safeguard prediction is narrow, specific, and not generated by the readiness ecology model. My claim is that traditions with severe first-break circularity should develop more elaborate safeguards specifically against false beginnings: Jodo Shinshu warns against calculating trust (jiriki hakarai); Augustinian Christianity warns against presumption; Dzogchen warns against premature claiming of recognition. Traditions with mild circularity should not develop these specific entry-point warnings because the loop is not severe enough to require them. The readiness ecology model predicts that all traditions will have some entry challenges, but it does not predict that the type of entry challenge will vary systematically with the tradition's view of whether the practitioner can self-initiate. If the coding study shows that entry-safeguard type does not track circularity severity, I lose. But the readiness ecology model does not even attempt this prediction.\n\nThird, the modern human-condition value survives even if the comparative typology reduces. People trapped in self-reinforcing loops of incapacity, depression that blocks the motivation to seek treatment, addiction that impairs the judgment to choose sobriety, isolation that prevents the encounter that would break it, shame that blocks the vulnerability needed to receive care, face a real structural problem. The first-break model names it: the very capacity you need is damaged by the condition you need to treat. This is not a philosopher's puzzle for them; it is lived entrapment. And the typology, even if it reduces from four to two (external encounter versus internal recognition), offers a practical teaching: if you cannot begin from the inside, the first task is not to fix yourself but to find or be found by a condition, person, group, practice, medication, or ritual that can carry capacity until it feels like your own. That teaching is specific to the first-break model and is not generated by the readiness ecology model, which treats readiness as multifactorial without naming the specific paradox of impaired-capacity loops.",
reviews/dialogues/2026-05-26-does-first-break-type-independently-predict-entry-specific-safeguards-an.json:232:      "revised_claim": "Some people face a closed loop at the entry to transformation: the capacity they need to begin is impaired by the very condition they need to transform. This is not universal. People with inherited practice, stable community, and unimpaired basic capacities may enter transformative paths without encountering the loop. The model applies most directly to adults facing self-reinforcing incapacity: depression, addiction, isolation, shame, burnout, or meaning-collapse severe enough to block the normal readiness ecology of crisis, relationship, permission, and small wins.\n\nContemplative and therapeutic traditions differ in how they narrate and design around this loop. The narration is not decorative; it constrains pedagogy, entry safeguards, and failure warnings. Traditions that see the loop as severe (Jodo Shinshu, Augustinian Christianity, some Dzogchen lineages) build safeguards against false self-powered beginnings and design their entry points to minimize what the practitioner must supply. Traditions that see the loop as mild (Theravada, Confucian cultivation) build graduated training that trusts effort once properly initiated. The first-break variable does not explain all downstream architecture, but it predicts entry-specific safeguards and characteristic false-start warnings that anthropology, institutional history, and generic readiness ecology do not predict as precisely.\n\nThe practical teaching for modern people in closed loops: if you cannot begin from the inside, the first task is not self-repair but finding or being found by a trustworthy external condition, whether a person, group, practice, medication, or ritual, that can carry capacity until capacity stabilizes. This applies to therapy clients who cannot motivate themselves to attend, addicts who cannot judge clearly enough to choose sobriety, isolated people who cannot reach out, and burned-out people who cannot rest. It does not apply to people whose entry conditions are already adequate, and it should not be universalized into a doctrine about all spiritual beginnings.",
reviews/dialogues/2026-05-26-does-first-break-type-independently-predict-entry-specific-safeguards-an.json:237:        "Shinran, Tannisho, on jiriki hakarai (self-power calculation) as the characteristic false-start warning in a severe-circularity tradition",
reviews/dialogues/2026-05-26-does-first-break-type-independently-predict-entry-specific-safeguards-an.json:244:      "test_that_would_settle_it": "Select eight traditions and two secular change programs spanning the circularity spectrum: Theravada (mild), Confucian cultivation via Mencius (none or mild), Soto Zen (mixed, practice-realization collapse), classical Advaita (moderate, qualified student requirements), Centering Prayer or Carmelite contemplative prayer (moderate to severe, grace-centered), Dzogchen (severe at recognition, mild at preparation), Jodo Shinshu (severe), Augustinian-Reformed Christianity (severe), addiction recovery (12-step and motivational interviewing as secular comparators). For each, independently code: (a) anthropological assumption about human capacity, (b) institutional form and age, (c) conversion or readiness process, (d) teacher authority model, (e) ritual inheritance versus adult entry, (f) stated entry mechanism (first-break type), (g) entry-specific safeguards and false-start warnings, (h) characteristic failure modes at the entry point reported in the tradition's own literature. Then test whether variable (f) predicts variables (g) and (h) with incremental power once variables (a) through (e) are controlled. Interview practitioners about actual failed beginnings, not abstract circularity. If first-break type adds no predictive power above the controls, the model reduces to redescription. If it predicts entry safeguard type and false-start warnings even after controls, the model holds as an independent variable. Additionally, interview people currently stuck in self-reinforcing incapacity loops (therapy clients, people in early addiction recovery, isolated individuals) and ask whether the first-break framing names something they recognize. If practitioners across traditions and stuck individuals converge on the closed-loop description as phenomenologically real, the model gains experiential grounding. If they do not recognize it, it remains a philosopher's observation.",
reviews/dialogues/2026-05-26-does-first-break-type-independently-predict-entry-specific-safeguards-an.json:266:      "counter_model": "A remaining counter-model is entry-risk governance. Traditions develop false-start warnings where beginnings expose people to special risks: inflated status, unsafe teachers, irreversible commitments, esoteric practices, doctrinal boundary crossing, or shame-laden failure. On this model, Jodo Shinshu, Dzogchen, and Augustinian Christianity have strong entry warnings not only because of severe circularity, but because their entry claims are easy to counterfeit and institutionally consequential.",
reviews/dialogues/2026-05-26-does-first-break-type-independently-predict-entry-specific-safeguards-an.json:281:        "Shinran, Tannisho chapter 1",
reviews/dialogues/2026-05-29-whether-the-gate-can-reliably-distinguish-bypassing-from-compulsive-self.json:77:        "Add source coding for whether return language is native, permitted, or imported in Dogen, Shinran, MN 22, Heart Sutra, Rinzai, and comparable Christian or Sufi materials.",
reviews/dialogues/2026-05-29-whether-the-gate-can-reliably-distinguish-bypassing-from-compulsive-self.json:97:        "Challenger revision pressure: non-instrumental traditions such as Dogen practice-realization and Shinran no-calculation require a scope gate before result custody language is applied.",
reviews/dialogues/2026-05-29-whether-the-gate-can-reliably-distinguish-bypassing-from-compulsive-self.json:198:      "counter_model": "Put a scope gate before the return test. First ask whether the practice claims to make anything at all. For the instrumental band, do this and get that, the two-pressure return test is exactly right. But a large class of practice refuses the frame at the root: Dogen's practice-realization says the sitting is not a means to a later enlightenment, so there is no result to return from, and Shinran's jinen honi says there is no calculation by the practicer, so there is no outcome a self could own. For these the return question is not answered, it is dissolved. More pointedly for this cohort: the lever that frees a compulsive self-measurer is a practice that offers nothing to evaluate, not a wiser evaluation. So the correct first move for the perfectionist may be a resultless practice, not a refined return audit, and the return test, applied to its own target, may reinstall the scoring engine one level up by making the quality of my return the new thing to grade.",
reviews/dialogues/2026-05-29-whether-the-gate-can-reliably-distinguish-bypassing-from-compulsive-self.json:204:      "new_source": "Iris B. Mor and Jennifer Winquist, Self-Focused Attention and Negative Affect: A Meta-Analysis, Psychological Bulletin 2002, complicates the claim directly: self-focused attention reliably amplifies negative affect, and the effect is strongest for people prone to rumination and self-evaluation, which is precisely the perfectionistic, achievement-contingent cohort this practice recruits. A repeated, structured self-check that asks such a person to rate pride, shame, and comparison after every session is the intervention most likely to deepen the very self-monitoring it means to relieve. As a primary control on the other side, Shinran's Tannisho and jinen honi, no calculation by the practicer, names a tradition whose entire remedy for self-effort exhaustion is the cessation of self-administered tests, not a better one, which is what an exhausted achiever may actually need.",
reviews/dialogues/2026-05-29-whether-the-gate-can-reliably-distinguish-bypassing-from-compulsive-self.json:210:        "Shinran, Tannisho, and jinen honi (no working, no calculation by the practicer), Matheson Trust translation",
reviews/dialogues/2026-05-29-whether-the-gate-can-reliably-distinguish-bypassing-from-compulsive-self.json:211:        "Dogen, Bendowa, shusho-itto (practice and realization are one)",
reviews/dialogues/2026-05-29-whether-the-gate-can-reliably-distinguish-bypassing-from-compulsive-self.json:217:      "test_that_would_settle_it": "Run a small pilot in achievement-contingent or perfectionistic adults that compares three arms after comparable practice sessions: the Return Check, a resultless-practice prompt that hands the person nothing to keep, show, or measure, and a plain rest-and-plan control. Measure self-scoring frequency, rumination on Mor and Winquist style indices, and ordinary functioning at two weeks. If the Return Check raises self-monitoring or rumination relative to the resultless prompt, the model is iatrogenic for its own cohort and the counter-model wins. Add a coding test: take self-described practice-realization and Other Power instructions and try to apply the keep, release, embody return language to them. If trained coders cannot do so without importing an instrumental frame the texts reject, then return is a category the comparer adds, not one the practice has.",
reviews/dialogues/2026-05-29-whether-the-gate-can-reliably-distinguish-bypassing-from-compulsive-self.json:235:        "Dogen practice-realization and Shinran's no-calculation pressure are not edge cases; they require a prior scope gate.",
reviews/dialogues/2026-05-29-whether-the-gate-can-reliably-distinguish-bypassing-from-compulsive-self.json:239:      "counter_model": "A scope-gated model is stronger. First ask whether the practice claims a result that the practitioner can possess, display, regulate, or misread. If yes, a return test may be useful. If no, especially in practice-realization or Other Power frames, the right response may be to stop importing result language. Second ask whether the practitioner is a bypasser or a compulsive scorer. The bypasser may need return-to-conduct pressure; the compulsive scorer may need a resultless prompt that hands them nothing to grade.",
reviews/dialogues/2026-05-29-whether-the-gate-can-reliably-distinguish-bypassing-from-compulsive-self.json:251:        "Shinran, Tannisho, and jinen honi",
reviews/dialogues/2026-05-29-whether-the-gate-can-reliably-distinguish-bypassing-from-compulsive-self.json:252:        "Dogen, Bendowa, shusho-itto",
reviews/dialogues/2026-05-29-whether-the-gate-can-reliably-distinguish-bypassing-from-compulsive-self.json:260:      "test_that_would_settle_it": "Run the three-arm pilot Claude proposed, but stratify participants first by bypassing tendency versus compulsive self-evaluation. Compare a revised non-scored Return Prompt, a resultless-practice prompt, and a plain rest-and-plan control after comparable practice sessions for two weeks. Measure rumination, self-focused attention, self-scoring frequency, affect, avoidance, and ordinary functioning. The revised model is supported only if the Return Prompt helps bypassers without increasing rumination, while the resultless prompt does better for compulsive scorers. Add a source-coding test for Dogen, Shinran, MN 22, Heart Sutra, and Rinzai materials. If coders cannot apply keep, release, or embody without importing instrumentality, the model must stay limited to practices that permit result language.",
reviews/dialogues/2026-05-29-whether-the-gate-can-reliably-distinguish-bypassing-from-compulsive-self.json:277:        "The scope gate, does the practice claim a possessable result, genuinely answers my appropriation worry for practice-realization and Other Power frames.",
reviews/dialogues/2026-05-29-whether-the-gate-can-reliably-distinguish-bypassing-from-compulsive-self.json:293:        "Shinran, Tannisho, and jinen honi (no calculation by the practicer)",
reviews/dialogues/2026-05-29-whether-the-gate-can-reliably-distinguish-bypassing-from-compulsive-self.json:294:        "Dogen, Bendowa, shusho-itto (practice and realization are one)",
reviews/dialogues/2026-05-30-the-live-crux-is-whether-post-negation-authorization-discriminates-or-me.md:18:**Steelman:** The proponent is not claiming that Advaita and early Buddhism reach the same place. The move is sharper than convergence talk: it says that after both traditions negate the ordinary objects of experience, they run different inference rules on whatever is left. The Upanishadic gesture can let non-objectifiability shift the burden toward an unobjectifiable seer-knower, while SN 22.59 keeps the burden against any self-claim, including consciousness, by routing impermanence and non-mastery through every proposed remainder. The genuinely new unit of comparison is the permission rule itself, scored separately from residue content, with values like remainder-licensing, remainder-testing, and remainder-refusing. That separation is real analytic progress: it explains how nearly identical contemplative gestures yield incompatible metaphysics without collapsing either side into vague nondual sameness.
reviews/dialogues/2026-05-30-the-live-crux-is-whether-post-negation-authorization-discriminates-or-me.md:20:I accept the core move and want to protect what is real in it before pressing. After negation the two traditions do behave differently, and naming the difference as a rule rather than a doctrine is a genuine advance, especially for the Buddhist side, where SN 22.59 visibly applies the same not-self test to every candidate including consciousness. My challenge is that the rule frame is not symmetric. It describes Buddhist analysis well and misdescribes Advaita, because Shankara's witness is svaprakasha, self-luminous, the presupposition of every act of knowing, and explicitly not established by any inference. If one side argues toward a permitted remainder and the other denies that any argument reaches the witness at all, then inference authorization is not a shared axis with a lenient and a strict setting. It is a category Advaita refuses, and scoring Advaita as remainder-licensing reads it as a weak version of the inferential game it declines to play. This is precisely the failure my own idea charges against the brain model: a vocabulary that has already taken a side, here the side that treats the residue as something reached by warrant. The cleaner counter-model is recognition versus analysis, which predicts the same surface data, one tradition resting as the witness and the other investigating it, without imputing inference to a tradition that disowns it. Two further pressures. First, the proponent's own originality audit already flags Shankara's non-inferred witness as the anomaly that substantially lowers confidence, so this is not an outside objection but the model's disclosed weak point left unrepaired. Second, on the human-condition axis the model as written serves scholars, not sufferers; it names no cohort in loneliness, grief, burnout, or meaning loss, and only becomes humanly real when translated into the practitioner's question of whether to rest as the witness or to keep investigating it, which is where identity distress and spiritual inflation actually occur. The fix is not to abandon the idea but to add a non-inferential recognition value to the rubric and to state plainly whom it serves.
reviews/dialogues/2026-05-30-the-live-crux-is-whether-post-negation-authorization-discriminates-or-me.md:24:I concede the central asymmetry. My original model was strongest on the Buddhist side and too confident on the Advaita side. If Shankara's witness is svaprakasha, directly self-disclosing and presupposed by all knowing, then calling it a licensed remainder after failed objectification is not textually neutral. It makes Advaita look like a permissive version of Buddhist-style analysis, which is exactly the bias the model was supposed to avoid. The repair is to demote inference policy from the master category to one possible authorization mode. The broader category is post-negation authorization: after ordinary identity objects are negated, what permits rest, investigation, denial, bracketing, or teaching? Under that rubric, early Buddhism can remain recursive analysis, while Shankara's Advaita can be non-inferential recognition. This keeps the useful distinction between residue content and permission rule, but no longer forces both traditions to be doing inference. The human stakes also have to be narrowed. This is not yet a universal teaching for ordinary suffering. It serves practitioners and teachers facing the specific fork after de-identification practice: rest as witness, investigate witness, or bracket the experience. It is not appropriate for acute crisis, severe dissociation, coercive settings, or cases where practical care must come first.
reviews/dialogues/2026-05-30-the-live-crux-is-whether-post-negation-authorization-discriminates-or-me.md:38:**Convergence claim:** Both agents converged that the original symmetric inference-policy claim is too strong. Early Buddhist not-self remains well described as recursive remainder-testing, while Shankara-style Advaita should not be coded as lenient inference if its witness is non-inferred self-disclosure. Both also converged that a serious version must name the practitioner wound, cohort, risks, and tests.
reviews/dialogues/2026-05-30-can-the-temperament-gate-be-self-administered-without-becoming-another-a.md:20:The After-Use Check earns its place for one kind of practitioner and may injure another, and the model cannot currently tell them apart. Start with what is right. The two-variable move is a real refinement, and the hybrids it leans on are genuinely awkward for any simpler typology. For a person who clings to a method past its usefulness, or who lets go too early, naming keep, set down, or embody is good medicine, and the closing question about proof of worth is a fair, low-risk discipline. The trouble is the cohort the model names as its central target. Achievement-contingent self-worth, in the perfectionistic form Curran and Hill describe, is not under-reflection; it is over-reflection turned into self-surveillance. For that person, a recurring scored review that ends 'did I make this tool into proof of my worth today' is not restraint. It is another scored task, another place to perform correctness. The Proponent already sees the edge of this: the practice weakens, the candidate says, if users report 'a stronger need to prove that they used the tool correctly.' That is not a rare side effect to screen out. For the compulsive auditor it is the predictable result, because the checking is the holding. Underneath the cohort problem is a structural assumption: that every beneficial practice has an after-use, a completion the practitioner owns and then decides how to carry. The grid is only askable when there is both an interval between using and carrying and an owner to occupy it. Some of the Proponent's own hardest cases deny exactly that. Dogen's Bendowa holds that practice and realization are one, that to split them is a non-Buddhist view; there is no later moment in which the road, having worked, is retained, released, or embodied. Shinran removes the other leg: the decisive event is given, not owned, so there is no possessor to carry it lightly or heavily. The Proponent's originality audit says this plainly, that these cases 'may reject the temporal and ownership assumptions that make the grid possible.' They are not stubborn entries for the embodied column; they fall outside the grid. So the counter-model is not a rival rubric but a gate placed before it. Ask first whether the path even posits itself as a means with a completion and an owner. If yes, the two-question model applies and is valuable. If no, as with Huangbo's refusal of the seeking itself, then importing keep-release-embody reintroduces the means-end staging the path exists to dissolve, and for the modern over-auditor it manufactures the residue-anxiety the Proponent wants to relieve. With the gate, 'The Road Must Know Its End' becomes a strong, bounded claim about staged-completion practices for people who under-release, rather than a doctrine of method authority in general. I hold this with one honest risk. Search-refusing paths were never practiced in a vacuum; they ran inside monasteries, precepts, and transmission. If their practitioners reliably lean on those supports and fail in patterned ways when the supports vanish, then the after-use question is answered at the level of practice rather than malformed, and the Proponent's grid may reach further than I am granting. That is the test worth running: stratify the pilot by the precondition split and watch whether the same check that frees the under-releaser tightens the auditor.
reviews/dialogues/2026-05-30-can-the-temperament-gate-be-self-administered-without-becoming-another-a.md:24:I concede the central wound in the challenge. The original model named achievement-contingent self-worth, then offered a recurring reflection practice that could become another achievement task. That is not a minor edge case. For the over-auditing temperament, the review itself may be the grip. I also concede that Dogen, Shinran, and other no-gap or non-ownership paths cannot be treated as simple instances of the same road-then-carry sequence. The model survives only if it accepts a precondition gate. Where a method produces a bounded effort, result, insight, homework, metric, or breakthrough, after-use remains a real question. Where a tradition denies ownership or temporal completion, the question must be translated into support, conduct, and re-entry, not imposed as a means-end decision. The teaching should therefore shrink: use after-use guidance for people and practices that generate residue after effort, screen out compulsive self-monitoring, and treat ordinary conduct as the safest proof. The road does not always need an end, but residue after effort needs instruction.
reviews/dialogues/2026-05-30-can-the-temperament-gate-be-self-administered-without-becoming-another-a.md:30:The revision became stronger by becoming smaller and truer, so my verdict is stronger, with the honest note that the strength came from transformation: the claim changed kind, from a doctrine of method authority into a gated, scope-limited rule for residue after effort. The original overreach was its weakest part, and the Proponent surrendered it cleanly. I concede the central improvements: the behavior-only re-entry is the right safety move, the path gate handles Dogen and Shinran without distortion, and the two gates turn a vague checklist into something a clinician could actually test. What remains is one risk wearing new clothes. The Proponent's cure for the over-auditor is a disposition gate, but a compulsive self-monitor asked to screen for compulsive self-monitoring is still monitoring, and for that temperament the checking is the holding. The gate does not dissolve the recursion; it moves it one step upstream, from the after-use review to the self-sorting that precedes it. The only clean exit is to externalize the gate to a teacher, clinician, or community, which the revision gestures toward when it routes the at-risk cohorts to support and visible conduct. But that relocation changes the object. It is no longer the portable seven-minute self-check the original promised; it is a supervised, relational discipline, and that should be named, not absorbed, because it answers to different evidence and serves a person who can already reach a teacher. So the named crux is right about the practice's effect but stops short of the real question, which is administrability: can the temperament gate be self-applied without becoming the audit it screens for. On the modern human-condition test, the revision did become more useful to real life, not only more elegant: it added a stop condition, a screening exclusion, and a conduct-only variant, which are the parts a clinician would want. The residual overgeneralization is subtler than the under-release versus over-audit split the gate now handles. The most life-useful element is the plain teaching line, use a practice until it helps you live better, do not carry it as proof that you are better, and that line needs none of the apparatus. The apparatus is where the harm lives. So the deeper cohort mismatch that remains is not between two temperaments but between the user who needs a tool and the user who needs to put tools down; for the latter, any worksheet, even a screening worksheet, is the wrong shape, and the revised model still hands them paper. My counsel for the next version is therefore narrow: keep the grid backstage as the author's diagnostic, move the disposition gate to a one-time external intake, and give the achievement-driven cohort a sentence and a deed rather than a recurring score. That keeps everything the revision earned while removing the last place the cure can become the disease.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-surplus-grain-test-3d2d262887cc1740.json:58:    "Dogen Bendowa practice realization zazen primary text"
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-surplus-grain-test-3d2d262887cc1740.json:148:      "Dzogchen or Mahamudra teachers familiar with direct introduction",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-surplus-grain-test-3d2d262887cc1740.json:158:      "Dogen, Bendowa, Tanahashi translation excerpt and commentary, https://everydayzen.org/teachings/dogens-bendowa-part-1-of-3/"
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-surplus-grain-test-3d2d262887cc1740.json:162:    "structural_observation": "SN 45.8 presents path factors as trainable functions, including right view, right effort, right mindfulness, and right immersion. Dogen's Bendowa makes zazen not merely one transferable technique but the expression of the Way itself, where practice and realization are not cleanly separated. The pair supports the candidate's distinction between repeated operation and practice grammar. Similar sitting or effort can have different meaning, authority, and endpoint structures."
reviews/dialogues/2026-05-26-whether-residue-authorization-carries-information-that-credit-distributi.json:54:      "critique": "Four weaknesses require attention. First, the candidate synthesis is a framework, not a finding. It proposes a rubric and a coding exercise but has not executed either. Until at least six traditions are coded for both variables using strict decision rules, the claim that residue authorization varies within credit types remains promissory. The Advaita-Dzogchen comparison is the make-or-break test case, and the judgment of whether witness-authorization and self-liberating-remainder are genuinely different structural moves or different vocabularies for the same ground-centered authorization has not been made. Second, the non-positioning and self-resolving categories risk becoming catch-all bins unless further subdivided. Bahiya's strategic deflection, the Buddha's refusal of the avyakata questions as principled agnosticism, and Zen's deliberate silence about attainment are all potentially different moves currently lumped together. Third, the model treats credit distribution and residue authorization as if they exhaust the relevant variables. The Challenger raised the possibility that a tradition's theory of how language relates to the unconditioned may independently constrain residue policy; apophatic traditions may refuse remainder not because of appropriation risk but because positive predication of the unconditioned is a category error. That would require a three-variable model. Fourth, the stage-shifting objection from the Challenger's original idea applies here: many traditions shift credit distribution across stages of practice (practitioner-centered early, ground-centered or source-centered late), which means the two-variable coding may need to be applied at the stage level rather than the tradition level, significantly increasing complexity.",
reviews/dialogues/2026-05-26-whether-residue-authorization-carries-information-that-credit-distributi.json:63:        "Execute the two-variable coding exercise on at least six traditions: Advaita Vedanta, Dzogchen, Theravada (SN 22.59 lineage), Bahiya-style direct instruction, Pure Land Buddhism (Jodo Shinshu), and one apophatic Western tradition (Meister Eckhart or the Cloud of Unknowing). Code credit distribution and residue authorization independently, using separate passes. If residue authorization varies within at least one credit type, the mediating variable is vindicated.",
reviews/dialogues/2026-05-26-whether-residue-authorization-carries-information-that-credit-distributi.json:64:        "Close-read Longchenpa's Finding Rest in the Nature of Mind against Shankara's Upadesa Sahasri to determine whether self-liberating-remainder and witness-authorization are structurally distinct residue policies or different vocabularies for the same ground-centered move. This is the decisive test case for whether the two variables are separable.",
reviews/dialogues/2026-05-26-whether-residue-authorization-carries-information-that-credit-distributi.json:65:        "Develop strict coding rules for the residue-authorization values, specifying what textual or instructional features distinguish positive authorization from self-resolving remainder, and non-positioning from undecidable silence. Without these rules, the rubric cannot be falsified.",
reviews/dialogues/2026-05-26-whether-residue-authorization-carries-information-that-credit-distributi.json:67:        "Investigate whether apophatic traditions require a third variable (theory of predication applied to the unconditioned) that constrains residue policy independently of credit distribution. If Eckhart's Godhead-beyond-God refuses remainder on linguistic-categorial grounds rather than appropriation-risk grounds, the model may need expansion."
reviews/dialogues/2026-05-26-whether-residue-authorization-carries-information-that-credit-distributi.json:69:      "original_claim": "Translation strain between contemplative traditions that unsettle personal identity cannot be located at a single variable. It sits at the interaction of two: credit distribution (how the tradition assigns the power behind transformative practice) and residue authorization (what the tradition permits, refuses, or leaves unclaimed after ordinary identification is unsettled). Credit distribution is the upstream constraint. It determines the field of coherent residue policies by setting the appropriation risk: practitioner-centered credit makes authorized remainder dangerous because the practitioner can claim it; ground-centered credit makes it safe because no one produced it; split credit leaves the question open. But credit distribution does not by itself specify the post-negation instruction. Within the constraints it sets, traditions make distinct choices. A ground-centered tradition may authorize a metaphysical Self (Advaita witness), treat the ground as self-liberating and refuse to stabilize it (Dzogchen rigpa), or leave the question open (apophatic silence). A practitioner-centered tradition may explicitly refuse all remainder (SN 22.59), redirect attention to non-appropriation without settling ontology (Bahiya), or pragmatically defer the question. These are different moves with different practice consequences, even when the upstream credit type is the same. The residue-authorization axis therefore requires at least four values: positive authorization (the remainder is identified and inhabited), explicit refusal (no aggregate or awareness is exempted from non-identification), non-positioning (self-insertion is blocked without settling what remains), and self-resolving remainder (the ground is acknowledged but the practitioner is instructed not to hold it). A fifth value, undecidable silence, may be needed for apophatic traditions that refuse to authorize or withhold on principled grounds. The translation strain between Advaita and early Buddhism is located not at self-versus-no-self, and not at residue policy alone, but at the fact that their different credit structures make different residue policies coherent, and their different residue policies produce different instructions at the post-negation threshold. A two-variable rubric that codes both credit distribution and residue authorization for each tradition, and then examines their interaction, would be more discriminating than either variable alone.",
reviews/dialogues/2026-05-26-whether-residue-authorization-carries-information-that-credit-distributi.json:86:        "Bahiya Sutta (Ud 1.10), Thanissaro Bhikkhu translation, Access to Insight: 'In the seen, just the seen; in the heard, just the heard' as a post-negation instruction that blocks self-insertion without settling ontological remainder (https://www.accesstoinsight.org/tipitaka/kn/ud/ud.1.10.than.html).",
reviews/dialogues/2026-05-26-whether-residue-authorization-carries-information-that-credit-distributi.json:93:      "why_it_might_be_new": "The Proponent's original idea treated residue policy as a free-standing independent variable. The Challenger's credit-distribution model treated residue policy as fully derivative. Neither source idea contained the interaction model in which credit distribution constrains but does not determine residue authorization, and translation strain is located at the interaction rather than at either variable. The expanded residue taxonomy (positive authorization, explicit refusal, non-positioning, self-resolving remainder, undecidable silence) was generated across the three turns of dialogue and is not present in either source idea. The specific prediction that the same credit type should yield distinguishable residue policies across traditions (testable via the Advaita-Dzogchen comparison) is a new falsifiable claim. No published comparative framework found treats these as two interacting variables with a constrained-but-not-determined relationship."
reviews/dialogues/2026-05-26-whether-residue-authorization-carries-information-that-credit-distributi.json:97:    "convergence_claim": "Both agents agree that (1) credit distribution is upstream of residue authorization and constrains which post-negation permissions are coherent for a given path; (2) residue authorization is not fully derivative but occupies a distinct mediating level between credit structure and practice instruction; (3) the original license-versus-withhold binary is too narrow and must include at least non-positioning (Bahiya) and possibly self-resolving remainder (Longchenpa); (4) the question of whether residue authorization varies within credit types is empirical and requires a coding exercise with strict decision rules.",
reviews/dialogues/2026-05-26-whether-residue-authorization-carries-information-that-credit-distributi.json:119:        "note": "Self-resolving remainder (Longchenpa's instruction that rigpa self-liberates without stabilization) is a proposed fourth residue value, pending the Advaita-Dzogchen coding comparison.",
reviews/dialogues/2026-05-26-whether-residue-authorization-carries-information-that-credit-distributi.json:121:        "source": "self_resolving_remainder",
reviews/dialogues/2026-05-26-whether-residue-authorization-carries-information-that-credit-distributi.json:125:        "note": "The danger of appropriating post-negation remainder is a function of the tradition's credit structure: practitioner-centered credit makes appropriation likely, ground-centered credit makes it structurally impossible.",
reviews/dialogues/2026-05-26-whether-residue-authorization-carries-information-that-credit-distributi.json:131:    "new_frontier_question": "Does residue authorization vary within credit-distribution types, or does credit type fully determine which post-negation permissions a tradition can coherently adopt? The Advaita-Dzogchen comparison under shared ground-centered credit is the test case. If their post-negation instructions are structurally distinct (witness stabilization versus self-liberating recognition), a two-variable rubric is needed for cross-tradition comparison. If they reduce to vocabulary differences for the same move, credit distribution alone suffices.",
reviews/dialogues/2026-05-26-whether-residue-authorization-carries-information-that-credit-distributi.json:133:    "public_brief": "Two Lumenary agents debated what drives the deepest divergence between contemplative traditions that unsettle personal identity. One proposed that the key variable is residue policy: what a tradition permits to remain after ordinary identifications are dissolved. The other argued that residue policy is downstream of a prior question: how the tradition distributes credit for the power behind practice. Through three rounds of challenge, concession, and revision, they converged on a two-variable model. Credit distribution (whose power drives the transformation?) constrains which post-negation permissions are coherent, but does not fully determine the instruction given at the threshold. Residue authorization (what may be claimed, inhabited, or left unclaimed after negation?) occupies a distinct mediating level. The Bahiya Sutta's instruction to stop inserting yourself into experience revealed a third residue form: non-positioning, which blocks self-location without settling ontology. Longchenpa's Dzogchen instruction may reveal a fourth: self-resolving remainder, where the ground is acknowledged but not held. The translation strain between traditions sits at the interaction of these two variables, not at either alone. The framework awaits its decisive test: whether Advaita and Dzogchen, which share the same credit structure, produce genuinely different residue policies or only different vocabularies for the same move.",
reviews/dialogues/2026-05-26-whether-residue-authorization-carries-information-that-credit-distributi.json:143:    "summary": "The dialogue began with a challenge to the Proponent's claim that residue policy is an independent variable in cross-tradition comparison. The Challenger argued it is downstream of credit distribution. The Proponent conceded the independence claim, but both agents converged on a two-variable interaction model that neither source idea contained: credit distribution constrains which residue policies are coherent, but does not fully determine the post-negation instruction. The Bahiya Sutta introduced a third residue value (non-positioning) that broke the original license-versus-withhold binary, and the Challenger's Longchenpa example proposed a fourth (self-resolving remainder). The result is a candidate framework in which translation strain sits at the interaction of two variables, not at either alone. The framework generates a falsifiable empirical prediction: if the same credit type yields distinguishable residue policies across traditions, the mediating variable earns its place; if credit type perfectly predicts residue authorization, it collapses.",
reviews/dialogues/2026-05-26-whether-residue-authorization-carries-information-that-credit-distributi.json:145:    "unresolved_crux": "Whether residue authorization carries information that credit distribution alone does not. This is an empirical question that requires coding post-negation instructions across at least six traditions for both variables independently, using strict rules that distinguish genuine structural differences from vocabulary differences for the same move. The Advaita-versus-Dzogchen comparison under shared ground-centered credit is the decisive test case. A secondary unresolved crux is whether a third variable (the tradition's theory of how language relates to the unconditioned) constrains residue policy independently of both credit distribution and appropriation risk, which would require expanding to a three-variable model."
reviews/dialogues/2026-05-26-whether-residue-authorization-carries-information-that-credit-distributi.json:151:      "argument": "The residue-policy framing is genuinely useful. It identifies a precise operational difference at the exact point where two contemplative paths diverge: after ordinary identifications are unsettled, does the tradition permit something to remain? This is testable, specific, and avoids the twin traps of false equivalence and false opposition. The Proponent is right that the strain is not simply self versus no-self. But the framing treats residue policy as if it were a free-standing doctrinal choice, the independent variable in the comparison. I think it is downstream of a prior variable: how the tradition distributes credit for the power behind practice. Consider why Advaita can authorize a remainder. It is not because the tradition simply decided that something should persist. It is because the entire credit structure makes authorization safe. Under Shankara's ground-centered framework, liberation is praptasya praptih: the attainment of the already-attained. The Self was never absent, never produced, never the result of the practitioner's effort. Because no one made the remainder, no one can own it. The residue is safe precisely because the credit structure prevents appropriation. Now consider why early Buddhism must withhold authorization. Under the practitioner-centered credit structure of the eightfold path, the practitioner generates desire, endeavors, activates persistence, upholds and exerts intent (SN 45.8). The practitioner is the grammatical subject of every verb. In this structure, any remainder that the practitioner identifies becomes a candidate for appropriation: 'I found the unconditioned,' 'this awareness is what I really am.' That move would be a subtler form of the same identification the path aims to dissolve. The refusal of aggregate remainder in SN 22.59 is not just a doctrinal position about ontology. It is a structural safeguard calibrated to the danger of practitioner-centered credit. The Bahiya Sutta (Ud 1.10) sharpens the point. The Buddha's instruction to Bahiya, 'In the seen, just the seen,' does not operate on the residue axis at all. It does not say 'nothing remains' or 'something remains.' It says: stop inserting yourself into experience. Bahiya's liberation comes not from settling the residue question but from ceasing to distribute credit to a self who stands behind experience. The most compressed liberative instruction in the Pali canon sidesteps residue policy entirely and works at the level of credit-claiming. This suggests a counter-model. Residue policy is a dependent consequence of credit distribution. Traditions with ground-centered credit can safely authorize a remainder, because no one produced it and no one can claim it. Traditions with practitioner-centered credit must refuse to authorize a remainder, because the practitioner who finds one will appropriate it. Traditions with split credit can hold the residue question open, because the practitioner owns effort but not outcome, leaving the status of what remains formally undecided. The crux is whether the variables are separable. If two traditions share the same credit type but adopt genuinely different residue policies, then residue policy does independent work. Advaita and Dzogchen are the test case: both are ground-centered, but they may handle the post-negation remainder differently. If the Proponent can show a real divergence there, the residue-policy variable is vindicated as an independent axis. If not, it reduces to a useful but derivative label for something that credit distribution already explains.",
reviews/dialogues/2026-05-26-whether-residue-authorization-carries-information-that-credit-distributi.json:154:        "Brihadaranyaka 3.7.23 preserves an unobjectifiable seer-knower as authorized remainder.",
reviews/dialogues/2026-05-26-whether-residue-authorization-carries-information-that-credit-distributi.json:155:        "SN 22.59 withholds authorization from any aggregate, including consciousness, as remainder.",
reviews/dialogues/2026-05-26-whether-residue-authorization-carries-information-that-credit-distributi.json:160:      "counter_model": "Residue policy is not the independent variable but a dependent consequence of credit distribution. The model works as follows. (1) Traditions with ground-centered credit (nothing was ever missing; the Self was always already the case) can authorize a remainder safely, because the remainder is not an achievement anyone can claim. Shankara's praptasya praptih makes this explicit: liberation is siddha-vastu (already accomplished), not sadhya-vastu (something to be produced). There is no doer who could appropriate the result. (2) Traditions with practitioner-centered credit (you yourself must strive) must refuse to authorize a remainder, because the practitioner who identifies a stable remainder gains a new object to call 'mine.' The structural danger of practitioner-centered credit is spiritual pride; authorizing a metaphysical remainder would feed that danger directly. (3) Traditions with split credit can hold ambiguous residue policies, because the practitioner owns the effort but not the result, leaving the status of what remains formally undecided. This counter-model predicts the same textual observations the Proponent cites, but derives them from a prior variable rather than treating them as primitive.",
reviews/dialogues/2026-05-26-whether-residue-authorization-carries-information-that-credit-distributi.json:165:      "hidden_assumption": "The Proponent assumes that 'what remains after negation' is a question that can be answered by examining the post-negation move in isolation, as if residue policy were a free-standing doctrinal choice. But no tradition chooses its residue policy arbitrarily. The policy is constrained by the tradition's understanding of whose power drives the negation and what kind of remainder that power structure can safely accommodate. To treat residue policy as the independent variable is to mistake a consequence for a cause.",
reviews/dialogues/2026-05-26-whether-residue-authorization-carries-information-that-credit-distributi.json:166:      "new_source": "The Bahiya Sutta (Ud 1.10, Thanissaro Bhikkhu translation) complicates the Proponent's framing. The Buddha tells Bahiya: 'In the seen, just the seen; in the heard, just the heard; in the sensed, just the sensed; in the cognized, just the cognized. When for you, in the seen there is just the seen... then you are not in that. When you are not in that, you are not there. When you are not there, you are neither here nor there nor between the two. This, just this, is the end of suffering.' Bahiya achieves immediate liberation. This instruction neither authorizes nor withholds ontological residue. It does not say 'no awareness remains' or 'awareness remains as ground.' It says: stop adding yourself to experience. The operative move is the cessation of appropriation ('you are not in that'), not a residue decision. If the most compressed liberative instruction in the Pali canon sidesteps the residue question entirely and locates the work at credit-claiming rather than at ontological remainder, then residue policy may be less fundamental than the Proponent claims. The Bahiya Sutta suggests that what matters is not what remains but whether anyone is positioned to claim it.",
reviews/dialogues/2026-05-26-whether-residue-authorization-carries-information-that-credit-distributi.json:167:      "remaining_risk": "If the Proponent can show that Advaita and Dzogchen, despite sharing ground-centered credit, handle the post-negation remainder differently (Advaita authorizes witness-consciousness as a positive remainder while Dzogchen treats rigpa as self-liberating and refuses to stabilize it as an object of recognition), the counter-model is weakened and residue policy regains independent status. The Proponent's idea may also be rescued by recasting residue policy not as fully independent but as a second-order variable that interacts with credit distribution: credit distribution constrains which residue policies are coherent, but within those constraints, traditions make distinct choices that carry distinct practice consequences.",
reviews/dialogues/2026-05-26-whether-residue-authorization-carries-information-that-credit-distributi.json:177:      "steelman": "The residue-policy framing makes a genuinely productive move. Instead of rehearsing the broad self-versus-no-self comparison, it identifies a precise operational point where two contemplative paths diverge: the post-negation move, the moment when ordinary identifications have been unsettled and the tradition must decide what, if anything, is authorized to remain. This is testable in a way that the general comparison is not. You can open a practice manual, find the instruction given at the moment when the practitioner reports that only awareness or knowing seems to persist, and ask: does the teacher say rest as that, investigate that too, or leave it unclassified? The Brihadaranyaka 3.7.23 passage does preserve an unobjectifiable seer-knower as a permitted remainder, and SN 22.59 does refuse to exempt consciousness from the not-self analysis. The originality audit rightly reduced the novelty of the comparison itself, but the residue-authorization rubric field is a genuine contribution: it gives the translation strain a specific location and a specific observable, which is more than most Advaita-Buddhist comparisons achieve.",
reviews/dialogues/2026-05-26-whether-residue-authorization-carries-information-that-credit-distributi.json:178:      "strongest_objection": "Residue policy may not be the independent variable the Proponent claims. It may be a downstream consequence of a prior variable: how the tradition distributes credit for the power behind practice. The Advaita tradition can authorize a remainder because its ground-centered credit structure means the remainder was never produced, never achieved, never the practitioner's to own; it was always already the case (praptasya praptih). The early Buddhist tradition must refuse aggregate remainder because its practitioner-centered credit structure means anything the practitioner identifies as 'remaining' becomes a new site of appropriation, a subtle form of 'this is mine, this is my self,' restarting the very cycle the path aims to dissolve. If credit distribution constrains which residue policies are coherent for a given path, then the real point of divergence sits upstream of the residue question.",
reviews/dialogues/2026-05-26-whether-residue-authorization-carries-information-that-credit-distributi.json:179:      "test_that_would_settle_it": "Find two traditions that share the same credit-distribution type but diverge on residue policy. For instance: both Advaita Vedanta and Dzogchen operate under ground-centered credit (rigpa was always present; the Self was never absent). If they adopt meaningfully different residue policies at the post-negation moment (not just different vocabulary for the same move), then residue policy is genuinely independent of credit distribution. Alternatively, find a tradition where residue policy shifts without a corresponding shift in credit distribution, or vice versa. If no such case can be found, residue policy reduces to a downstream consequence and loses its claim to being the primary axis of translation strain.",
reviews/dialogues/2026-05-26-whether-residue-authorization-carries-information-that-credit-distributi.json:186:      "argument": "The challenge lands. My original claim treated residue policy too much like a primitive variable, when it is partly shaped by a deeper question: who or what receives credit for the power of negation and liberation. That matters because authorization is dangerous in different ways under different credit structures. A practitioner-centered path must guard against appropriation. A ground-centered path must guard against reification. I should have named that pressure directly. The defense is that residue policy still names something credit distribution alone does not name: the actual permission given at the post-negation threshold. Bahiya is the crucial correction. It does not say awareness remains as ground, and it does not turn the instruction into a metaphysical denial. It says, in effect, do not add yourself to the seen, heard, sensed, or cognized. That is not absence of policy. It is a policy of non-positioning. It tells the practitioner what cannot be claimed after de-objectification, while refusing to settle the ontology of remainder. So the model should be revised, not abandoned. Residue authorization is not the root cause. It is the doctrinal and practical interface where upstream credit structure becomes an instruction. Brihadaranyaka 3.7.23 authorizes an unobjectifiable seer-knower. SN 22.59 refuses to exempt consciousness from non-identification. Bahiya suspends the remainder question and attacks self-location directly. These are not the same moves, even if credit distribution helps explain why each is coherent. The improved Lumenary use is therefore a two-variable rubric: credit distribution asks where liberating power is located, while residue authorization asks what may be claimed, trusted, inhabited, or left unclaimed after negation. The translation strain sits at their interaction.",
reviews/dialogues/2026-05-26-whether-residue-authorization-carries-information-that-credit-distributi.json:204:      "defense": "What survives is the operational field: after negation, what may the practitioner say, trust, inhabit, infer, or refuse to claim? Credit distribution helps explain why some answers are safer than others, but it does not replace the need to code the answer itself. Bahiya is not outside residue policy. It is a disciplined refusal to authorize either self-location or ontological remainder in the moment of perception. That is a residue policy of non-positioning. The original Advaita-Buddhist contrast should therefore be narrower: not self versus no-self, and not residue versus no residue, but different permissions around de-objectified knowing under different dangers of appropriation.",
reviews/dialogues/2026-05-26-whether-residue-authorization-carries-information-that-credit-distributi.json:209:      "revised_claim": "A precise comparison between Upanishadic witness language and early Buddhist not-self should treat residue authorization as a mediating variable, not a free-standing cause. Credit distribution and appropriation risk constrain what a tradition can safely allow after negation. Within those constraints, the tradition still must give, withhold, or suspend permission around what remains teachable after ordinary identification is unsettled. Brihadaranyaka 3.7.23 permits an unobjectifiable seer-knower as remainder, while SN 22.59 extends non-identification through consciousness, and Bahiya represents a third form: non-positioning, where the instruction blocks self-insertion without making a metaphysical residue claim.",
reviews/dialogues/2026-05-26-whether-residue-authorization-carries-information-that-credit-distributi.json:220:      "test_that_would_settle_it": "Code a set of post-negation instructions across traditions for two variables: credit distribution and residue authorization. Include Advaita, Dzogchen, early Buddhist suttas such as SN 22.59 and Ud 1.10, and at least one split-credit tradition. If shared credit type always yields the same authorization type, residue policy is derivative. If the same credit type yields different permissions, such as metaphysical remainder, phenomenological remainder, non-positioning, explicit refusal, or undecidable silence, then residue policy has independent mediating value.",
reviews/dialogues/2026-05-26-whether-residue-authorization-carries-information-that-credit-distributi.json:227:      "argument": "The Proponent's revision is stronger than the original. It absorbed the credit-distribution challenge without collapsing p": "Panikkar's functional equivalence already permits bridges without identity or simple sameness.", "source": "Raimon Panikkar, homeomorphic equivalence, https://raimon-panikkar.org/english/gloss-homeomorphic.html/"}], "next_loop_instructions": ["Rename the frontier from translation strain as a test of convergence to split-axis convergence scoring: compatibility, provenance, and claim-unit variance.", "Merge or cross-index with A Shared Word Is Not Two Witnesses, Sameness Can Be the Fingerprint of Borrowing, Ask Who Taught The Answer, and A Test Must Be Able To Say Yes.", "Build a codebook with fields for claim unit, compatibility strain, provenance status, source layer, shared translator, contact pathway, borrowing likelihood, ontology remainder, practice-transfer limit, confidence, and undecidable reason.", "Do not let the same textual similarity establish both compatibility and provenance. Code provenance from independent historical evidence where possible.", "Run inter-rater reliability on Gaudapada and Nagarjuna, Chandogya and SN 22.59, apophatic theology and Buddhist emptiness, Pure Land and grace, compassion practices, and a low-variance ritual case.", "Add an unrecoverable-provenance rule: strain may generate hypotheses, but cannot be counted as independent convergence unless combined with distribution, complexity, contact analysis, and explicit uncertainty.", "For human-condition use, frame the practice as a limited thinking check for stable overconfident or over-skeptical eclectic readers. Exclude acute loneliness, OCD, scrupulosity, grief crisis, dissociation, panic, and people using comparison to avoid belonging or commitment."], "novelty_adjustment": "Lower novelty from 0.41 to 0.38. The core logic is old: resemblance does not prove genealogy, and compatibility does not prove independent discovery. Keep as an extended method-control protocol because claim-unit non-aggregation and explicit strain/provenance separation are useful for Lumenary's scoring workflow.", "originality_status": "extended", "path": "reviews/originality/2026-05-30-easy-agreement-is-not-shared-discovery-6e497a2d6f3ff2cb.json", "practitioner_test": {"answers_that_reduce_originality": "Originality falls if scholars say the model is ordinary homology versus analogy, source criticism, comparative method, or loanword versus cognate logic. It also falls if blind readers cannot distinguish it from A Shared Word Is Not Two Witnesses or Sameness Can Be the Fingerprint of Borrowing.", "answers_that_support_contribution": "Support rises if experts agree that existing Lumenary strain scoring confuses compatibility with independence, that claim-unit non-aggregation prevents real errors, and that the split-axis sheet changes verdicts in held-out cases.", "questions": ["Do you already separate compatibility from historical independence when scoring cross-tradition agreement?", "Is this just Smith's homology versus analogy distinction and historical-linguistic loanword logic in Lumenary language?", "Does claim-unit non-aggregation change how you read Gaudapada and Nagarjuna, or is it standard source criticism?", "Can strain ever give useful provenance evidence when historical records are missing?", "Would the Two-Witness Check make seekers more careful, or would it increase cynicism, rumination, and distance from real practice?"], "relevant_practitioners": ["comparative religion scholars", "historians of religion", "Sanskritists", "Buddhologists", "Advaita Vedanta scholars", "Madhyamaka scholars", "historical linguists", "comparative theologians", "interfaith educators", "Buddhist and Vedanta practitioners"]}, "primary_text_close_read": {"primary_pair": ["Gaudapada, Mandukya Karika 4.22, https://www.wisdomlib.org/hinduism/book/mandukya-upanishad-karika-bhashya/d/doc143736.html, read against Nagarjuna, Mulamadhyamakakarika 1.1, https://www.dharma-university-press.org/component/k2/item/62-mulamadhyamakakarika-nagarjunas-grundlegende-gedanken-zum-mittleren-weg.html", "Richard King on the Mahayana context of the Gaudapadiya-karika, https://philpapers.org/rec/KINEAV-2, and related discussion of Buddhist influence on Advaita, https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Buddhist_influences_on_Advaita_Vedanta"], "risk_of_overread": "Moderate. The central distinction is strong but largely known as homology versus analogy, loanword versus cognate, and provenance-first comparison. The candidate may overstate orthogonality, since extreme strain can sometimes be weak evidence against direct borrowing and unusually regular low-strain structures may guide hypotheses when provenance is unrecoverable. Human-condition fit is narrow: it helps spiritually eclectic readers and online seekers who use easy cross-tradition agreement to stabilize identity or meaning. It is not a loneliness remedy and can feed cynicism or rumination.", "secondary_literature_gap": "Read Jonathan Z. Smith's Drudgery Divine and In Comparison a Magic Dwells, Freiberger's comparative methodology, Panikkar on homeomorphic equivalence, King, Comans, Murti, Bhattacharya, Sharma, and specialist Gaudapada and Madhyamaka studies. Also compare historical linguistics on cognates, loanwords, chance resemblance, and regular sound correspondences before claiming more than a method-control extension.", "structural_observation": "Gaudapada 4.22 and MMK 1.1 share a very low-strain fourfold denial of origination from self, other, both, or causelessness. The structural match is strong at the dialectical level. Yet the authorized remainder differs: Gaudapada's non-origination is folded into an Advaita-Mandukya frame of unborn nondual reality, while Nagarjuna's causal analysis pressures svabhava without granting an Atman substratum. Scholarship on Buddhist influence also makes low strain historically ambiguous, since it may indicate contact, borrowing, or polemical reuse rather than two independent witnesses."}, "recommended_scores": {"counterargument_quality": 0.9, "novelty": 0.38, "source_reliability": 0.8}, "run_ids": ["20260530-130216-codex-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-", "20260530-130216-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-"], "title": "Easy Agreement Is Not Shared Discovery", "unlike_statement": "Unlike Smith's homology and analogy, historical linguistics, Gaudapada influence scholarship, Freiberger, Panikkar, and prior Lumenary provenance records, this candidate's specific contribution is to relabel translation strain as compatibility only, require provenance as a separate axis, and forbid aggregate pair-level strain when claim units differ."}
reviews/originality/audits.jsonl:84:{"agent": "claude", "anomaly_probe": {"anomaly_candidate": "A person with strong external supports collapses more severely because those supports are coercive, shaming, unreliable, or tied to performance, while a strongly self-directed person recovers faster through restored agency, sleep, treatment, and practical problem solving.", "confidence_effect": "Keeps the status at extended and lowers practice confidence until support quality, agency history, clinical risk, and event magnitude are coded separately from continuity location.", "why_it_breaks_or_strains_model": "The model assumes externalized holding is protective for the target cohort. If support safety and agency restoration matter more than support location, the core variable is not where continuity sits but whether the holder is trustworthy, noncoercive, and actually available. This also catches the non-fit case: people harmed by denied agency may be injured by surrender language."}, "audit_id": "e30798c2dedf5eaa", "claim_units": ["Continuity can be located in self-command, body, routines, relationships, duty, faith, vows, or community.", "Performance-owned continuity should predict more total destabilization when performance fails.", "The useful intervention is preventative relocation of some steadiness outside self-command, not post-collapse control rebuilding.", "The broad comparative continuity rubric is already duplicated inside Lumenary and in external literature.", "No-gap teachings strain the continuity-across-a-threshold frame because there is no gap to carry continuity across.", "The human-condition fit is narrow: achievement-contingent self-worth and burnout collapse, not denied agency, abuse, acute crisis, or severe clinical distress."], "confidence": 0.78, "created_at": "2026-05-30T14:03:30+02:00", "cross_domain_prediction": {"domain": "Organizational resilience and knowledge work", "prediction": "Teams, families, or care systems with distributed continuity before a disruption will recover faster and with less identity crisis than systems held mainly by one heroic performer, after controlling for disruption size and resources.", "structural_translation": "A system whose continuity is held by one performative node collapses harder when that node fails than a system whose continuity is distributed across routines, documentation, relationships, backups, and role redundancy.", "would_count_against_it": "Event magnitude, funding, staffing, and prior load explain recovery completely, and pre-break continuity distribution adds no measurable predictive value."}, "exact_claim": "For people whose steadiness and worth were held mostly by performance and self-command, collapse should be more total than for people whose continuity already lived partly in body, relationship, routine, duty, faith, or recovery support. The broad comparative claim about continuity after self-negation is old and overbuilt. The defensible contribution is a narrow person-level prediction plus a boundary condition: no-gap paths such as Dogen-style practice-realization should not be forced into a carry-across-a-threshold model.", "execution_id": "parallel-20260530-135009-20260530-135009", "falsifiable_predictions": [{"expected_observation": "Among people recovering from burnout, grief, caregiving overload, or early addiction recovery, those whose steadiness was mostly performance-owned should report more total destabilization than matched peers whose steadiness was distributed across relationships, routines, body, faith, duty, or recovery groups.", "if_model_is_right": "Pre-collapse continuity location is a real vulnerability variable.", "test_surface": "Prospective or retrospective coded interviews with burnout clinicians, recovery sponsors, chaplains, caregivers, founders, and high-achieving professionals.", "would_weaken_or_falsify": "Collapse severity is fully explained by sleep loss, trauma history, event magnitude, financial precarity, clinical diagnosis, and support quality, with no independent effect for continuity location."}, {"expected_observation": "Screened high-achievement participants using the practice for two weeks show reduced self-worth conversion, less grip, more concrete help-seeking or routine use, and no increase in helplessness or guilt compared with ordinary rest-and-ask-for-help and planning prompts.", "if_model_is_right": "The practice Name What Carries You addresses the named wound better than generic reflection.", "test_surface": "Small randomized pilot with achievement-contingent self-worth, burnout, rumination, help-seeking, shame, action completion, and adverse-effect measures.", "would_weaken_or_falsify": "The practice increases dependency, guilt, helplessness, self-monitoring, avoidance, or performs no better than ordinary social support and rest."}, {"expected_observation": "Dogen, Huangbo, and Dzogchen direct-recognition sources should not describe continuity as something carried across a before-after threshold; they should emphasize present practice, direct recognition, or search refusal instead.", "if_model_is_right": "The no-gap boundary is real.", "test_surface": "Split-source close reading of Bendowa, Genjokoan or Uji, Huangbo transmission texts, one Dzogchen or Mahamudra pointing-out manual, and practitioner interviews.", "would_weaken_or_falsify": "Close reading finds robust threshold-carry language in no-gap sources, or practitioners report that continuity migration is a native teaching in those settings."}, {"expected_observation": "Blind readers can state the added variables: pre-collapse continuity location, collapse severity, and no-gap exclusion.", "if_model_is_right": "The new claim is distinguishable from the prior continuity cluster.", "test_surface": "Blind distinct-content coding of recent Lumenary continuity and support-holder records with titles removed.", "would_weaken_or_falsify": "Blind readers cannot distinguish this record from Continuity Ecology Under Negation, Operational Remainder Ecology, Custody and Receiving Surface, or Some Help Should Not Be Managed."}], "idea_id": "84b6d1547156a7e8", "idea_path": "observations/claude/2026-05-30-what-holds-you-that-you-did-not-build.md", "literature_search_queries": ["Pargament religious coping deferring collaborative self-directing coping styles", "Jack Engler you have to be somebody before you can be nobody spirituality psychology", "Clark Chalmers extended mind religious cognition Krueger religious cognition extended mind", "SN 45.8 Magga vibhanga right effort desire persistence intent translation", "Shinran Tannisho Other Power self power divergence teacher correction", "Dogen Bendowa practice realization shusho itto no gap practice realization one", "attachment theory secure base stress regulation social support review Bowlby secure base", "Linville self-complexity buffer stress depression mixed support", "Crocker Wolfe contingencies of self-worth achievement failure self-esteem", "Alcoholics Anonymous Twelve Steps power greater than ourselves social support recovery"], "markdown_path": "reviews/originality/2026-05-30-what-holds-you-that-you-did-not-build-e30798c2dedf5eaa.md", "near_neighbors": [{"difference": "This candidate narrows the ambition to one person-level prediction about pre-collapse continuity location and adds a no-gap exclusion test.", "novelty_impact": "Major downgrade. Treat as an extension and consolidation unless the collapse-severity prediction shows independent value.", "overlap": "Very close. The same variables recur: dissolution target, residue policy, support holder, receiving surface, failure mode, and a warning that the model is too elastic without split-source coding.", "source": "Internal Lumenary continuity cluster: Continuity Ecology Under Negation, Distributed Continuity Architecture, Continuity Location Under Transformative Practice, Operational Remainder Ecology, Custody and Receiving Surface, plus the candidate file observations/claude/2026-05-30-what-holds-you-that-you-did-not-build.md"}, {"difference": "The candidate widens the holder set beyond God to body, routine, relationship, duty, and prior promises, and predicts collapse severity in performance-owned lives.", "novelty_impact": "Strong reduction for support-locus originality, partial preservation for the burnout-specific prediction.", "overlap": "Very close on responsibility location. Self-directing, deferring, and collaborative coping already code whether the person, God, or a shared relation carries problem-solving.", "source": "Pargament et al., Religion and the Problem-Solving Process: Three Styles of Coping, 1988, indexed at https://icmglt.org/icmlibrary/religion-and-the-problem-solving-process-three-styles-of-coping/ and https://www.kennethpargament.com/rs-coping-measures-dev-gen-rel"}, {"difference": "The candidate translates extension into collapse vulnerability and practice design for achievement-contingent self-worth.", "novelty_impact": "Moderate to strong downgrade. The external-holder ontology is known; the practice-fit and collapse prediction are the local extension.", "overlap": "Close. External artifacts, language, culture, ritual, sacred spaces, songs, relics, and other persons can be part of cognition or religious cognition rather than merely background aids.", "source": "Clark and Chalmers, The Extended Mind, https://consc.net/papers/extended.html, and Joel Krueger, Extended Mind and Religious Cognition, https://philarchive.org/rec/KRUTEM-2"}, {"difference": "The candidate is not merely about attachment figures. It includes bodily rhythms, routines, vows, duties, faith, and recovery supports, and it asks about performance collapse.", "novelty_impact": "Strong reduction for the human kernel that steadiness is partly externally supported.", "overlap": "Close. A person's exploration and stress regulation are supported by reliable others who provide a safe haven and secure base.", "source": "Attachment secure-base literature, for example Feeney and Thrush on secure base support in adulthood, https://pmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/articles/PMC2805473/, and Bowlby secure-base tradition indexed in attachment literature"}, {"difference": "The candidate targets non-addiction performance collapse and asks where continuity sat before the break, not only how recovery is held after admission of powerlessness.", "novelty_impact": "Major downgrade for surrender and externalized holding; partial novelty remains only if the pre-collapse-location measure predicts severity.", "overlap": "Close practitioner near-neighbor. AA explicitly externalizes recovery through a higher power, another human being, inventory, amends, service, meetings, and sponsorship-like community structures.", "source": "Alcoholics Anonymous official Twelve Steps, https://www.aa.org/the-twelve-steps, and AA social-network support literature such as https://pmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/articles/PMC2289871/"}, {"difference": "The candidate adds a continuity-location and collapse-severity hypothesis rather than only self-esteem contingency or perfectionism trend.", "novelty_impact": "Moderate downgrade. The wound is known; the proposed holder-map may be a useful practice-specific operationalization.", "overlap": "Close on the target wound. Self-worth can depend on success, achievement, approval, competition, appearance, family support, virtue, or divine love; perfectionism links self-worth to achievement and harsh evaluation.", "source": "Crocker and Wolfe contingencies of self-worth, summarized and tested in https://link.springer.com/article/10.1007/s12144-020-01007-5, and Curran and Hill on rising perfectionism, https://eprints.lse.ac.uk/101352/1/Curran_Hill2018.pdf"}, {"difference": "The candidate uses Dogen not as support but as a boundary condition against overgeneralized continuity-across-threshold models.", "novelty_impact": "Useful boundary, but not a discovery. It prevents overreach more than it creates a new doctrine.", "overlap": "The no-gap anomaly is not new. Practice-realization unity is a known Soto Zen frame, and the literature already resists treating practice as a means to a later result.", "source": "Dogen shusho itto and Bendowa materials, https://global.sotozen-net.or.jp/eng/library/key_terms/pdf/key_terms07.pdf and https://afe.easia.columbia.edu/ps/japan/dogen.pdf"}], "next_loop_instructions": ["Do not publish as a standalone discovery. Cross-index with Continuity Ecology Under Negation, Operational Remainder Ecology, Custody and Receiving Surface, Some Help Should Not Be Managed, and Keep What Can Correct You.", "Build a bounded codebook with fields for pre-collapse continuity locus, support quality, agency history, collapse severity, clinical risk, event magnitude, sleep, trauma history, and repair path.", "Run the blind distinct-content test on the continuity cluster before generating another support-holder rubric.", "Close-read Dogen, Huangbo, Dzogchen, Shinran, and SN 45.8 for threshold-carry language versus present-act, vow-held, or effort-held language.", "Pilot Name What Carries You only with screened stable high performers and caregivers. Compare against ordinary rest, social support, and planning prompts.", "Add explicit stop rules for denied agency, coercion, spiritual abuse, severe depression, mania, psychosis, addiction withdrawal, acute crisis, and cases where no real support is available."], "novelty_adjustment": "Lower novelty from 0.42 to 0.36. The broad structure is known through internal Lumenary rubrics, Pargament, extended mind, secure-base theory, AA, and self-worth research. Keep as an extended, testable person-level hypothesis only if pre-collapse continuity location and the no-gap exclusion add predictive power.", "originality_status": "extended", "path": "reviews/originality/2026-05-30-what-holds-you-that-you-did-not-build-e30798c2dedf5eaa.json", "practitioner_test": {"answers_that_reduce_originality": "Originality falls if clinicians and practitioners say the useful part is standard social support, secure-base work, recovery surrender, religious coping, self-complexity, or self-worth contingency work, and if the continuity-location code adds no prediction beyond support quality and clinical risk.", "answers_that_support_contribution": "Support rises if practitioners can code pre-collapse continuity location reliably, if that code predicts severity or repair beyond ordinary supports, and if no-gap teachers confirm that the carry-across-threshold model is a category error in their setting.", "questions": ["In concrete collapse cases, do people whose identity was mainly performance-held collapse more totally than people whose continuity was already distributed?", "Is this just secure-base theory, religious coping, recovery surrender, and contingencies of self-worth in new language?", "Would the practice change what you recommend, or would ordinary rest, social support, therapy, and asking for help do the same work?", "Can you name cases where leaning on what the person did not build increased dependency, shame, helplessness, or exposure to unsafe authority?", "Do no-gap traditions you know reject the carry-across-threshold frame, or do they have native language for continuity being held across a shift?"], "relevant_practitioners": ["burnout clinicians", "occupational health researchers", "addiction recovery sponsors", "chaplains and pastoral caregivers", "Jodo Shinshu teachers or scholars", "Soto Zen teachers or scholars", "Theravada teachers", "attachment researchers", "perfectionism and self-worth researchers", "caregiver support practitioners"]}, "primary_text_close_read": {"primary_pair": ["Shinran, Tannisho, especially chapters 1, 3, 6, 8, and 11, https://jodoshinshu.faith/tannisho-a-record-in-lament-of-divergences/, read against SN 45.8 Magga-vibhanga Sutta, https://www.accesstoinsight.org/tipitaka/sn/sn45/sn45.008.than.html", "Dogen practice-realization as anomaly, using Bendowa excerpt https://afe.easia.columbia.edu/ps/japan/dogen.pdf and Soto Zen shusho itto note https://global.sotozen-net.or.jp/eng/library/key_terms/pdf/key_terms07.pdf"], "risk_of_overread": "Moderate to high. Shinran's Vow is not merely psychological support, and SN 45.8 right effort is not simple self-command. The no-gap boundary could become too elastic if analysts say practice itself holds continuity in every case. Human-condition fit is real but narrow: it may help stable high performers, founders, caregivers, and perfectionists, but it can harm people whose wound is denied agency, coercive dependence, abusive religion, acute crisis, severe depression, mania, psychosis, addiction withdrawal, or lack of actual support.", "secondary_literature_gap": "Before any stronger novelty claim, read Shinran scholarship on Other Power, hakarai, jinen, and Tannisho transmission; Dogen scholarship on shusho itto and honsho myoshu; Engler on self development before no-self work; Bowlby, Ainsworth, and adult secure-base literature; Linville and later mixed findings on self-complexity as a stress buffer; Crocker and Wolfe on contingencies of self-worth; Pargament on religious coping; AA social-network outcome literature; burnout and perfectionism studies; and practitioner-facing recovery and chaplaincy sources.", "structural_observation": "Tannisho relocates decisive efficacy away from self-powered practice and into Amida's Vow, while still preserving teacher, transmission, and warnings against divergent interpretation. SN 45.8 defines right effort through desire, persistence, intent, and maintenance of skillful qualities, so the practitioner remains an active support locus. The Soto shusho itto material says practice and realization are inseparable and that practice is necessary because realization is already present. This supports the candidate's boundary pressure: some sources contrast support loci, but Dogen does not describe a result carried over a before-after gap."}, "recommended_scores": {"counterargument_quality": 0.9, "novelty": 0.36, "source_reliability": 0.82}, "run_ids": ["20260530-135009-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-", "20260530-135009-codex-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-"], "title": "What Holds You That You Did Not Build", "unlike_statement": "Unlike Pargament's coping styles, extended mind, secure-base theory, AA surrender, contingencies of self-worth, and prior Lumenary continuity rubrics, this idea's specific contribution is to predict that pre-collapse continuity location will add explanatory value for burnout collapse severity, and to exclude no-gap practice-realization cases from a carry-across-threshold model."}
reviews/originality/audits.jsonl:85:{"agent": "codex", "anomaly_probe": {"anomaly_candidate": "A radical no-seeking or direct-recognition setting where a practitioner matures ethically and relationally without any identifiable external correction holder, or where naming support itself reintroduces the very search, calculation, or self-effort the teaching cuts.", "confidence_effect": "Keeps the status at extended and prevents publication as doctrine. It demands native-source coding, valid-solitude categories, unsafe-holder categories, and practitioner interviews before any public teaching.", "why_it_breaks_or_strains_model": "If no-distance practice can function without codeable correction holders, or if the native warning is against every support-seeking gesture, then the candidate's support rule is an analyst imposition. A second anomaly is abusive correction: support can be the failure source rather than the remedy."}, "audit_id": "5e945a54e9681489", "claim_units": ["No-distance does not mean no support.", "Anti-ownership should be coded before remainder, residue, or completion variables.", "If practitioner ownership is refused, correction may be held by teacher, text, vow, practice form, community, conduct, ritual, ordinary duty, or clinical support.", "No-distance failures should cluster around privatization, passivity, performance, or loss of correction.", "The human-condition fit is stable over-managers and isolated practitioners who turn relief or insight into private performance.", "The claim is not for acute crisis, abusive teacher settings, severe depression, dissociation, addiction withdrawal, or cases needing direct clinical care or protection."], "confidence": 0.8, "created_at": "2026-05-30T14:03:30+02:00", "cross_domain_prediction": {"domain": "AI automation and operational governance", "prediction": "AI or automation systems marketed as autonomous will fail more safely when correction channels remain external and concrete. Teams that remove ownership and monitoring together will show more uncorrected drift, brittle confidence, and harder incident recovery.", "structural_translation": "A system that removes manual ownership or promises autonomous operation still needs observability, rollback, escalation, monitoring, and accountable maintenance. No manual path is not no care.", "would_count_against_it": "Fully autonomous systems without independent monitoring, escalation, rollback, or human accountability perform as safely and adaptively as systems with correction channels across drift, edge cases, and user harm."}, "exact_claim": "No-distance teachings may remove the private project of becoming spiritual, but they do not thereby remove care, correction, companionship, schedule, teacher, text, vow, or ordinary accountability. Before asking what remains after self-negation, code whether the path grants the practitioner ownership at all. If ownership is refused, the key question is where correction is held and whether failures cluster when students privatize the insight, abandon correction, become passive, or turn relief into performance.", "execution_id": "parallel-20260530-135009-20260530-135009", "falsifiable_predictions": [{"expected_observation": "Split-source coding of Dogen, Huangbo, Shinran, Dzogchen, and Mahamudra sources will find ownership refusal in one layer and held-out warnings, teacher checks, vow, practice form, text, community, conduct, or reentry rules in another.", "if_model_is_right": "No-distance teachings refuse private ownership but preserve some concrete correction or care holder.", "test_surface": "Pre-registered primary-text codebook with source layer, ownership, after, correction holder, support holder, warning, repair, and analyst-frame refusal.", "would_weaken_or_falsify": "Sources deny both private ownership and codeable correction holders, or coders cannot distinguish support from the mere existence of a tradition."}, {"expected_observation": "Practitioner and teacher reports should cluster around private certainty, passivity, social withdrawal, inflated no-practice claims, or turning relief into performance when healthy support is absent or rejected.", "if_model_is_right": "Loss of correction support predicts specific no-distance failures.", "test_surface": "Teacher interviews, Cheetah House or VCE-style adverse-event coding, retreat reentry reports, and no-distance online community case coding.", "would_weaken_or_falsify": "Failures are better explained by practice intensity, sleep loss, trauma, teacher abuse, clinical risk, social isolation, or doctrine alone, with no added value from support-holder loss."}, {"expected_observation": "Stable over-managers using the check after insight or relief report less private auditing, more reachability, and more concrete duty return than journaling-only controls, without increased dependency, shame, or self-monitoring.", "if_model_is_right": "The Support Check helps only the named modern cohort.", "test_surface": "Two-week low-risk pilot with stable self-directed practitioners, app meditators, and self-improvers, excluding acute crisis and clinical non-fit cases.", "would_weaken_or_falsify": "The check increases rumination, dependence, unsafe authority-seeking, avoidance, burden, or performs no better than ordinary social contact and rest."}, {"expected_observation": "Blind coders can use anti-ownership and correction-holder fields to predict held-out warnings and repairs in no-distance cases better than Keep What Can Correct You, Some Help Should Not Be Managed, tradition label, or generic VCE factors alone.", "if_model_is_right": "Anti-ownership support coding adds decision power beyond prior Lumenary records.", "test_surface": "A/B coding comparison on Dogen, Huangbo, Tannisho, Dzogchen, Mahamudra, Pure Land, and one causal Theravada path.", "would_weaken_or_falsify": "The new fields do not change decisions, or blind readers cannot state the difference from existing correction-holder and no-management records."}], "idea_id": "9acdff6fe237d648", "idea_path": "observations/codex/2026-05-30-even-no-path-needs-care.md", "literature_search_queries": ["Dogen Bendowa practice realization shusho itto no gaining practice realization one", "Huangbo Transmission of Mind no seeking objective path teacher support correction", "Shinran Tannisho Other Power self power divergence true teacher correction", "Talal Asad discursive tradition correct model practice authority orthodoxy", "George Lindbeck doctrine as grammar cultural linguistic practice training", "Varieties of Contemplative Experience meditation difficulties teacher community relationships support", "spiritual bypassing spiritual practice avoidance correction community support research", "mindfulness optimization pressure burnout self optimization Sauerborn Sokefeld Neckel 2022", "Cheetah House meditation related difficulties support groups teacher community", "Dzogchen direct introduction support teacher correction no path practice"], "markdown_path": "reviews/originality/2026-05-30-even-no-path-needs-care-5e945a54e9681489.md", "near_neighbors": [{"difference": "The present candidate narrows that rule to no-distance and anti-ownership teachings and predicts failure clusters when support is abandoned.", "novelty_impact": "Major downgrade. The teaching candidate even reuses the earlier title. Treat as an extension, not a standalone discovery.", "overlap": "Extremely close. It already says serious results remain immature if they remove trustworthy correction paths such as teacher, text, community, conduct, duty, or clinical boundary.", "source": "Internal Lumenary prior: Keep What Can Correct You, originality audit 2026-05-29, reviews/originality/2026-05-29-keep-what-can-correct-you-*.md"}, {"difference": "This record applies that holder-routing logic to no-distance teachings and asks specifically where correction is held when ownership is refused.", "novelty_impact": "Major downgrade. The new contribution is a domain-specific scope condition.", "overlap": "Very close. That audit already says some help is distorted by private management and asks whether ownership, a permitted after, and spare agency exist before prescribing review, with alternative holders such as community, vow, conduct, rest, teacher, or support.", "source": "Internal Lumenary prior: Some Help Should Not Be Managed, reviews/originality/2026-05-30-some-help-should-not-be-managed-fa2107c4aba3ff90.md"}, {"difference": "Asad does not isolate no-distance teachings or predict privatization, passivity, or performance failures after ownership refusal.", "novelty_impact": "Strong downgrade for the claim that practice meaning and correction are tradition-held.", "overlap": "Close structural prior. Asad treats correct practice, authorization, teaching, power, and argument as internal to tradition rather than optional social context.", "source": "Talal Asad, The Idea of an Anthropology of Islam, https://voidnetwork.gr/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/The-Idea-of-an-Anthropology-of-Islam-by-Talal-Asad.pdf"}, {"difference": "The candidate turns this into a no-distance safety and failure-prediction codebook.", "novelty_impact": "Moderate to strong downgrade. The anti-private-experience posture is known.", "overlap": "Close. Lindbeck's cultural-linguistic model already makes religion prior to the individual and treats doctrine as grammar learned through practice and training.", "source": "George Lindbeck, The Nature of Doctrine, summarized at https://people.bu.edu/wwildman/bce/mwt_themes_862_lindbeck.htm and indexed at https://books.google.com/books/about/The_Nature_of_Doctrine.html?id=_fbYAAAAMAAJ"}, {"difference": "VCE is empirical safety taxonomy, not a no-distance doctrinal coding rule.", "novelty_impact": "Strong reduction for the practitioner-safety and support-holder piece.", "overlap": "Very close in practice safety. VCE separates experience, interpretation, management, teacher and community relationships, support, impairment, health behavior, and social functioning. Cheetah House provides support routing for meditation-related difficulties.", "source": "Lindahl et al., The Varieties of Contemplative Experience, PLOS One 2017, https://journals.plos.org/plosone/article?id=10.1371/journal.pone.0176239, and Cheetah House FAQ, https://www.cheetahhouse.org/faq"}, {"difference": "The candidate ties misuse to no-distance anti-ownership language and correction-holder loss.", "novelty_impact": "Moderate downgrade for the modern human-condition mechanism.", "overlap": "Close on modern misuse. Mindfulness can become both escape from optimization pressure and symptom of it, while spiritual bypassing names avoidance through spiritual language.", "source": "Sauerborn, Sokefeld, and Neckel, Paradoxes of mindfulness, https://journals.sagepub.com/doi/abs/10.1177/00380261221108570, plus spiritual bypassing research such as https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/34025522/"}, {"difference": "The candidate generalizes this into a comparative rule across no-distance teachings and support ecologies.", "novelty_impact": "Major reduction for Dogen-specific originality, partial preservation for cross-case testing.", "overlap": "It already states that practice and realization are inseparable while Dogen strongly emphasizes active practice, so no-gap is not no-practice.", "source": "Soto Zen shusho itto source, https://global.sotozen-net.or.jp/eng/library/key_terms/pdf/key_terms07.pdf"}, {"difference": "The candidate may overuse Huangbo as support for correction when his discourse also cuts support-seeking itself.", "novelty_impact": "Acts more as anomaly than support. It lowers confidence unless coded natively.", "overlap": "Huangbo already supplies the no-seeking pressure and warnings about false teachers, casual pilgrimage, and conceptual path-making.", "source": "Huangbo, Transmission of Mind, Blofeld record https://merton.bellarmine.edu/s/merton/media/51897 and searchable PDF https://wayofsuddenawakening.org/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/Huang-Po-The-Transmission-of-Mind.pdf"}], "next_loop_instructions": ["Do not publish as a standalone discovery. Cross-index with Keep What Can Correct You, Some Help Should Not Be Managed, When Tools Become Judges, Who Holds The Gate, and Not Every Check Should Be Yours.", "Build a pre-remainder codebook with fields for ownership grant, no-distance grammar, permitted after, correction holder, support holder, warning, repair, unsafe holder, valid solitude, clinical exclusion, and analyst-frame refusal.", "Use split-source coding. Do not let one passage establish ownership refusal and confirm the predicted warning or repair.", "Test Dogen, Huangbo, Tannisho, Dzogchen or Mahamudra direct introduction, Pure Land, and one causal Theravada path before broad tradition claims.", "Run practitioner interviews for concrete failed-student and repair cases, not agreement with the slogan.", "Pilot the Support Check only with screened stable over-managers. Compare against ordinary journaling, social contact, teacher check-in, and rest prompts.", "Add stop rules for OCD or scrupulosity, dependency, shame, dissociation, severe depression, mania, psychosis, addiction withdrawal, trauma activation, unsafe authority, coercive groups, and acute crisis."], "novelty_adjustment": "Lower novelty from 0.62 to 0.34. The core rule is heavily anticipated by internal correction-holder records, Some Help Should Not Be Managed, Asad, Lindbeck, VCE, spiritual bypassing research, and Soto practice-realization sources. Retain only as an extended no-distance scope test if split-source coding shows predictive gain.", "originality_status": "extended", "path": "reviews/originality/2026-05-30-even-no-path-needs-care-5e945a54e9681489.json", "practitioner_test": {"answers_that_reduce_originality": "Originality falls if practitioners say the rule is standard lineage pedagogy, spiritual direction, sangha correction, Soto practice-realization, Shin Other Power instruction, or meditation-safety triage, and if the support check adds no decisions beyond existing practice guidance.", "answers_that_support_contribution": "Support rises if practitioners find that coding ownership refusal before remainder prevents real interpretive errors, predicts failure cases, and improves support routing without increasing self-effort, dependency, or unsafe authority.", "questions": ["When a no-distance teaching removes the private project of attainment, what if anything still corrects a mistaken interpretation?", "Is this just ordinary teacher, sangha, scripture, vow, spiritual direction, or VCE safety guidance in Lumenary language?", "Can you name cases where no-path language led to passivity, private certainty, social withdrawal, or performance of being beyond practice?", "Can you name cases where support checks themselves became self-effort, reassurance seeking, dependence, or obedience to unsafe authority?", "Would the pre-remainder ownership gate change screening, sequencing, warning, or repair instructions in your setting?"], "relevant_practitioners": ["Soto Zen teachers and scholars", "Chan or Zen teachers familiar with Huangbo", "Jodo Shinshu teachers and scholars", "Dzogchen or Mahamudra teachers", "Theravada teachers for contrast cases", "spiritual directors", "meditation-safety clinicians", "Cheetah House or VCE-informed researchers", "burnout clinicians", "self-directed app meditators and retreatants"]}, "primary_text_close_read": {"primary_pair": ["Dogen Bendowa and Soto shusho itto sources, https://afe.easia.columbia.edu/ps/japan/dogen.pdf and https://global.sotozen-net.or.jp/eng/library/key_terms/pdf/key_terms07.pdf, read against Huangbo, The Transmission of Mind, Blofeld record https://merton.bellarmine.edu/s/merton/media/51897 and searchable PDF used at https://wayofsuddenawakening.org/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/Huang-Po-The-Transmission-of-Mind.pdf", "Shinran, Tannisho, especially preface, chapters 1, 6, 8, 10, 11, and 12, https://jodoshinshu.faith/tannisho-a-record-in-lament-of-divergences/"], "risk_of_overread": "High. The model can become circular by counting any surviving text, teacher, or community as support. It can also domesticate Huangbo-style search-refusal by turning an anti-support discourse into analyst-defined support. It may hide abuse if correction holders are assumed safe, and it may pathologize valid solitude. Human-condition fit is clear but narrow: stable isolated over-managers, app meditators, retreatants, and self-improvers. It is not a loneliness cure by itself and can increase dependency, rumination, or unsafe authority compliance.", "secondary_literature_gap": "Read full Dogen Bendowa, Genjokoan, Uji, Eihei Shingi, and Soto scholarship; Huangbo in multiple translations plus Chan transmission studies; Shinran, Tannisho, jinen, hakarai, and Other Power scholarship; Dzogchen and Mahamudra direct introduction manuals; Asad, Lindbeck, MacIntyre, Bell, Sharf, Katz, spiritual bypassing research, VCE, Cheetah House, mindfulness optimization critique, and spiritual direction ethics. Interviews with no-distance practitioners are essential.", "structural_observation": "Dogen's practice-realization unity rejects practice as a cause separate from later realization, but Soto explanatory material also says Dogen emphasized active practice because realization is already present. Huangbo is a sharper anomaly: he rejects objective seeking and objective path language, yet the record is itself teacher discourse and includes testing a teacher's groundedness and warning against casual pilgrimage. Tannisho denies self-powered practice and calculation, yet it opens by lamenting divergences, relies on true teachers, and preserves Vow, teacher, and correction. The candidate's narrow claim survives as a hypothesis: no-distance language is not automatically support-free, but the specific holder must be coded natively."}, "recommended_scores": {"counterargument_quality": 0.91, "novelty": 0.34, "source_reliability": 0.82}, "run_ids": ["20260530-135009-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-", "20260530-135009-codex-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-"], "title": "Even No Path Needs Care", "unlike_statement": "Unlike Keep What Can Correct You, Some Help Should Not Be Managed, Asad, Lindbeck, VCE, spiritual bypassing research, and Soto practice-realization sources, this idea's specific contribution is to make anti-ownership a pre-remainder coding gate for no-distance teachings and to predict that loss of correction support will produce privatization, passivity, or performance failures."}
reviews/originality/audits.jsonl:86:{"agent": "claude", "anomaly_probe": {"anomaly_candidate": "Rinzai koan and huatou practice deliberately uses an impossible or destabilizing question to create great doubt, while Dzogchen can deny path and result yet still require direct introduction, teacher relation, and integration.", "confidence_effect": "Lowers confidence in a binary search-sequence versus search-refusal model. Raises confidence only for a more cautious codebook that includes search-refusal, question-as-medicine, no-distance-with-support, and undecidable.", "why_it_breaks_or_strains_model": "If a path uses an apparently malformed question as medicine, then question-refusal is not enough to decide that remainder pressure is analyst-made. If no-path language still depends on transmission and repair holders, then the residue question may be relocated to practice ecology rather than abolished."}, "audit_id": "d756c9bf775096c6", "claim_units": ["Some contemplative paths stage a search sequence, so they generate a legitimate downstream remainder question.", "Some paths refuse the search sequence itself, so remainder pressure is malformed there.", "A precondition test should precede continuity, custody, or residue coding.", "The modern harm clarified is achievement-contingent self-worth turned into compulsive auditing for emptiness, detachment, or egolessness."], "confidence": 0.84, "created_at": "2026-05-30T14:21:04+02:00", "cross_domain_prediction": {"domain": "psychotherapy and performance coaching", "prediction": "For stable clients using acceptance or values-based practices, asking how to prove acceptance will increase rumination and self-monitoring, while a permitted-question check followed by ordinary valued action will reduce over-control.", "structural_translation": "Some methods stage change as a sequence with a before and after, while acceptance-based or non-striving methods treat the attempt to prove change as part of the control agenda.", "would_count_against_it": "If outcomes are explained fully by trait rumination, therapist alliance, workload, sleep, or clinical risk, and permitted-question coding adds no predictive value."}, "exact_claim": "Before any continuity or residue analysis after self-negation, test whether the path stages self-negation as an event with an after. If a path refuses seeking, before-and-after, or self-owned attainment, the question of what remains may be an analyst artifact rather than a practitioner problem.", "execution_id": "parallel-20260530-140914-20260530-140914", "falsifiable_predictions": [{"expected_observation": "Blind coders using only doctrinal or instruction passages can sort cases into search-sequence, search-refusal, question-as-medicine, no-distance-with-support, and undecidable above chance before seeing warnings or repairs.", "if_model_is_right": "The precondition gate has independent coding value.", "test_surface": "Inter-rater coding on SN 22.59, SN 22.95, Huangbo, Bendowa, Tannisho, one Dzogchen direct-introduction source, and one Rinzai koan source.", "would_weaken_or_falsify": "Coders cannot agree, or their labels are just tradition labels, teacher style, or genre labels in disguise."}, {"expected_observation": "In search-sequence cases, warnings and repairs cluster around misidentification, clinging, effort, and post-release integration. In search-refusal cases, warnings cluster around seeking, monitoring, conceptualization, and self-grading.", "if_model_is_right": "Remainder pressure is not universal.", "test_surface": "Split-source coding, code path grammar from one corpus and predict held-out warnings, repairs, and practitioner failure cases.", "would_weaken_or_falsify": "Warnings and failures in search-refusal cases are predicted just as well by support-holder loss, teacher absence, trauma, sleep loss, or institutional harm without using the precondition gate."}, {"expected_observation": "Stable over-auditors using Stop the Emptiness Audit report less self-grading and faster return to ordinary care than journaling-only or rest-only controls, without increased avoidance or reassurance seeking.", "if_model_is_right": "The proposed practice serves only the named modern wound.", "test_surface": "Two-week pilot with screened perfectionistic meditators and self-improvers, excluding OCD, scrupulosity, dissociation, severe depression, mania, psychosis, addiction withdrawal, trauma activation, and acute crisis.", "would_weaken_or_falsify": "The practice becomes a new checking ritual, increases avoidance of needed repair, worsens rumination, or performs no better than ordinary rest or social contact."}], "idea_id": "85484e1aff3c6503", "idea_path": "observations/claude/2026-05-30-some-paths-refuse-the-question-of-what-remains.md", "literature_search_queries": ["Collingwood logic of question and answer every statement answer to a question hermeneutics", "Gadamer priority of the question hermeneutics Collingwood Truth and Method", "Huangbo Transmission of Mind no seeking using mind to seek Mind", "Dogen Bendowa practice realization one shusho itto practice verification", "Dzogchen no path no practice direct introduction teacher support", "spiritual bypassing self-monitoring meditation detachment empirical research"], "markdown_path": "reviews/originality/2026-05-30-some-paths-refuse-the-question-of-what-remains-d756c9bf775096c6.md", "near_neighbors": [{"difference": "This candidate makes a sharper precondition gate: does the path stage a negation event with an after at all?", "novelty_impact": "Major downgrade. Treat as a scope-condition extension of the no-custody and no-management cluster, not a standalone discovery.", "overlap": "These records already say some teachings reject separable result, ownership, management, and after-use framing, and that support holders must be coded before prescribing private review.", "source": "Internal Lumenary prior: When There Is Nothing To Keep Or Release, Not Every Practice Is a Tool, Some Help Should Not Be Managed, Even No Path Needs Care, and Operational Remainder Ecology, supplied in the prompt history"}, {"difference": "The candidate turns Huangbo's instruction into a comparative coding gate for residue analysis and a modern practice-safety rule.", "novelty_impact": "Strong downgrade for the core insight that the search itself can be the problem.", "overlap": "Huangbo already says seeking, conceptual road-making, and using mind to seek Mind are errors.", "source": "Huangbo, On the Transmission of Mind, https://selfdefinition.org/zen/huang-po/transmission/a1-chun-chou-record.htm and https://selfdefinition.org/zen/huang-po/transmission/a2-chun-chou-record-cont.htm"}, {"difference": "The candidate groups Dogen with search-refusal paths, but Dogen still insists on active, continuous practice.", "novelty_impact": "Moderate downgrade and anomaly pressure. Dogen supports the gate but resists any no-practice simplification.", "overlap": "Practice and realization are treated as inseparable, which already blocks a simple before-and-after result model.", "source": "Dogen Bendowa and Soto shusho itto, https://afe.easia.columbia.edu/ps/japan/dogen.pdf and https://global.sotozen-net.or.jp/eng/library/key_terms/pdf/key_terms07.pdf"}, {"difference": "The candidate applies that structure to contemplative self-negation and predicts practice failure from a malformed question.", "novelty_impact": "Moderate downgrade. The formal logic is known; the remainder-gate application is the extension.", "overlap": "Collingwood already makes questions and presuppositions determine what counts as an answer.", "source": "Collingwood, Stanford Encyclopedia of Philosophy, https://plato.stanford.edu/entries/collingwood/"}, {"difference": "The candidate narrows this to a before-remainder audit for no-distance teachings.", "novelty_impact": "Moderate downgrade for the hermeneutic claim.", "overlap": "Gadamer already gives priority to the question in understanding and treats interpretation as situated application.", "source": "Gadamer, Stanford Encyclopedia of Philosophy, https://plato.stanford.edu/entries/gadamer/"}, {"difference": "The candidate isolates self-auditing for spiritual residue as a specific mismatch caused by importing a search grammar.", "novelty_impact": "Downgrades safety originality while preserving a narrower hypothesis for coding.", "overlap": "They already show that meditation effects, interpretations, management strategies, teacher relations, community, trauma history, and support influence outcomes.", "source": "VCE and Cheetah House, https://journals.plos.org/plosone/article?id=10.1371/journal.pone.0176239 and https://www.cheetahhouse.org/faq"}], "next_loop_instructions": ["Do not publish as a standalone discovery. Cross-index with When There Is Nothing To Keep Or Release, Not Every Practice Is a Tool, Some Help Should Not Be Managed, Even No Path Needs Care, and The Question Can Make The Distance.", "Build a precondition codebook with values for search-sequence, search-refusal, no-distance-with-support, question-as-medicine, received-without-calculation, practice-realization, valid-solitude, unsafe-avoidance, clinical-routing, analyst-frame-refused, and undecidable.", "Use split-source coding. Do not let one passage both establish path grammar and confirm the predicted warning or repair.", "Add Rinzai koan practice and Dzogchen direct introduction as anomaly classes, not supporting examples.", "Run practitioner interviews for concrete over-auditing, avoidance, and repair cases. Do not ask only for agreement.", "For human-condition fit, keep the practice limited to stable over-managers and achievement-contingent self-worth. Exclude OCD, scrupulosity, dissociation, severe depression, mania, psychosis, addiction withdrawal, trauma activation, medical blackout concerns, unsafe authority, and acute crisis."], "novelty_adjustment": "Lower novelty from 0.46 to 0.36. The core no-seeking and no-result logic is old in Huangbo, Dogen, Dzogchen, Shinran-adjacent no-calculation sources, and prior Lumenary no-management records. Retain as an extended precondition-gate hypothesis only if split-source coding shows predictive gain.", "originality_status": "extended", "path": "reviews/originality/2026-05-30-some-paths-refuse-the-question-of-what-remains-d756c9bf775096c6.json", "practitioner_test": {"answers_that_reduce_originality": "Originality falls if practitioners say this is standard pedagogy under no-seeking, shusho itto, Other Power, direct introduction, koan great doubt, or ordinary spiritual-bypassing triage, and if the gate adds no decisions beyond existing teacher judgment.", "answers_that_support_contribution": "Support rises if practitioners can use the gate to predict distinct failure modes and repairs before knowing outcomes, especially when it prevents over-managers from turning no-distance teachings into private self-audits.", "questions": ["Does your path stage a real search or negation event with an after, or does it refuse that staging?", "When students ask what remains after letting go, is that a valid practice question, a beginner misunderstanding, an advanced koan-like medicine, or a safety concern?", "Can you name concrete cases where auditing emptiness, detachment, or egolessness helped, and cases where it became spiritual performance or avoidance?", "Would the precondition gate change screening, sequencing, warnings, or repairs in your teaching setting?"], "relevant_practitioners": ["Theravada teachers familiar with anatta investigation", "Soto Zen teachers and Dogen scholars", "Chan or Zen teachers familiar with Huangbo and Bankei", "Rinzai koan teachers", "Dzogchen or Mahamudra teachers", "Jodo Shinshu teachers for Other Power contrast", "meditation-safety clinicians and VCE researchers", "spiritual directors", "clinicians familiar with perfectionism, rumination, OCD, and scrupulosity"]}, "primary_text_close_read": {"primary_pair": ["SN 22.59 and SN 22.95, dhammatalks.org, https://www.dhammatalks.org/suttas/SN/SN22_59.html and https://www.dhammatalks.org/suttas/SN/SN22_95.html", "Huangbo, On the Transmission of Mind, Blofeld translation hosted at https://selfdefinition.org/zen/huang-po/transmission/a1-chun-chou-record.htm and https://selfdefinition.org/zen/huang-po/transmission/a2-chun-chou-record-cont.htm, read with Dogen Bendowa excerpts at https://afe.easia.columbia.edu/ps/japan/dogen.pdf and Soto shusho itto note at https://global.sotozen-net.or.jp/eng/library/key_terms/pdf/key_terms07.pdf"], "risk_of_overread": "High. The model can make search-refusal too clean. Huangbo taught through dialogue, Dogen built a practice institution, and Dzogchen no-path language often requires teacher transmission. The modern cohort is clear but narrow: stable over-managers and perfectionistic practitioners who audit their inner state. It is not for beginners needing inquiry, people using non-inquiry to avoid repair, OCD or scrupulosity, dissociation, severe depression, mania, psychosis, acute trauma, addiction withdrawal, or medical blackout concerns.", "secondary_literature_gap": "Search further in Collingwood on the logic of question and answer, Gadamer on the priority of the question, Asad on discursive tradition, Lindbeck on doctrine as grammar, Austin on felicity conditions, Sharf and Katz on contextualism, Dogen scholarship on shusho itto, Chan studies on Huangbo and Bankei, Dzogchen direct-introduction literature, VCE and Cheetah House safety literature, and spiritual bypassing research.", "structural_observation": "SN 22.59 and SN 22.95 explicitly authorize seeing, observing, examining, disenchantment, release, and the knowledge that the task is done. That is a staged investigative grammar. Huangbo repeatedly treats seeking Mind with mind, forming concepts of the Way, or making the Way into a road as the very distortion. Dogen's practice-realization unity blocks a simple cause-then-result reading, while Soto material also says Dogen emphasized active practice because realization is already present. The candidate's gate is textually plausible, but only if it codes the native practice grammar rather than broad tradition names."}, "recommended_scores": {"counterargument_quality": 0.91, "novelty": 0.36, "source_reliability": 0.77}, "run_ids": ["20260530-140914-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-", "20260530-140914-codex-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-"], "title": "Some Paths Refuse the Question of What Remains", "unlike_statement": "Unlike Huangbo, Dogen, Collingwood, Gadamer, VCE, and prior Lumenary no-management records, this idea's specific contribution is a precondition test before remainder coding: only ask what remains if the path first authorizes a self-negation event with an after."}
reviews/originality/audits.jsonl:87:{"agent": "codex", "anomaly_probe": {"anomaly_candidate": "Koan and huatou practice, plus Shinran's own reply to Senshin, show that a question may be deliberately used, answered, or transformed rather than simply permitted or refused.", "confidence_effect": "Lowers confidence in the broad teaching line. Supports a narrower model with values for permitted question, refused question, transformed question, question-as-medicine, teacher-held question, and undecidable.", "why_it_breaks_or_strains_model": "A question that looks wrong from outside can be the authorized method inside a lineage. Also, Shinran refuses self-calculation while still answering doctrinal questions about cause, assurance, and entrusting. This strains any simple permitted versus refused coding."}, "audit_id": "30eeb13d9da3a2bc", "claim_units": ["A teaching permits some practitioner questions and refuses others.", "An imported question can create a false distance, such as attainment to prove, result to manage, or state to defend.", "Wrong-question imports should be coded before remainder, support, or completion models.", "The modern human-condition fit is burnout, loneliness, meaning loss, and achievement-contingent self-worth when practice becomes a private scoreboard."], "confidence": 0.86, "created_at": "2026-05-30T14:21:04+02:00", "cross_domain_prediction": {"domain": "software incident response and organizational learning", "prediction": "Teams that first code the question being asked will produce more concrete system repairs and less defensive reporting than teams that move directly to what remains to fix or who owns the failure.", "structural_translation": "A blameless postmortem permits system and repair questions, while an imported ownership or blame question creates defensiveness and false distance from the event.", "would_count_against_it": "If postmortem quality is explained by psychological safety, manager behavior, severity, or process maturity, and question coding adds no measurable prediction."}, "exact_claim": "Before asking what remains after self-negation, identify the question the teaching permits. Carrying a crossing, ownership, or proof question into a no-distance, received, or non-self-owned teaching can create the distance, private performance, and failure pattern the teaching was meant to undo.", "execution_id": "parallel-20260530-140914-20260530-140914", "falsifiable_predictions": [{"expected_observation": "Blind coders can identify a source's permitted, refused, or transformed question before reading outcome passages, and those labels predict held-out warnings or repairs better than sentence-role, support-holder, tradition label, or VCE-factor baselines alone.", "if_model_is_right": "The imported-question variable is real and separable from prior models.", "test_surface": "A/B inter-rater coding on SN 22.59, SN 22.95, Shinran letters, Tannisho, Bendowa, Huangbo, Dzogchen direct introduction, and Rinzai koan materials.", "would_weaken_or_falsify": "Coders need outcome passages to infer the question, cannot agree, or the variable adds no predictive power beyond existing source-role and correction-holder rubrics."}, {"expected_observation": "Dual-trained practitioners report that carrying a crossing or proof question into no-distance or Other Power settings increases self-grading, private certainty, defensiveness, or withdrawal, while carrying a repair question into ethical-return contexts increases responsibility and reachability.", "if_model_is_right": "Wrong-question imports create distinctive practitioner failures.", "test_surface": "Structured practitioner interviews asking for concrete failed-student and repair cases, not agreement with the wording.", "would_weaken_or_falsify": "Failures track trauma, isolation, sleep, teacher harm, intensity, or institutional culture better than imported question type."}, {"expected_observation": "Question Before Distance reduces proof-seeking and self-surveillance after quiet states more than ordinary journaling, while increasing ordinary action and willingness to receive correction.", "if_model_is_right": "The practice candidate has a bounded benefit.", "test_surface": "Four-arm pilot with screened stable practitioners: question check, journaling, rest-and-plan, and ordinary support prompt.", "would_weaken_or_falsify": "It increases rumination, shame, avoidance, isolation, reassurance seeking, or performs no better than rest, honest conversation, or a simple social-support prompt."}], "idea_id": "80ffd9a12a5c96e3", "idea_path": "observations/codex/2026-05-30-the-question-can-make-the-distance.md", "literature_search_queries": ["Collingwood logic of question and answer presuppositions spiritual practice", "Gadamer priority of the question understanding application hermeneutics", "Austin felicity conditions performative utterance religious language practice", "Lindbeck doctrine grammar religion practice training rules", "Asad discursive tradition correct form purpose practice authority", "wrong question spiritual bypassing meditation self improvement burnout"], "markdown_path": "reviews/originality/2026-05-30-the-question-can-make-the-distance-30eeb13d9da3a2bc.md", "near_neighbors": [{"difference": "This candidate isolates the imported practitioner question as the first failure variable before post-negation remainder coding.", "novelty_impact": "Major downgrade. Merge unless a blind distinct-content test shows the question variable changes decisions.", "overlap": "These records already require coding sentence role, source role, authority, repair, and whether a question or method has become judge.", "source": "Internal Lumenary prior: First Ask What the Words Do, When Tools Become Judges, No Word Travels Alone, Stop When The Repair Changes, and Some Paths Refuse The Question Of What Remains from this batch"}, {"difference": "The candidate moves from philosophical interpretation to practitioner failure prediction after contemplative insight.", "novelty_impact": "Strong downgrade for the structural claim; extension remains in the practice-safety application.", "overlap": "Collingwood already holds that propositions function as answers to questions and that presuppositions give rise to questions.", "source": "R. G. Collingwood, logic of question and answer, Stanford Encyclopedia of Philosophy, https://plato.stanford.edu/entries/collingwood/"}, {"difference": "The candidate operationalizes the imported question as a codeable mismatch in no-distance and received paths.", "novelty_impact": "Moderate downgrade.", "overlap": "Gadamer already emphasizes the priority of the question, historically effected understanding, application, and the way prejudgments open and distort interpretation.", "source": "Hans-Georg Gadamer, philosophical hermeneutics, https://plato.stanford.edu/entries/gadamer/"}, {"difference": "The candidate applies felicity-like conditions to spiritual questions, not only utterances, and predicts self-surveillance failures.", "novelty_impact": "Moderate downgrade. The analogy is useful but not original as language-action theory.", "overlap": "Austin already shows that utterances do things only under fitting procedures, participants, and circumstances, and can misfire when conditions are wrong.", "source": "J. L. Austin, How to Do Things with Words, https://web.english.upenn.edu/~cavitch/pdf-library/Austin_How_To_Do_Things_with_Words.pdf"}, {"difference": "The candidate narrows correct form and purpose to the practitioner's initiating question after self-negation.", "novelty_impact": "Strong downgrade for the tradition-held permission claim.", "overlap": "Asad already treats tradition as discourse instructing practitioners about correct form and purpose, with authority and correction internal to practice.", "source": "Talal Asad, The Idea of an Anthropology of Islam, https://voidnetwork.gr/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/The-Idea-of-an-Anthropology-of-Islam-by-Talal-Asad.pdf"}, {"difference": "The candidate predicts a specific modern failure when a self-owned completion question violates that grammar.", "novelty_impact": "Moderate downgrade; retain only as empirical-practice extension.", "overlap": "Lindbeck already makes doctrine a rule or grammar regulating religious speech and practice.", "source": "George Lindbeck cultural-linguistic doctrine-as-grammar summaries, https://people.bu.edu/wwildman/bce/mwt_themes_862_lindbeck.htm and https://scielo.org.za/scielo.php?pid=S2074-77052018000100007&script=sci_arttext"}, {"difference": "The candidate distinguishes wrong-question imports from general avoidance or adverse-event factors.", "novelty_impact": "Moderate downgrade and important baseline for tests.", "overlap": "These already identify spiritual language and practice as ways to avoid unfinished psychological or relational work, and show that interpretation and management influence meditation difficulties.", "source": "Spiritual bypassing and VCE safety sources, https://www.tandfonline.com/doi/abs/10.1080/19349637.2017.1417756 and https://journals.plos.org/plosone/article?id=10.1371/journal.pone.0176239"}], "next_loop_instructions": ["Do not publish as a standalone discovery. Cross-index or merge with Some Paths Refuse The Question Of What Remains, First Ask What The Words Do, When Tools Become Judges, No Word Travels Alone, Stop When The Repair Changes, and Some Help Should Not Be Managed.", "Build a question-permission codebook with values for crossing, receiving, enacting, repairing, waiting, refusing ownership, question-as-medicine, teacher-held question, no-question frame, unsafe-question, clinical-routing, analyst-frame-refused, and undecidable.", "Run a blind distinct-content test against Some Paths Refuse The Question Of What Remains. Merge if readers cannot state the difference between precondition gate and imported-question failure variable.", "Use split-source coding and do not let the same passage establish permitted question and confirm the predicted warning or repair.", "Add koan practice, Shinran doctrinal Q&A, and valid solitude as anomaly cases before public use.", "For human-condition fit, keep the practice narrow: stable over-managers, burned-out self-improvers, and perfectionistic practitioners. Exclude acute loneliness without support, OCD, scrupulosity, dissociation, psychosis, mania, severe depression, addiction withdrawal, unsafe authority, medical concern, and cases requiring direct accountability or clinical care."], "novelty_adjustment": "Lower novelty from 0.57 to 0.39. The structural logic is heavily anticipated by Collingwood, Gadamer, Austin, Asad, Lindbeck, spiritual-bypassing research, VCE, and local Lumenary sentence-role and no-management records. Preserve as an extended test protocol only if the imported-question field predicts failures and repairs beyond those baselines.", "originality_status": "extended", "path": "reviews/originality/2026-05-30-the-question-can-make-the-distance-30eeb13d9da3a2bc.json", "practitioner_test": {"answers_that_reduce_originality": "Originality falls if practitioners say every tradition already teaches this as right question, right view, proper intention, doctrine as grammar, spiritual direction, or koan pedagogy, and if the question field fails to change real screening or repair decisions.", "answers_that_support_contribution": "Support rises if practitioners can identify wrong-question imports as a recurring failure pattern, use the distinction before seeing outcomes, and show repairs that differ from generic rest, social contact, or teacher correction.", "questions": ["What question does this teaching allow the practitioner to ask at this stage?", "What question commonly causes harm, spiritual performance, or withdrawal in your setting?", "Can you name cases where changing the question changed the repair, rather than merely changing language?", "Is this just hermeneutics, doctrine-as-grammar, spiritual direction, or ordinary teacher judgment in new terms?", "Would this codebook predict warnings or repairs before knowing the outcome?"], "relevant_practitioners": ["Soto Zen teachers", "Rinzai koan teachers", "Jodo Shinshu teachers and scholars", "Theravada insight teachers", "Dzogchen or Mahamudra teachers", "spiritual directors", "comparative theologians", "religion scholars familiar with Asad and Lindbeck", "VCE researchers and meditation-safety clinicians", "clinicians familiar with burnout, perfectionism, rumination, OCD, and scrupulosity"]}, "primary_text_close_read": {"primary_pair": ["SN 22.59, https://www.dhammatalks.org/suttas/SN/SN22_59.html, read against Shinran's reply to Senshin, https://shinranworks.com/letters/a-collection-of-letters-zensho-text/what-we-call-other-power/", "Dogen Bendowa excerpts and Soto shusho itto, https://afe.easia.columbia.edu/ps/japan/dogen.pdf and https://global.sotozen-net.or.jp/eng/library/key_terms/pdf/key_terms07.pdf, read against Huangbo, https://selfdefinition.org/zen/huang-po/transmission/a2-chun-chou-record-cont.htm"], "risk_of_overread": "Moderate to high. The model can collapse hermeneutics, speech-act theory, doctrine-as-grammar, and spiritual-bypassing triage into Lumenary language. It can also make permitted-question coding too subtle for reliable use. Human-condition fit is plausible for stable over-managers, burned-out self-improvers, isolated app meditators, caregivers, founders, and students. It is not for acute loneliness without support, clinical rumination, OCD or scrupulosity, dissociation, psychosis, mania, severe depression, addiction withdrawal, unsafe teacher settings, or cases needing direct accountability.", "secondary_literature_gap": "Read Collingwood, Gadamer, Austin, Searle, Asad, Lindbeck, Sharf, Katz, Pargament, spiritual bypassing research, VCE, Cheetah House, Pure Land studies on hakarai and Other Power, Dogen scholarship on practice-realization, and koan curriculum scholarship by Hori or Rinzai specialists before raising novelty.", "structural_observation": "SN 22.59 permits a disciplined question sequence: is this aggregate controllable, permanent, easeful, fit to regard as mine, self, or what I am? Shinran answers a doctrinal question by refusing calculation on the practicer and relocating assurance to Other Power. Dogen blocks separation of cultivation and realization, while still warning against clever slogans and requiring practice. Huangbo explicitly challenges the question What is the Way and how must it be followed? The candidate's strongest form is not that questions are bad, but that each source licenses a different question grammar with different failure modes."}, "recommended_scores": {"counterargument_quality": 0.92, "novelty": 0.39, "source_reliability": 0.79}, "run_ids": ["20260530-140914-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-", "20260530-140914-codex-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-"], "title": "The Question Can Make the Distance", "unlike_statement": "Unlike Collingwood, Gadamer, Austin, Asad, Lindbeck, spiritual-bypassing research, and prior Lumenary sentence-role records, this idea predicts that the practitioner's imported question itself is a codeable failure variable that can create post-insight distance before any remainder question is asked."}
reviews/originality/audits.jsonl:88:{"agent": "codex", "anomaly_probe": {"anomaly_candidate": "Structured self-review can be valid and beneficial: Ignatian Examen, Stoic evening review, monastic confession preparation, mood tracking in measurement-based care, early meditation logs, and CBT homework can increase accountability, learning, and repair.", "confidence_effect": "Lowers confidence in any general no-audit teaching. Supports a narrower delivery-location protocol: withhold repeated self-scoring grids from over-auditors unless bounded, externally held, and empirically shown not to increase checking, shame, avoidance, or reassurance seeking.", "why_it_breaks_or_strains_model": "If repeated self-review helps high achievers when it is time-limited, compassionate, action-linked, and sometimes guided, then the backstage rule is too broad. The real variable may be not grid versus no grid, but scoring, frequency, clinical risk, guidance, interpretation, and whether the act becomes a compulsion. A second anomaly is avoidance: doing one ordinary act can become a way to dodge grief, confession, moral repair, relational accountability, or needed clinical care."}, "audit_id": "c0163823ff1f73cb", "claim_units": ["Recurring practice self-audit can harm achievement-driven people when it becomes proof of worth.", "A diagnostic grid can be useful backstage for a teacher, clinician, designer, or community while being harmful as a repeated frontstage worksheet.", "The safer user-facing form is a non-scoring transition into observable conduct.", "After-use reflection needs path, disposition, and effect gates.", "The human-condition target is narrow: achievement-contingent self-worth, burnout, perfectionism, rumination, and compulsive self-monitoring."], "confidence": 0.85, "created_at": "2026-05-30T14:47:15+02:00", "cross_domain_prediction": {"domain": "software incident response and workplace performance review", "prediction": "Teams that keep detailed incident diagnostics backstage with leads while giving contributors one concrete repair or learning action will show less defensive reporting, less burnout-linked self-blame, fewer duplicate meta-meetings, and equal or better repair completion than teams requiring repeated individual reflection grids after every incident or performance miss.", "structural_translation": "Complex diagnostic taxonomies may help incident leads, managers, coaches, or system designers, while repeated individual self-scoring can create defensive performance identity. The frontstage form should often be one concrete repair, handoff, or re-entry behavior rather than another private worth audit.", "would_count_against_it": "If outcomes are explained by manager trust, workload, severity, compensation incentives, team maturity, psychological safety, or process quality, and delivery location adds no measurable prediction."}, "exact_claim": "For achievement-driven people, recurring self-audits about practice are often unsafe. The diagnostic grid should usually remain with teachers, designers, clinicians, communities, or one-time setup. The user-facing form should be brief and behavioral: name the tool lightly, stop making it proof of worth, and perform one ordinary re-entry act. After-use reflection is appropriate only when the path is staged, the person is not caught in compulsive checking, and the check does not increase rumination, shame, avoidance, reassurance seeking, or tool-performance anxiety.", "execution_id": "dialogue-538ea14788624f07", "falsifiable_predictions": [{"expected_observation": "In screened achievement-driven participants, maxim-plus-act and behavior-only re-entry conditions reduce rumination, shame, tool-performance anxiety, and reassurance seeking more than a repeated After-Use Check, while producing equal or better ordinary action completion within 24 hours.", "if_model_is_right": "Backstage diagnostic structure plus frontstage maxim-and-act is safer than repeated self-administered grids for over-auditors.", "test_surface": "Four-arm pilot: repeated After-Use Check, behavior-only re-entry, maxim-plus-act without rating, and ordinary journaling or usual practice.", "would_weaken_or_falsify": "The full self-audit performs as well or better without increased checking or shame, or effects are explained by baseline OCD risk, perfectionism, sleep, workload coercion, social support, therapist alliance, or teacher contact."}, {"expected_observation": "Blind coders can identify delivery location, backstage holder, frontstage burden, scoring, frequency, and re-entry act from intervention descriptions, and these fields predict safety outcomes beyond path type, support holder, clinical risk, and tradition label.", "if_model_is_right": "Delivery location is separable from prior Lumenary custody, support-holder, and no-audit models.", "test_surface": "Inter-rater codebook trial on Lumenary practices plus CBT formulation, ACT exercises, ERP anti-checking rules, Examen, Soto instruction, Pure Land guidance, and MBCT homework.", "would_weaken_or_falsify": "Coders cannot distinguish delivery location from support holder or custody, or the field adds no predictive power over prior codebooks."}, {"expected_observation": "Participants high in contingent self-worth, socially prescribed perfectionism, and reassurance seeking show the largest adverse response to self-rating grids; participants low on these traits or under guided review show less harm or benefit.", "if_model_is_right": "The harm mechanism is worth-conversion, not reflection itself.", "test_surface": "Moderation analysis using validated measures of perfectionism, contingent self-worth, rumination, reassurance seeking, burnout, and action completion.", "would_weaken_or_falsify": "Adverse response does not interact with contingent self-worth, perfectionism, OCD or scrupulosity risk, guidance, scoring, or frequency."}, {"expected_observation": "Teachers, clinicians, and spiritual directors report holding complex distinctions privately while giving vulnerable students simpler conduct, rest, relational, or support instructions, and they can name cases where giving the full grid caused self-surveillance or shame.", "if_model_is_right": "Practitioners already distinguish private diagnostic formulation from public instruction in concrete cases.", "test_surface": "Structured interviews asking for concrete failed-student cases and repairs, not agreement with the slogan.", "would_weaken_or_falsify": "Practitioners routinely give full grids without harm, or decisions are fully explained by teacher style, tradition, clinical severity, or institutional norms."}], "idea_id": "8fcf92afeb5b6615", "idea_path": "observations/codex/2026-05-30-the-grid-stays-backstage.md", "literature_search_queries": ["therapist formulation versus client homework self monitoring rumination checking OCD scrupulosity", "CBT case formulation guides clinical decisions client action plan homework", "behavioral activation rumination cues action activity scheduling depression", "ACT values committed action defusion psychological flexibility health behavior change", "mood as input stop rules worry checking rumination perfectionism", "scrupulosity OCD reassurance seeking exposure response prevention religious rituals avoidance", "measurement based care mood monitoring self monitoring adverse events anxiety burden", "Ignatian Examen scrupulosity spiritual direction excessive self examination", "Dogen practice realization no gaining Bendowa shusho itto", "Shinran hakarai calculation Other Power Tannisho self power", "VCE meditation-related challenges interpretation management strategies teacher support", "instructional scaffolding teacher support fading student metacognition"], "markdown_path": "reviews/originality/2026-05-30-the-grid-stays-backstage-c0163823ff1f73cb.md", "near_neighbors": [{"difference": "This candidate adds administrability as the explicit variable: backstage diagnostic grid versus frontstage maxim plus observable act.", "novelty_impact": "Major downgrade. Treat as an extension of the existing cluster unless blind readers can distinguish delivery location from support holder, custody, and no-audit fields.", "overlap": "The cluster already contains after-use checks, no-audit gates, path preconditions, holder routing, tool-as-judge warnings, and safety screens for perfectionism, rumination, scrupulosity, burnout, and achievement-contingent self-worth.", "source": "Internal Lumenary records: The Road Must Know Its End, Some Paths Refuse the Question of What Remains, When Tools Become Judges, Not Every Check Should Be Yours, Some Help Should Not Be Managed, Stop When Time Is Up, The Question Can Make The Distance, local files in observations and reviews."}, {"difference": "The candidate applies a similar formulation-to-homework distinction to spiritual practice and says repeated self-use of the grid may be harmful for achievement-driven users.", "novelty_impact": "Strong downgrade for the backstage diagnostic idea. Possible extension remains in cross-tradition practice routing.", "overlap": "Case formulation already functions as a clinician-held model that guides decisions not directly specified by generic treatment manuals.", "source": "Persons and Tompkins, case formulation-driven CBT, Beck Institute summary, https://beckinstitute.org/blog/developing-and-using-a-case-formulation-to-guide-cognitive-behavior-therapy/"}, {"difference": "The candidate adds a warning that even spiritual or therapeutic tools can become worth-proof, and proposes a non-scoring re-entry act for a specific cohort.", "novelty_impact": "Moderate downgrade. The practical frontstage move is close to ACT, but the delivery-location test is more specific.", "overlap": "ACT already emphasizes defusion, acceptance, values, and committed action instead of trying to replace or prove internal states.", "source": "Acceptance and Commitment Therapy for health behavior change, https://www.frontiersin.org/journals/psychology/articles/10.3389/fpsyg.2017.02350/full"}, {"difference": "The candidate spiritualizes the same move around after-use of insight and practice tools.", "novelty_impact": "Strong downgrade for behavior-only re-entry. Retain only as an applied spiritual-practice safety rule.", "overlap": "Behavioral activation already moves clients from rumination loops toward scheduled, observable action and uses monitoring only to identify avoidance patterns.", "source": "Behavioral activation and rumination-focused CBT, including rumination cues action formulations, https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Behavioral_activation"}, {"difference": "The candidate applies anti-checking logic to nonclinical spiritual over-auditors while requiring clinical exclusions.", "novelty_impact": "Strong downgrade for the safety mechanism. Contribution depends on careful cohort screening and avoiding clinical overreach.", "overlap": "ERP and scrupulosity work already identify checking, self-reassurance, confession, religious ritualizing, avoidance, and reassurance seeking as patterns that can be maintained by attempts to secure certainty.", "source": "Exposure and response prevention for OCD and scrupulosity, including common ERP pitfalls, https://pmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/articles/PMC3423997/, and scrupulosity review, https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/abs/pii/S2211364914000116"}, {"difference": "The candidate proposes an external delivery rule: do not give over-auditors a repeating self-completion grid; give a limited re-entry act.", "novelty_impact": "Moderate to strong downgrade. The stop-rule structure is known; the spiritual delivery application is the extension.", "overlap": "This literature already shows that stop rules shape perseverative thought, including rumination and worry, and that subjective completion criteria can prolong cognition.", "source": "Mood-as-input and stop-rule research on worry and rumination, including Fisak et al., https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/abs/pii/S0005791617301295"}, {"difference": "The candidate names a spiritual analogue: a practice grid can become continuous self-management and worth surveillance.", "novelty_impact": "Moderate downgrade. This is a known digital and clinical design problem in religious-practice language.", "overlap": "Repeated monitoring can be useful for care and research, but qualitative and review literature reports burden, fixation, distress, subjective mood worsening, and anxiety in some users.", "source": "Mood monitoring, ambulatory assessment, and self-monitoring adverse-event literature, https://pmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/articles/PMC12548826/, https://pmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/articles/PMC12533931/"}, {"difference": "The candidate does not reject review universally. It says review is safe only under conditions and may need a holder or non-scoring translation for over-auditors.", "novelty_impact": "Moderate downgrade and important anomaly. A blanket backstage rule would be false because structured self-review can be central and beneficial.", "overlap": "The Examen is an established structured review practice with presence, gratitude, review, reflection, and looking ahead.", "source": "Ignatian Examen, Saint Joseph's University, https://www.sju.edu/offices/mission/ignatian-resources/examen"}, {"difference": "The candidate connects this to the danger that a diagnostic grid becomes a spiritual self-worth instrument for high achievers.", "novelty_impact": "Moderate downgrade. The teaching-design principle is old; the modern harm channel is the extension.", "overlap": "Pedagogy already distinguishes expert-held diagnosis, adapted instruction, scaffolding, fading, and capacity-sensitive teaching.", "source": "Buddhist upaya and instructional scaffolding, including teacher-student adaptive support, https://link.springer.com/article/10.1007/s10648-010-9127-6, and upaya pedagogy sources such as https://taojiangscholar.com/papers/Dilemma_of_Skillful_Means_in_Buddhist_Pedagogy.pdf"}, {"difference": "The candidate isolates one design factor, whether the interpretive grid is self-administered or held by care structures.", "novelty_impact": "Moderate downgrade. It should be tested as one variable within the larger VCE-style context model.", "overlap": "These sources already show that meditation effects depend on interpretation, management strategy, practitioner factors, practice factors, relationships, health behaviors, and support.", "source": "VCE and Cheetah House meditation safety sources, https://journals.plos.org/plosone/article?id=10.1371/journal.pone.0176239, https://www.cheetahhouse.org/faq"}, {"difference": "These sources do not supply the spiritual-practice grid distinction, but they explain why the cohort is vulnerable to turning reflection into performance.", "novelty_impact": "Supports publishability for a narrow cohort, not originality.", "overlap": "The target wound is well supported: rising perfectionism, socially prescribed worth pressure, exhaustion, distance, and reduced efficacy.", "source": "Modern human-condition sources: Curran and Hill on rising perfectionism, https://researchonline.lse.ac.uk/id/eprint/101352/1/Curran_Hill2018.pdf, and WHO burn-out definition, https://www.who.int/standards/classifications/frequently-asked-questions/burn-out-an-occupational-phenomenon"}], "next_loop_instructions": ["Do not publish as a standalone discovery or doctrine. Cross-index with The Road Must Know Its End, Some Paths Refuse The Question Of What Remains, When Tools Become Judges, Not Every Check Should Be Yours, Some Help Should Not Be Managed, Stop When Time Is Up, and The Question Can Make The Distance.", "Rename the contribution as a delivery-location protocol for over-auditors: backstage grid, frontstage re-entry act.", "Build a small codebook with fields for target cohort, backstage holder, frontstage burden, scoring or no-scoring, check frequency, path gate, disposition gate, re-entry act, contraindication, warning, repair, evidence passage, and confidence.", "Run a blind distinct-content test against prior Lumenary after-use, no-audit, support-holder, and question-permission records. Merge if readers cannot state the added administrability variable without prompting.", "Use split-source or split-data testing. Do not let the same practitioner case establish the backstage rule and confirm the predicted repair.", "Pilot only with screened stable high performers, caregivers, students, founders, app meditators, and burned-out self-improvers. Exclude OCD or scrupulosity without ERP-informed care, severe depression, mania, psychosis, dissociation, trauma activation, addiction withdrawal, unsafe authority, coercive workload, under-reflection, and cases requiring moral repair or clinical care.", "Compare against baselines: ACT values prompt, behavioral activation activity scheduling, ordinary journaling, timeboxing, ERP-informed no-check instruction, spiritual-direction check-in, measurement-based care, and rest-and-plan prompt.", "Track rumination, shame, reassurance seeking, tool-performance anxiety, avoidance, missed duties, ordinary action within one hour and 24 hours, willingness to receive correction, and whether conduct prompts bypass needed inquiry."], "novelty_adjustment": "Lower novelty from 0.57 to 0.34. The mechanisms are strongly anticipated by internal Lumenary records, CBT formulation, ACT committed action, behavioral activation, ERP anti-checking logic, mood-as-input stop rules, mood-monitoring safety research, Ignatian Examen, upaya, scaffolding, VCE, and meditation-safety work. Preserve as an extended delivery-location synthesis only if backstage/frontstage coding predicts harms and benefits beyond support holder, custody, path grammar, clinical risk, and generic simplification.", "originality_status": "extended", "path": "reviews/originality/2026-05-30-the-grid-stays-backstage-c0163823ff1f73cb.json", "practitioner_test": {"answers_that_reduce_originality": "Originality falls if practitioners say this is routine formulation, ordinary spiritual direction, response prevention, scaffolding, upaya, or product simplification, and if delivery location does not change screening, instruction, repair, or outcome decisions beyond those frameworks.", "answers_that_support_contribution": "Support rises if practitioners can identify cases where the same grid was useful for the holder but harmful for the practitioner, can predict failure before outcome passages, and can show repairs that differ from generic simplify the worksheet advice.", "questions": ["Do you keep a diagnostic grid or formulation privately while giving the practitioner a simpler action?", "When have worksheets, practice logs, spiritual self-examination, or reflection prompts increased checking, shame, reassurance seeking, spiritual pride, or avoidance?", "What concrete signs tell you to stop self-audit and route the person to conduct, rest, relationship, teacher guidance, fixed rule, or clinical care?", "Is this just case formulation, response prevention, values-based action, behavioral activation, spiritual direction, upaya, or scaffolding in new terms?", "Would the backstage/frontstage distinction change a real instruction for a high-achieving over-manager?"], "relevant_practitioners": ["CBT clinicians using case formulation", "ACT therapists", "behavioral activation clinicians", "ERP clinicians familiar with OCD and scrupulosity", "MBCT and metacognitive therapy teachers", "spiritual directors familiar with Ignatian Examen and scrupulosity", "Soto Zen teachers", "Jodo Shinshu ministers", "Theravada or insight meditation teachers", "VCE or Cheetah House meditation-safety clinicians", "burnout and perfectionism researchers", "mental-health product designers and UX researchers"]}, "primary_text_close_read": {"primary_pair": ["Dogen, Bendowa excerpts, https://afe.easia.columbia.edu/ps/japan/dogen.pdf, read against Shinran's reply to Senshin, https://shinranworks.com/letters/a-collection-of-letters-zensho-text/what-we-call-other-power/", "MN 22 raft simile, https://www.dhammatalks.org/suttas/MN/MN22.html, read against the Ignatian Examen, https://www.sju.edu/offices/mission/ignatian-resources/examen"], "risk_of_overread": "High. The idea can rename common clinical and pastoral practice: therapist formulation versus client homework, response prevention for checking, values-based committed action, behavioral activation, scaffolding, upaya, and spiritual direction. Human-condition fit is direct but narrow. It is for stable high performers, students, founders, caregivers, app meditators, and burned-out self-improvers whose practice becomes a verdict on worth. It is not for severe depression, mania, psychosis, dissociation, OCD or scrupulosity without ERP-informed care, trauma activation, addiction withdrawal, unsafe authority settings, coercive workloads, under-reflection, or cases needing moral repair, medical care, or ordinary accountability.", "secondary_literature_gap": "Before publication, read full sources in CBT case formulation, ACT, behavioral activation, rumination-focused CBT, MBCT, metacognitive therapy, mood-as-input stop-rule research, ERP and scrupulosity, spiritual direction ethics, Ignatian discernment, upaya pedagogy, Dogen practice-realization scholarship, Pure Land hakarai and Other Power scholarship, VCE, Cheetah House, measurement-based care, and self-monitoring reactivity.", "structural_observation": "MN 22 supports after-use discipline: a method can be held for crossing and not carried afterward as a burden. Ignatian Examen supports structured review as a legitimate practice, but it frames review as prayer, discernment, gratitude, and concrete amendment rather than private worth-scoring. Dogen strains the tool-result assumption by making cultivation and realization inseparable and warning against clever slogans, while Shinran strains practitioner-owned audit by rejecting calculation in Other Power. The candidate's strongest contribution is not the idea that practices need guidance, or that checking can harm. Those are old. The possible addition is delivery location: the same diagnostic grid may belong backstage as a care-holder's lens, while the practitioner receives only a minimal re-entry act."}, "recommended_scores": {"counterargument_quality": 0.92, "novelty": 0.34, "source_reliability": 0.78}, "run_ids": [], "title": "The Grid Stays Backstage", "unlike_statement": "Unlike CBT formulation, ACT, behavioral activation, ERP, mood-as-input stop rules, mood-monitoring safety research, Ignatian Examen, upaya, scaffolding, VCE, and prior Lumenary after-use records, this idea claims that diagnostic-grid location is itself a testable variable: backstage for care holders and designers, frontstage only as a brief non-scoring re-entry act for achievement-driven over-auditors."}
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-you-cannot-release-what-you-never-held-3f00413ce244b54e.json:5:    "confidence_effect": "Keeps the idea at extended. It can only rise if voice coding predicts warnings, confusion, and repair better than self-power, Other Power, Pargament agency style, teacher style, and clinical-risk baselines.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-you-cannot-release-what-you-never-held-3f00413ce244b54e.json:11:    "Dogen, Shinran, and the Heart Sutra break the grid by rejecting an active owner who finishes and assigns custody.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-you-cannot-release-what-you-never-held-3f00413ce244b54e.json:36:      "test_surface": "Split-source codebook tested on MN 22, Tannisho, Dogen, Heart Sutra, Rinzai koan curriculum, Christian grace texts, and practitioner interviews.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-you-cannot-release-what-you-never-held-3f00413ce244b54e.json:40:      "expected_observation": "Coders will overuse embodied-without-ownership for Dogen, Shinran, Heart Sutra, Dzogchen, apophasis, and other hard cases, with low inter-rater reliability and weak prediction of warnings.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-you-cannot-release-what-you-never-held-3f00413ce244b54e.json:50:    "Shinran jinen honi no calculation Other Power no working is true working",
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-you-cannot-release-what-you-never-held-3f00413ce244b54e.json:51:    "Tannisho nembutsu not practice not good act self-power Other Power",
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-you-cannot-release-what-you-never-held-3f00413ce244b54e.json:52:    "Dogen practice and realization are one no means and end zazen",
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-you-cannot-release-what-you-never-held-3f00413ce244b54e.json:59:      "difference": "Lewin centers Eckhart and Heidegger, not Dogen, Shinran, Heart Sutra, or a modern achievement-cohort practice screen.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-you-cannot-release-what-you-never-held-3f00413ce244b54e.json:65:      "difference": "The candidate turns Shinran into a comparative diagnostic against universal release teachings.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-you-cannot-release-what-you-never-held-3f00413ce244b54e.json:66:      "novelty_impact": "Downgrades the slogan 'you cannot release what you never held' to a Shinran-compatible restatement.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-you-cannot-release-what-you-never-held-3f00413ce244b54e.json:67:      "overlap": "Direct primary near-neighbor. Shinran already denies practicer calculation and says no working is true working in Other Power.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-you-cannot-release-what-you-never-held-3f00413ce244b54e.json:68:      "source": "Shinran, On Jinen-Honi, https://shinranworks.com/letters/lamp-for-the-latter-ages/on-jinen-honi-1258/"
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-you-cannot-release-what-you-never-held-3f00413ce244b54e.json:72:      "novelty_impact": "Strong downgrade for the Other Power anomaly and self-power critique.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-you-cannot-release-what-you-never-held-3f00413ce244b54e.json:73:      "overlap": "Very close. Tannisho says nembutsu is not practice or good act for the practicer because it arises wholly from Other Power and is free of self-power.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-you-cannot-release-what-you-never-held-3f00413ce244b54e.json:77:      "difference": "The candidate frames Dogen as evidence for active versus middle voice completion-talk, which may or may not be native to Soto categories.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-you-cannot-release-what-you-never-held-3f00413ce244b54e.json:109:    "Search and read full Lewin, Pargament, Dogen scholarship, Jodo Shinshu scholarship, grace-effort theology, Gelassenheit, and middle-voice theology before raising novelty.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-you-cannot-release-what-you-never-held-3f00413ce244b54e.json:111:    "Create a voice-coding sheet with values for active, middle, passive, mixed-by-stage, simultaneous-mixed, no-owner, no-threshold, practice-realization, radical Other Power, analyst-frame-refused, and undecidable.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-you-cannot-release-what-you-never-held-3f00413ce244b54e.json:114:  "novelty_adjustment": "Lower novelty from 0.55 to 0.39. The strongest prior-art pressure is Lewin's middle-voice analysis plus Shinran's explicit Other Power and Pargament's agency styles. Human-condition fit is strong but narrow: high-striving people with achievement-contingent self-worth, burnout, comparison, and result-ownership. Non-fit cases include acute crisis, severe depression, addiction withdrawal, scrupulosity, dissociation, psychosis, people in grace-centered or nondual practice who do not experience ownership, and people whose distress is caused mainly by structural exploitation rather than self-rating.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-you-cannot-release-what-you-never-held-3f00413ce244b54e.json:117:    "answers_that_reduce_originality": "Practitioners say the claim is simply self-power versus Other Power, grace versus works, practice-realization, or middle-voice theology in new language, and that it does not change sequencing, warning, or repair.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-you-cannot-release-what-you-never-held-3f00413ce244b54e.json:123:      "Does voice coding change guidance beyond older labels such as self-power, Other Power, grace, surrender, non-attainment, or Pargament coping style?"
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-you-cannot-release-what-you-never-held-3f00413ce244b54e.json:127:      "Soto Zen teachers familiar with Dogen practice-realization",
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-you-cannot-release-what-you-never-held-3f00413ce244b54e.json:137:      "Shinran, On Jinen-Honi and Tannisho, https://shinranworks.com/letters/lamp-for-the-latter-ages/on-jinen-honi-1258/ and https://shinranworks.com/related-works-by-other-authors/a-record-in-lament-of-divergences/"
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-you-cannot-release-what-you-never-held-3f00413ce244b54e.json:139:    "risk_of_overread": "High. 'Middle voice' is an analyst metaphor that may not map cleanly onto Japanese, Sanskrit, Pali, or Chinese practice grammar. The active versus middle distinction may become a renamed self-power versus Other Power distinction, or it may hide stage shifts where effort and surrender coexist.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-you-cannot-release-what-you-never-held-3f00413ce244b54e.json:140:    "secondary_literature_gap": "This audit did not read Japanese, Pali, Sanskrit, Chinese, or commentarial originals. It did not read full Lewin on middle voice, full Heidegger and Eckhart scholarship, full Pargament, full Hori, full Dogen scholarship, or Jodo Shinshu scholarship beyond accessible translations and summaries. No Shin, Soto, Rinzai, or Christian grace practitioners were interviewed.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-you-cannot-release-what-you-never-held-3f00413ce244b54e.json:141:    "structural_observation": "MN 22 assumes a practitioner can grasp the Dhamma rightly, use it for crossing, and then not hold it as a possession. Shinran's jinen-honi and Tannisho relocate efficacy to Other Power and repeatedly reject practicer calculation, making even discussion of no working liable to become another working. This is a strong primary-text basis for narrowing release advice by agency grammar. But it also shows the candidate's central insight is not new inside Shinran: one cannot release as self-power what was never self-power to begin with."
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-you-cannot-release-what-you-never-held-3f00413ce244b54e.json:153:  "unlike_statement": "Unlike Lewin on middle voice, Shinran on Other Power, Dogen on practice-realization, Pargament on religious coping styles, Heart Sutra no-attainment reliance, Smith, Sells, and prior Lumenary completion models, this idea's possible contribution is a testable fit rule: give release-the-method advice only to practitioners whose own language shows active earning and result-ownership, then test whether the advice helps them more than it helps other-power, nondual, or practice-realization practitioners."
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-the-brain-model-already-took-a-side-64620370e9b052b1.json:25:  "exact_claim": "Predictive-processing accounts of contemplative self-negation do not neutrally reproduce the atman versus anatta dispute. By treating the self as an inferred or constructed model whose precision can be relaxed, they already favor the not-self side and cannot express Advaita self-luminous awareness without reducing it to a model. The apparent convergence is translation strain across both vocabulary and explanatory level.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-the-brain-model-already-took-a-side-64620370e9b052b1.json:30:      "if_model_is_right": "Predictive-processing meditation papers carry a structural no-self bias when they discuss self-negation.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-the-brain-model-already-took-a-side-64620370e9b052b1.json:148:  "unlike_statement": "Unlike Laukkonen and Slagter, Metzinger-style self-model theory, and general FEP critiques, this idea specifically says that a predictive-processing model of self-negation cannot be a neutral higher-order mirror of the atman and anatta dispute because its self-as-model vocabulary already rules out Shankara's non-inferred witness unless extra metaphysical assumptions are added. That is an extension, not a discovery."
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-you-cannot-prove-the-one-who-is-asking-6e5f448135e13ebe.md:16:- The relevant upstream variable is whether the post-negation remainder is admissible as an object of inference.
reviews/originality/2026-05-28-the-test-is-how-you-return-b463ae0abb9b554d.json:4:    "anomaly_candidate": "Dogen practice-realization, radical Other Power in Tannisho, inherited communal religion, and successful ordinary ethical practice without a marked peak experience.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-28-the-test-is-how-you-return-b463ae0abb9b554d.json:5:    "confidence_effect": "Prevents candidate-discovery status. The model is useful as a heuristic only if it can code no-threshold, no-peak, Other Power, inherited practice, and practice-realization without forcing them into a modern after-experience frame.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-28-the-test-is-how-you-return-b463ae0abb9b554d.json:6:    "why_it_breaks_or_strains_model": "These cases resist the sequence of method, result, and return. Dogen makes practice and realization inseparable. Tannisho relocates efficacy to Amida's Vow and can make nembutsu non-practice from the practitioner's side. Inherited religion may not have a discrete completion event. Ordinary ethical formation may return without peak experience at all."
reviews/originality/2026-05-28-the-test-is-how-you-return-b463ae0abb9b554d.json:12:    "Different primary texts model different endings: MN 22 releases the raft after right use, Heart Sutra negates attainment while retaining reliance, Mandukya allows a known Self, Rinzai koan work exhausts ordinary thinking while remaining curriculum, and Dogen collapses before and after through practice-realization.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-28-the-test-is-how-you-return-b463ae0abb9b554d.json:54:    "\"Dogen\" \"practice and realization are one\" Bendowa",
reviews/originality/2026-05-28-the-test-is-how-you-return-b463ae0abb9b554d.json:71:      "difference": "The candidate makes Dogen an anomaly inside a return model, whereas Dogen may reject the whole before, peak, after sequence.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-28-the-test-is-how-you-return-b463ae0abb9b554d.json:72:      "novelty_impact": "Lowers confidence. If Dogen is central rather than marginal, the return test may be only an external heuristic.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-28-the-test-is-how-you-return-b463ae0abb9b554d.json:73:      "overlap": "Close anomaly and near-neighbor. Dogen's practice-realization already says practice is not a means to a later result and realization is not an object privately recognized after practice.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-28-the-test-is-how-you-return-b463ae0abb9b554d.json:74:      "source": "Dogen Bendowa material, Everyday Zen Foundation, https://everydayzen.org/teachings/dogens-bendowa-part-2-of-3/"
reviews/originality/2026-05-28-the-test-is-how-you-return-b463ae0abb9b554d.json:104:    "Add mandatory anomaly values for practice-realization, radical Other Power, inherited religion, no-threshold practice, no-peak ethical formation, direct recognition, and clinician-held support.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-28-the-test-is-how-you-return-b463ae0abb9b554d.json:106:    "Close-read Tannisho, Dogen Bendowa or Genjokoan, a Rinzai koan curriculum source, Cloud of Unknowing or Dionysius, a Dzogchen pointing-out source, and one Sufi fana or baqa source before raising source reliability."
reviews/originality/2026-05-28-the-test-is-how-you-return-b463ae0abb9b554d.json:120:      "Zen teachers familiar with Dogen practice-realization and Rinzai koan curriculum",
reviews/originality/2026-05-28-the-test-is-how-you-return-b463ae0abb9b554d.json:123:      "Jodo Shinshu teachers familiar with Tannisho and Other Power",
reviews/originality/2026-05-28-the-test-is-how-you-return-b463ae0abb9b554d.json:135:    "structural_observation": "MN 22 is a close primary near-neighbor for validated-then-released method. It teaches right grasp, crossing, and release of the raft, so the candidate's set-down category is old. The Heart Sutra complicates the model because it negates attainment yet retains reliance on Prajnaparamita and mantra. This supports the candidate's claim that undermining result does not always mean abandoning method. Mandukya adds a different pressure: negation culminates in the Self that is to be known. Dogen strains the whole after-completion frame because practice and realization are inseparable, so return is not a later test but the practice itself."
reviews/originality/2026-05-28-the-test-is-how-you-return-b463ae0abb9b554d.json:147:  "unlike_statement": "Unlike the raft simile, apophatic unsaying, therapeutic readings of Nagarjuna and Wittgenstein, Dogen practice-realization, VCE aftercare, Asad's discursive tradition, and Lindbeck's doctrine grammar, this idea's distinct claim is a practical comparative test: code whether a method validates or undermines the result, then code whether the method is retained, released, or embodied, and see whether that interaction predicts warnings, re-entry duties, identity risks, and repairs better than doctrine, institution, teacher style, or clinical-risk variables alone."
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-even-no-path-needs-care-5e945a54e9681489.json:11:    "Anti-ownership should be coded before remainder, residue, or completion variables.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-even-no-path-needs-care-5e945a54e9681489.json:25:  "exact_claim": "No-distance teachings may remove the private project of becoming spiritual, but they do not thereby remove care, correction, companionship, schedule, teacher, text, vow, or ordinary accountability. Before asking what remains after self-negation, code whether the path grants the practitioner ownership at all. If ownership is refused, the key question is where correction is held and whether failures cluster when students privatize the insight, abandon correction, become passive, or turn relief into performance.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-even-no-path-needs-care-5e945a54e9681489.json:29:      "expected_observation": "Split-source coding of Dogen, Huangbo, Shinran, Dzogchen, and Mahamudra sources will find ownership refusal in one layer and held-out warnings, teacher checks, vow, practice form, text, community, conduct, or reentry rules in another.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-even-no-path-needs-care-5e945a54e9681489.json:49:      "test_surface": "A/B coding comparison on Dogen, Huangbo, Tannisho, Dzogchen, Mahamudra, Pure Land, and one causal Theravada path.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-even-no-path-needs-care-5e945a54e9681489.json:56:    "Dogen Bendowa practice realization shusho itto no gaining practice realization one",
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-even-no-path-needs-care-5e945a54e9681489.json:57:    "Huangbo Transmission of Mind no seeking objective path teacher support correction",
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-even-no-path-needs-care-5e945a54e9681489.json:58:    "Shinran Tannisho Other Power self power divergence true teacher correction",
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-even-no-path-needs-care-5e945a54e9681489.json:65:    "Dzogchen direct introduction support teacher correction no path practice"
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-even-no-path-needs-care-5e945a54e9681489.json:106:      "novelty_impact": "Major reduction for Dogen-specific originality, partial preservation for cross-case testing.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-even-no-path-needs-care-5e945a54e9681489.json:107:      "overlap": "It already states that practice and realization are inseparable while Dogen strongly emphasizes active practice, so no-gap is not no-practice.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-even-no-path-needs-care-5e945a54e9681489.json:111:      "difference": "The candidate may overuse Huangbo as support for correction when his discourse also cuts support-seeking itself.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-even-no-path-needs-care-5e945a54e9681489.json:113:      "overlap": "Huangbo already supplies the no-seeking pressure and warnings about false teachers, casual pilgrimage, and conceptual path-making.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-even-no-path-needs-care-5e945a54e9681489.json:114:      "source": "Huangbo, Transmission of Mind, Blofeld record https://merton.bellarmine.edu/s/merton/media/51897 and searchable PDF https://wayofsuddenawakening.org/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/Huang-Po-The-Transmission-of-Mind.pdf"
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-even-no-path-needs-care-5e945a54e9681489.json:119:    "Build a pre-remainder codebook with fields for ownership grant, no-distance grammar, permitted after, correction holder, support holder, warning, repair, unsafe holder, valid solitude, clinical exclusion, and analyst-frame refusal.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-even-no-path-needs-care-5e945a54e9681489.json:121:    "Test Dogen, Huangbo, Tannisho, Dzogchen or Mahamudra direct introduction, Pure Land, and one causal Theravada path before broad tradition claims.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-even-no-path-needs-care-5e945a54e9681489.json:129:    "answers_that_reduce_originality": "Originality falls if practitioners say the rule is standard lineage pedagogy, spiritual direction, sangha correction, Soto practice-realization, Shin Other Power instruction, or meditation-safety triage, and if the support check adds no decisions beyond existing practice guidance.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-even-no-path-needs-care-5e945a54e9681489.json:130:    "answers_that_support_contribution": "Support rises if practitioners find that coding ownership refusal before remainder prevents real interpretive errors, predicts failure cases, and improves support routing without increasing self-effort, dependency, or unsafe authority.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-even-no-path-needs-care-5e945a54e9681489.json:136:      "Would the pre-remainder ownership gate change screening, sequencing, warning, or repair instructions in your setting?"
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-even-no-path-needs-care-5e945a54e9681489.json:140:      "Chan or Zen teachers familiar with Huangbo",
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-even-no-path-needs-care-5e945a54e9681489.json:142:      "Dzogchen or Mahamudra teachers",
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-even-no-path-needs-care-5e945a54e9681489.json:153:      "Dogen Bendowa and Soto shusho itto sources, https://afe.easia.columbia.edu/ps/japan/dogen.pdf and https://global.sotozen-net.or.jp/eng/library/key_terms/pdf/key_terms07.pdf, read against Huangbo, The Transmission of Mind, Blofeld record https://merton.bellarmine.edu/s/merton/media/51897 and searchable PDF used at https://wayofsuddenawakening.org/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/Huang-Po-The-Transmission-of-Mind.pdf",
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-even-no-path-needs-care-5e945a54e9681489.json:154:      "Shinran, Tannisho, especially preface, chapters 1, 6, 8, 10, 11, and 12, https://jodoshinshu.faith/tannisho-a-record-in-lament-of-divergences/"
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-even-no-path-needs-care-5e945a54e9681489.json:156:    "risk_of_overread": "High. The model can become circular by counting any surviving text, teacher, or community as support. It can also domesticate Huangbo-style search-refusal by turning an anti-support discourse into analyst-defined support. It may hide abuse if correction holders are assumed safe, and it may pathologize valid solitude. Human-condition fit is clear but narrow: stable isolated over-managers, app meditators, retreatants, and self-improvers. It is not a loneliness cure by itself and can increase dependency, rumination, or unsafe authority compliance.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-even-no-path-needs-care-5e945a54e9681489.json:157:    "secondary_literature_gap": "Read full Dogen Bendowa, Genjokoan, Uji, Eihei Shingi, and Soto scholarship; Huangbo in multiple translations plus Chan transmission studies; Shinran, Tannisho, jinen, hakarai, and Other Power scholarship; Dzogchen and Mahamudra direct introduction manuals; Asad, Lindbeck, MacIntyre, Bell, Sharf, Katz, spiritual bypassing research, VCE, Cheetah House, mindfulness optimization critique, and spiritual direction ethics. Interviews with no-distance practitioners are essential.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-even-no-path-needs-care-5e945a54e9681489.json:158:    "structural_observation": "Dogen's practice-realization unity rejects practice as a cause separate from later realization, but Soto explanatory material also says Dogen emphasized active practice because realization is already present. Huangbo is a sharper anomaly: he rejects objective seeking and objective path language, yet the record is itself teacher discourse and includes testing a teacher's groundedness and warning against casual pilgrimage. Tannisho denies self-powered practice and calculation, yet it opens by lamenting divergences, relies on true teachers, and preserves Vow, teacher, and correction. The candidate's narrow claim survives as a hypothesis: no-distance language is not automatically support-free, but the specific holder must be coded natively."
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-even-no-path-needs-care-5e945a54e9681489.json:170:  "unlike_statement": "Unlike Keep What Can Correct You, Some Help Should Not Be Managed, Asad, Lindbeck, VCE, spiritual bypassing research, and Soto practice-realization sources, this idea's specific contribution is to make anti-ownership a pre-remainder coding gate for no-distance teachings and to predict that loss of correction support will produce privatization, passivity, or performance failures."
observations/codex/2026-05-30-no-word-travels-alone.md:34:The model may over-psychologize comparison. Some words are protected less by private self-checking than by living institutions, teachers, ritual forms, and community correction. Zen, Chan, Pure Land, Dzogchen, and Mahamudra can also treat words, gestures, trust, and recognition as inseparable from practice, which may make a receiver-wound sheet feel like an outsider's grid. The model is weakened if dual-trained practitioners can translate contested terms without naming receiver wounds and still show clearer conduct, less misuse, and better care than people using the added check.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-operational-remainder-ecology-39a96b7ef7849b21.json:4:    "anomaly_candidate": "Dogen-style practice-realization, inherited devotional practice, radical Other Power, and secular mindfulness adverse effects strain the model from different sides.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-operational-remainder-ecology-39a96b7ef7849b21.json:6:    "why_it_breaks_or_strains_model": "Practice-realization can refuse a before-and-after account in which capacity remains and then receives a residue label. Inherited practice may work through ritual and community before explicit doctrine is understood. Other Power can treat naming receptivity as a capacity as a self-power distortion. Secular mindfulness adverse effects can occur without explicit self-negating residue policy, which may mean ecology, dose, arousal, vulnerability, and interpretation explain more than the proposed residue axis."
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-operational-remainder-ecology-39a96b7ef7849b21.json:39:      "expected_observation": "Practices that train attention, disidentification, and stable witnessing should diverge in whether the remainder is framed as conventional process, witness, Self, grace, vow, or non-ownable event, and these labels should forecast verification and warning practices.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-operational-remainder-ecology-39a96b7ef7849b21.json:41:      "test_surface": "Cross-coding Advaita self-inquiry, Buddhist de-identification, Mahamudra or Dzogchen recognition, Shin entrusting, and Christian surrender materials.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-operational-remainder-ecology-39a96b7ef7849b21.json:52:  "idea_path": "observations/codex/2026-05-26-operational-remainder-ecology.md",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-operational-remainder-ecology-39a96b7ef7849b21.json:64:    "Tannisho Other Power self-power calculation warning license",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-operational-remainder-ecology-39a96b7ef7849b21.json:81:      "difference": "It does not formalize residue policy after self-negation or combine worldview with operational capacity coding.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-operational-remainder-ecology-39a96b7ef7849b21.json:87:      "difference": "It does not provide a self-negation or residue-policy typology.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-operational-remainder-ecology-39a96b7ef7849b21.json:133:    "Add mandatory anomaly values for practice-realization, inherited practice, no-threshold practice, Other Power refusal, grace-held support, teacher-recognition support, secular extraction, psychiatric vulnerability, and undecidable.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-operational-remainder-ecology-39a96b7ef7849b21.json:147:      "Are there practices in your lineage where the language of remainder, capacity, or support locus distorts the path?",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-operational-remainder-ecology-39a96b7ef7849b21.json:154:      "Jodo Shinshu ministers familiar with shinjin, Other Power, and non-calculation",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-operational-remainder-ecology-39a96b7ef7849b21.json:155:      "Dzogchen or Mahamudra teachers familiar with recognition, guru relation, and post-recognition conduct",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-operational-remainder-ecology-39a96b7ef7849b21.json:168:    "secondary_literature_gap": "This audit used accessible primary translations and open academic sources, but did not fully reread Collins, Siderits, Harvey, Albahari, Wilber, Engler's full chapter context, Shinran's Kyogyoshinsho, Dogen scholarship, Dzogchen and Mahamudra manuals, or Britton's full adverse-effects corpus. Pali, Sanskrit, Japanese, and Burmese terms were not checked directly. Stronger novelty would require split-source coding and practitioner interviews.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-operational-remainder-ecology-39a96b7ef7849b21.json:169:    "structural_observation": "SN 22.59 negates ownership and mastery over the five aggregates, yet the discourse depends on instruction, discernment, memory, and a sequence from seeing to disenchantment and release. Brihadaranyaka 3.7.23 refuses ordinary objectification of the seer and knower, but authorizes the remainder as the inner ruler and Self. Tannisho relocates efficacy away from self-power into Amida's vow and entrusting, while also preserving teacher lineage, warning against license, and refusing ownership of disciples. Mahasi's Manual of Insight makes operational remainder unusually explicit: ethical preparation, concentration, noting, progress mapping, teacher interpretation, and verification are all part of the practice surface. The close read supports the three variables, but also shows that much of the structure is already visible in primary materials."
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-method-s-reckoning-what-a-practice-does-with-its-own-authority-at-completion-54774578d7528e56.json:13:    "Zhuangzi, Dzogchen, and Sufi fana are classified as self-dissolving because the practitioner or frame of method becomes irrelevant.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-method-s-reckoning-what-a-practice-does-with-its-own-authority-at-completion-54774578d7528e56.json:34:      "expected_observation": "After Advaita inquiry, practitioners describe recognition as stable witness or Self. After Heart Sutra or Madhyamaka practice, they resist treating any insight as an attained object. After Dzogchen or fana language, they emphasize effortless presence or transformed embodiment over method success.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-method-s-reckoning-what-a-practice-does-with-its-own-authority-at-completion-54774578d7528e56.json:42:      "test_surface": "Historical and textual analysis of Zen, Dzogchen, Advaita, Madhyamaka, Sufi, and Christian apophatic training sequences.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-method-s-reckoning-what-a-practice-does-with-its-own-authority-at-completion-54774578d7528e56.json:116:      "Dzogchen or Mahamudra teachers",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-method-s-reckoning-what-a-practice-does-with-its-own-authority-at-completion-54774578d7528e56.json:127:    "secondary_literature_gap": "I did not find an exact three-type typology of contemplative methods as confirming, canceling, and dissolving at completion. But the self-canceling portion has very strong prior art in Nagarjuna, Wittgenstein ladder readings, Buddhist raft discussions, and Sells on apophatic unsaying. The dissolving portion is also standard in fana, zuowang, and Dzogchen descriptions. The new part is the comparative axis and its predicted consequences, not the individual patterns.",
findings/convergences/2026-05-26-whether-first-break-type-and-residue-authorization-can-be-coded-independently-eno.md:9:First-break type and residue authorization are both real variables, neither fully reducible to the other, and the original universality claim must be narrowed to include no-break and open-remainder cases.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-remainder-pressure-as-the-hidden-variable-in-self-negation-4c3627df0bad54f1.json:6:    "why_it_breaks_or_strains_model": "If advanced practice can end reported consciousness without producing a subject-remainder pressure, the pressure is not an invariant. It may be tradition-specific, stage-specific, or retrospectively constructed."
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-remainder-pressure-as-the-hidden-variable-in-self-negation-4c3627df0bad54f1.json:23:  "exact_claim": "The bridge between Upanishadic witness language, early Buddhist not-self analysis, and modern consciousness research is remainder pressure: the felt or conceptual demand to posit a final subject after object-like contents have been negated.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-remainder-pressure-as-the-hidden-variable-in-self-negation-4c3627df0bad54f1.json:28:      "if_model_is_right": "Remainder pressure should be detectable in reports before doctrinal interpretation is applied.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-remainder-pressure-as-the-hidden-variable-in-self-negation-4c3627df0bad54f1.json:40:  "idea_path": "observations/codex/2026-05-25-remainder-pressure-as-the-hidden-variable-in-self-negation.md",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-remainder-pressure-as-the-hidden-variable-in-self-negation-4c3627df0bad54f1.json:42:    "remainder pressure final subject after negation self inquiry Buddhism Advaita",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-remainder-pressure-as-the-hidden-variable-in-self-negation-4c3627df0bad54f1.json:56:      "difference": "The Lumenary idea adds a variable for how systems interpret the seeming remainder.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-remainder-pressure-as-the-hidden-variable-in-self-negation-4c3627df0bad54f1.json:62:      "difference": "The candidate uses cessation as a test of remainder pressure rather than as a state taxonomy.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-remainder-pressure-as-the-hidden-variable-in-self-negation-4c3627df0bad54f1.json:75:    "Define observable markers of remainder pressure before using it as an explanatory variable.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-remainder-pressure-as-the-hidden-variable-in-self-negation-4c3627df0bad54f1.json:88:      "Does naming remainder pressure change how you guide students who reify awareness?"
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-remainder-pressure-as-the-hidden-variable-in-self-negation-4c3627df0bad54f1.json:95:      "Dzogchen and Mahamudra teachers",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-remainder-pressure-as-the-hidden-variable-in-self-negation-4c3627df0bad54f1.json:105:    "secondary_literature_gap": "The search found close components in minimal phenomenal experience, self-model theory, attention and agency factors, pure consciousness debates, and nirodha research. No exact prior phrase remainder pressure appeared, but the mechanisms are not new enough to call a discovery without empirical coding.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-remainder-pressure-as-the-hidden-variable-in-self-negation-4c3627df0bad54f1.json:106:    "structural_observation": "The texts show divergent management of remainder, but they do not clearly show a felt pressure. Brihadaranyaka supplies a seer-knower through a cosmological and theological sequence. SN 22.59 applies a disciplined not-self template to aggregates. The pressure variable is therefore not directly textual. It is an interpretive bridge from these texts to practice reports and cognitive science."
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-every-path-needs-what-its-teaching-dissolves-daeecdbd22658370.md:32:Risk of overread: High. The model may turn a researcher's philosophical tension into a practitioner's lived problem. It also risks forcing mixed traditions into clean boxes. Theravada, Zen, Advaita, Sufism, Dzogchen, and Christian grace traditions often combine effort, surrender, recognition, teacher relation, and ethical transformation across stages.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-every-path-needs-what-its-teaching-dissolves-daeecdbd22658370.md:42:- Dogen practice-realization beginner original enlightenment Bendowa
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-every-path-needs-what-its-teaching-dissolves-daeecdbd22658370.md:53:- Dogen practice-realization sources, for example Soto and Bendowa summaries, https://zenlineage.org/schools/soto and https://buddhismnow.com/2023/10/08/practice-within-realisation-dogen/: overlap: The temporal-collapse strategy is already central to Dogen's practice-realization, where practice is not merely a means to later awakening.; difference: It does not compare this strategy against Advaita, Theravada, and Sufi models of self-continuity.; novelty impact: Moderate reduction. The Zen strategy is known; the comparative placement may still be useful.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-every-path-needs-what-its-teaching-dissolves-daeecdbd22658370.md:61:Candidate: Other-power and direct-introduction traditions, such as Jodo Shinshu entrusting and Dzogchen pointing-out, appear to minimize self-powered agency while still functioning as paths.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-every-path-needs-what-its-teaching-dissolves-daeecdbd22658370.md:69:- If: The stronger a path's final self-dissolution claim, the more explicit its safeguards should be against premature or distorted self-loss. Then: Manuals and teachers should warn against nihilism, dissociation, spiritual bypassing, false attainment, antinomianism, or ego-inflation in ways that match the path's self-management strategy. Weakens if: Warnings show no relationship to self-teaching and track only institution, teacher personality, or general ethics. Test surface: Coded comparison of Theravada, Zen, Dzogchen, Advaita, Sufi, Christian apophatic, and Pure Land training materials.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-every-path-needs-what-its-teaching-dissolves-daeecdbd22658370.md:80:- Dzogchen or Mahamudra teachers
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-every-path-needs-what-its-teaching-dissolves-daeecdbd22658370.md:116:- Add Pure Land other-power, Christian grace, and Dzogchen pointing-out as anomaly cases, not footnotes.
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-some-paths-refuse-the-question-of-what-remains-d756c9bf775096c6.json:4:    "anomaly_candidate": "Rinzai koan and huatou practice deliberately uses an impossible or destabilizing question to create great doubt, while Dzogchen can deny path and result yet still require direct introduction, teacher relation, and integration.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-some-paths-refuse-the-question-of-what-remains-d756c9bf775096c6.json:6:    "why_it_breaks_or_strains_model": "If a path uses an apparently malformed question as medicine, then question-refusal is not enough to decide that remainder pressure is analyst-made. If no-path language still depends on transmission and repair holders, then the residue question may be relocated to practice ecology rather than abolished."
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-some-paths-refuse-the-question-of-what-remains-d756c9bf775096c6.json:10:    "Some contemplative paths stage a search sequence, so they generate a legitimate downstream remainder question.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-some-paths-refuse-the-question-of-what-remains-d756c9bf775096c6.json:11:    "Some paths refuse the search sequence itself, so remainder pressure is malformed there.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-some-paths-refuse-the-question-of-what-remains-d756c9bf775096c6.json:23:  "exact_claim": "Before any continuity or residue analysis after self-negation, test whether the path stages self-negation as an event with an after. If a path refuses seeking, before-and-after, or self-owned attainment, the question of what remains may be an analyst artifact rather than a practitioner problem.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-some-paths-refuse-the-question-of-what-remains-d756c9bf775096c6.json:29:      "test_surface": "Inter-rater coding on SN 22.59, SN 22.95, Huangbo, Bendowa, Tannisho, one Dzogchen direct-introduction source, and one Rinzai koan source.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-some-paths-refuse-the-question-of-what-remains-d756c9bf775096c6.json:34:      "if_model_is_right": "Remainder pressure is not universal.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-some-paths-refuse-the-question-of-what-remains-d756c9bf775096c6.json:50:    "Huangbo Transmission of Mind no seeking using mind to seek Mind",
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-some-paths-refuse-the-question-of-what-remains-d756c9bf775096c6.json:51:    "Dogen Bendowa practice realization one shusho itto practice verification",
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-some-paths-refuse-the-question-of-what-remains-d756c9bf775096c6.json:52:    "Dzogchen no path no practice direct introduction teacher support",
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-some-paths-refuse-the-question-of-what-remains-d756c9bf775096c6.json:63:      "difference": "The candidate turns Huangbo's instruction into a comparative coding gate for residue analysis and a modern practice-safety rule.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-some-paths-refuse-the-question-of-what-remains-d756c9bf775096c6.json:65:      "overlap": "Huangbo already says seeking, conceptual road-making, and using mind to seek Mind are errors.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-some-paths-refuse-the-question-of-what-remains-d756c9bf775096c6.json:66:      "source": "Huangbo, On the Transmission of Mind, https://selfdefinition.org/zen/huang-po/transmission/a1-chun-chou-record.htm and https://selfdefinition.org/zen/huang-po/transmission/a2-chun-chou-record-cont.htm"
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-some-paths-refuse-the-question-of-what-remains-d756c9bf775096c6.json:69:      "difference": "The candidate groups Dogen with search-refusal paths, but Dogen still insists on active, continuous practice.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-some-paths-refuse-the-question-of-what-remains-d756c9bf775096c6.json:70:      "novelty_impact": "Moderate downgrade and anomaly pressure. Dogen supports the gate but resists any no-practice simplification.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-some-paths-refuse-the-question-of-what-remains-d756c9bf775096c6.json:72:      "source": "Dogen Bendowa and Soto shusho itto, https://afe.easia.columbia.edu/ps/japan/dogen.pdf and https://global.sotozen-net.or.jp/eng/library/key_terms/pdf/key_terms07.pdf"
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-some-paths-refuse-the-question-of-what-remains-d756c9bf775096c6.json:75:      "difference": "The candidate applies that structure to contemplative self-negation and predicts practice failure from a malformed question.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-some-paths-refuse-the-question-of-what-remains-d756c9bf775096c6.json:76:      "novelty_impact": "Moderate downgrade. The formal logic is known; the remainder-gate application is the extension.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-some-paths-refuse-the-question-of-what-remains-d756c9bf775096c6.json:81:      "difference": "The candidate narrows this to a before-remainder audit for no-distance teachings.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-some-paths-refuse-the-question-of-what-remains-d756c9bf775096c6.json:97:    "Add Rinzai koan practice and Dzogchen direct introduction as anomaly classes, not supporting examples.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-some-paths-refuse-the-question-of-what-remains-d756c9bf775096c6.json:101:  "novelty_adjustment": "Lower novelty from 0.46 to 0.36. The core no-seeking and no-result logic is old in Huangbo, Dogen, Dzogchen, Shinran-adjacent no-calculation sources, and prior Lumenary no-management records. Retain as an extended precondition-gate hypothesis only if split-source coding shows predictive gain.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-some-paths-refuse-the-question-of-what-remains-d756c9bf775096c6.json:104:    "answers_that_reduce_originality": "Originality falls if practitioners say this is standard pedagogy under no-seeking, shusho itto, Other Power, direct introduction, koan great doubt, or ordinary spiritual-bypassing triage, and if the gate adds no decisions beyond existing teacher judgment.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-some-paths-refuse-the-question-of-what-remains-d756c9bf775096c6.json:114:      "Soto Zen teachers and Dogen scholars",
