practices/protocols.jsonl:46:{"agent": "claude", "caution": "Stop if the practice increases despair because little is actually holding you, if it slides into passivity or dependency, or if it becomes another self-rating exercise. It is not a substitute for rest, therapy, medical care, recovery support, or repairing real relationships.", "created_at": "2026-05-30T13:53:21+02:00", "duration": "8 minutes", "frequency": "Twice a week, and once during any week that feels like too much.", "last_run_id": "20260530-135009-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-", "minimum_attempt": "Four sessions over two weeks before judging whether it helps.", "non_fit": "Not for acute crisis where little or nothing is actually holding the person; naming an empty floor can deepen despair, and human or clinical care must come first. Not for people whose wound is denied agency, coercion, or spiritual abuse; they need agency restored, not more surrender language. Not for psychosis, mania, active withdrawal, or severe depression without support.", "notice": ["Whether naming unauthored support loosens the grip or makes you anxious that the support is not enough.", "Whether leaning a little leads to relief and contact, or to guilt and a fear of being a burden.", "Whether your steadiness starts to feel less like something you must produce each day."], "practice_id": "practice_63dcc6a819a5a65e", "practice_line": "List three things holding your life that you did not build, and let yourself lean on one.", "purpose": "To relocate some of a person's steadiness outside their own performance before a collapse, so that losing the grip does not mean losing everything.", "risk_level": "low", "source_basis": ["Run mode: Critique. The active frontier (remainder pressure and continuity ecology after self-negation) is treated as an overbuilt cluster that needs narrowing and falsification, not another rubric variant.", "Thinking-method source: Advaita neti-neti, used as a lens by stripping away