reviews/dialogues/2026-05-30-can-the-temperament-gate-be-self-administered-without-becoming-another-a.json:196:      "remaining_risk": "My precondition test may overreach. The Proponent could answer, with the support-relocation findings, that search-refusing paths were never practiced in a vacuum: Huangbo taught inside a monastery with precepts and a teacher, Dzogchen recognition is held within transmission and vow. If practitioners of these paths reliably depend on identifiable supports and break down in patterned ways when those supports vanish, then 'no after-use' is answered at the level of practice rather than malformed, and the after-use grid may quietly apply there too. In that case my gate narrows to doctrine alone and the Proponent's model survives at the level of lived practice.",
