reviews/originality/2026-05-26-custody-and-receiving-surface-255ec907071592a1.md:51:- Prior Lumenary records in prompt: Capacity Ledger, Forbidden Claimant Rubric, Credit Distribution, Handoff Point, Entry-Claimant Grammar, Claimability and Support Rubric, Continuity Ecology Under Negation, Operational Remainder Ecology: overlap: Extremely close. Prior Lumenary work already separates support locus, claimant rules, agency distribution, handoff timing, residue policy, operational capacity, training ecology, safeguards, failure modes, repairs, and verification.; difference: The current idea gives the practitioner-side variable a clearer name, receiving surface, and proposes a direct separability test against custody assignment.; novelty impact: Large reduction. Treat as consolidation and extension unless the receiving-surface variable shows independent predictive value beyond prior ledgers.
