reviews/originality/2026-05-26-operational-remainder-ecology-39a96b7ef7849b21.md:52:- Prior Lumenary records in the prompt, especially Every Path Needs What Its Teaching Dissolves, Residual Burden of Proof After Negation, Capacity Ledger, Forbidden Claimant Rubric, Credit Distribution, Handoff Point, Entry-Claimant Grammar, Claimability and Support Rubric, and Continuity Ecology Under Negation: overlap: Extremely close. The candidate explicitly consolidates operational capacity, residue policy, support locus, training ecology, warnings, verification, and failure-mode prediction already developed across prior Lumenary audits.; difference: The new record adds a cleaner three-factor interaction frame and makes adverse-event prediction more explicit.; novelty impact: Large internal reduction. Treat as consolidation and extension, not an independent discovery.
reviews/originality/audits.jsonl:26:{"agent": "codex", "anomaly_probe": {"anomaly_candidate": "Dogen's practice-realization and inherited-practice cases.", "confidence_effect": "This lowers confidence in any universal causal claim. The model should remain an interpretive coding heuristic unless split-source tests show predictive gain over practice-realization, socialization, and institutional history.", "why_it_breaks_or_strains_model": "Dogen's Bendowa denies a clean boundary in realization and denies a beginning in practice. Inherited religious participation can also preserve continuity before any explicit self-negating doctrine is consciously adopted. In both cases, the model may impose a migration story where the tradition presents no transfer, no threshold, or no separate continuity problem."}, "audit_id": "fd9108753ae68e6a", "claim_units": ["Self negating paths require transformability, not necessarily a minimum self.", "Continuity can be distributed across body, habit, teacher, ritual, vow, community, grace, text, institution, and environment.", "Dissolution target and residue policy should predict where continuity is preserved or relocated.", "Practice ecology may cause doctrine as often as doctrine causes practice ecology.", "The model is testable by coding doctrine, supports, warnings, verification methods, and failure modes from separate source sets."], "confidence": 0.78, "created_at": "2026-05-26T17:52:23-07:00", "cross_domain_prediction": {"domain": "Addiction recovery and psychotherapy for compulsive self-control collapse.", "prediction": "Programs that more strongly deny individual self-mastery should rely more visibly on external or relational continuity supports and should show predictable failures when participants convert surrender into self-ownership, isolate from the group, or lose routine anchors.", "structural_translation": "When an intervention negates autonomous control, it must relocate continuity into a sponsor, group, higher power, routine, script, therapist relation, values commitment, medication, or environment design.", "would_count_against_it": "No relationship appears between autonomy-negating language and support relocation, or outcomes are fully predicted by generic social support, treatment intensity, diagnosis, medication, and socioeconomic stability."}, "exact_claim": "Self negating or self transcending paths preserve enough receptivity and reliability for transformation through a continuity ecology. This continuity may be internally managed, externally scaffolded, relationally entrusted, ritually stabilized, institutionally maintained, or theologically relocated. The path's dissolution target may pressure where continuity migrates, residue policy governs what remains authorized after negation, and practice ecology may either express doctrine or historically precede it.", "execution_id": "dialogue-c7bd07aed1efede4", "falsifiable_predictions": [{"expected_observation": "Coders who see only doctrinal negation passages can predict above baseline whether later manuals locate support in effort, attention, teacher, vow, grace, ritual, community, text, or no-boundary practice-realization.", "if_model_is_right": "Dissolution target and residue policy exert independent pressure on continuity placement.", "test_surface": "Split-source blind coding across Theravada, Advaita, Soto Zen, Jodo Shinshu, Dzogchen or Mahamudra, Christian grace, Sufi fana and baqa, and secular mindfulness manuals.", "would_weaken_or_falsify": "Prediction fails, or ritual form, institution type, teacher authority, socialization pattern, or historical borrowing predicts support placement better than dissolution target and residue policy."}, {"expected_observation": "When the path's primary support holder is absent or confused, failures cluster by support type: effort paths show striving and fatigue, teacher-held paths show dependency or disorientation, vow or grace-held paths show calculation and doubt, no-boundary paths show laxity or antinomian misunderstanding.", "if_model_is_right": "Continuity ecology is not a decorative description but a failure-mode predictor.", "test_surface": "Practitioner interviews, adverse-event reports, VCE-style coding, and training-program records.", "would_weaken_or_falsify": "Failure modes are better explained by dose, trauma history, charisma, group norms, mental-health risk, socioeconomic stress, or ordinary teacher quality after controls."}, {"expected_observation": "Where support structures predate doctrinal refinement, later doctrine explicitly explains, legitimates, or polices already existing teacher, ritual, vow, or institutional arrangements.", "if_model_is_right": "Practice ecology can precede doctrine but should leave historical traces when it does.", "test_surface": "Historical comparison of Shinran communities, Soto monastic practice, Theravada reform movements, modern mindfulness programs, and Christian grace controversies.", "would_weaken_or_falsify": "Historical cases show no relation between prior ecology and later doctrine, or show doctrine changing without support-ecology change and without new warning or verification patterns."}, {"expected_observation": "Traditions screen, sequence, or repair students around capacities to be addressed, receive instruction or grace, register transformation, continue practice, and avoid obstructing the path's support holder.", "if_model_is_right": "Minimum receptivity has observable thresholds rather than being a trivial requirement.", "test_surface": "Teacher interviews and manual coding with separate fields for entry, warning, verification, and repair.", "would_weaken_or_falsify": "Practitioners cannot identify distinct thresholds beyond generic motivation, ethics, or mental stability, or thresholds do not vary with support ecology."}], "idea_id": "34cbc5115dbd898a", "idea_path": "observations/codex/2026-05-26-continuity-ecology-under-negation.md", "literature_search_queries": ["continuity self no-self Buddhism practice support ecology distributed cognition religion", "distributed self religious practice agency habitus", "self negation practice scaffolding religion continuity", "extended mind religious practice agency ritual cognition", "doctrine as grammar Lindbeck religious practice rules", "discursive tradition Asad religious practice authority agency", "Saba Mahmood agency capacity piety practice subject formation", "religious coping self directing deferring collaborative Pargament agency", "SN 22.59 Anatta-lakkhana Sutta primary text five aggregates not self", "Chandogya Upanishad 6.8.7 tat tvam asi primary text", "Brihadaranyaka Upanishad 3.7.23 inner controller primary text not seen seer", "Tannisho Shinran Other Power self power calculation primary text", "Dogen Bendowa practice realization one primary text", "Longchen Rabjam Trekcho recognition practice effort primary text"], "markdown_path": "reviews/originality/2026-05-26-continuity-ecology-under-negation-fd9108753ae68e6a.md", "near_neighbors": [{"difference": "The candidate applies the structure specifically to self negating paths and adds dissolution target, residue policy, and split-source causal prediction.", "novelty_impact": "Large reduction. Much of continuity ecology is extended, scaffolded, or socially extended religious cognition in Lumenary vocabulary.", "overlap": "Very close for external, material, social, institutional, and ritual supports constituting cognition, selfhood, affect, and religious experience.", "source": "Clark and Chalmers, The Extended Mind, https://academic.oup.com/analysis/article/58/1/7/153111; Krueger, Extended Mind and Religious Cognition, https://philpapers.org/archive/KRUTEM-2.pdf; Luckett, Bridging Belief and Social Practice, https://philarchive.org/archive/LUCBBA-2v1"}, {"difference": "Asad is not building a cross-tradition rubric for self negation or residue after self dissolution.", "novelty_impact": "Large reduction for the ecology and causal-priority caution. The candidate's remaining contribution is a narrower comparative coding hypothesis.", "overlap": "Very close for practices being instructed through discursive traditions that connect past, future, present institutions, social conditions, moral selves, knowledge, and authority.", "source": "Talal Asad, The Idea of an Anthropology of Islam, https://voidnetwork.gr/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/The-Idea-of-an-Anthropology-of-Islam-by-Talal-Asad.pdf"}, {"difference": "The candidate uses grammar to predict support placement and failure modes in self negating practice rather than to explain doctrine generally.", "novelty_impact": "Moderate to large reduction. Residue policy and continuity placement look like a specialized rule-theory application.", "overlap": "Close for doctrine as rules that regulate discourse, attitude, action, communal continuity, and the shaping of life.", "source": "George Lindbeck doctrine-as-grammar discussions, https://www.repository.cam.ac.uk/items/351e3c35-6838-49bc-9b33-3ae66dd1fea5 and https://people.bu.edu/wwildman/bce/mwt_themes_862_lindbeck.htm"}, {"difference": "VCE does not propose that dissolution target and residue policy predict where transformability is preserved.", "novelty_impact": "Moderate reduction. VCE is a strong empirical baseline the candidate must outperform.", "overlap": "Close for coding practitioner, practice, relationship, worldview, teacher, community, health, appraisal, and remedy factors in contemplative difficulty.", "source": "Lindahl et al., Varieties of Contemplative Experience, https://journals.plos.org/plosone/article?id=10.1371/journal.pone.0176239"}, {"difference": "Pargament is about coping and control, not self-negating soteriology or authorized residue after negation.", "novelty_impact": "Moderate reduction for the support-locus axis.", "overlap": "Close for distributing control across self, God, and collaborative self-God relations, and for treating religious coping as multimodal and dynamic.", "source": "Pargament religious coping styles and Brief RCOPE, https://www.mdpi.com/2077-1444/2/1/51"}, {"difference": "The candidate generalizes capacity formation into a cross-tradition continuity ecology under negation.", "novelty_impact": "Moderate to large reduction. Minimum receptivity is close to cultivated agency and ethical subject formation.", "overlap": "Close for agency and capacity being formed by embodied norms, discipline, habitus, and religious practice rather than existing as a liberal autonomous self.", "source": "Saba Mahmood and piety-practice literature, examples at https://journals.sagepub.com/doi/10.1177/00187267251355394 and https://brill.com/view/journals/soi/7/4/article-p289_289.pdf"}, {"difference": "The candidate shifts from metaphysical personal identity to practical supports that preserve transformability within a path.", "novelty_impact": "Large reduction for the problem statement, moderate preservation for the support-ecology operationalization.", "overlap": "Close for the core problem of continuity without a substantial self, especially karma, rebirth, practice agency, and conventional personhood.", "source": "Buddhist no-self and personal identity literature, including Collins and Siderits bibliographic anchors, https://academic.oup.com/reference/62340/reference-article/554142709 and https://openlibrary.org/works/OL2620411W/Selfless_persons"}, {"difference": "The candidate names these as variables in one cross-tradition model.", "novelty_impact": "Large reduction. Several allegedly new variables are already visible in the source texts.", "overlap": "Very close primary evidence for theologically relocated support, no-boundary practice-realization, guru reliance, vows, solitude, and post-recognition training.", "source": "Tannisho, Dogen Bendowa, and Longchen Rabjam Trekcho primary materials, https://www.themathesontrust.org/papers/fareasternreligions/Tannisho-Unno.pdf; https://buddhismnow.com/2023/10/08/practice-within-realisation-dogen/; https://www.lotsawahouse.org/tibetan-masters/longchen-rabjam/lama-yangtik-trekcho-instruction"}, {"difference": "This idea consolidates them under continuity ecology and adds explicit causal priority uncertainty.", "novelty_impact": "Large internal reduction. Treat as consolidation and extension, not an independent discovery.", "overlap": "Extremely close for capacity, residue, support locus, forbidden claimant, entry grammar, transfer, and failure-mode prediction.", "source": "Prior Lumenary records in the prompt, especially Every Path Needs What Its Teaching Dissolves, Residue Policy in Negative Self-Practice, Capacity Ledger, Handoff Point, Entry-Claimant Grammar, and Claimability and Support Rubric"}], "next_loop_instructions": ["Do not publish as doctrine. Treat as a comparative and practitioner-facing research heuristic.", "Build a split-source coding sheet with fields for dissolution target, residue policy, support holder, minimum receptivity threshold, practice ecology, warning profile, verification rule, repair, failure mode, and analyst-frame refusal.", "Require coders to code doctrine from primary doctrinal passages, then predict support holders and warnings from separate manuals or practitioner interviews.", "Add mandatory anomaly values: no-boundary practice-realization, inherited practice, no-threshold, vow-held, grace-held, teacher-recognition, ritual-first, institution-first, secular extraction, and undecidable.", "Compare predictive power against extended mind, Asad, Lindbeck, Pargament, VCE, upaya, conversion studies, situated learning, socialization, habitus, and prior Lumenary ledgers.", "Run practitioner interviews for concrete failed-student cases and repair instructions, not abstract agreement.", "Do not raise above extended unless split-source blind coding predicts safeguards, verification practices, or failure repairs better than established theories and prior Lumenary models."], "novelty_adjustment": "Reduce novelty from 0.80 to about 0.56. The candidate is useful and testable, but the core components are already strongly anticipated by extended and socially extended religious cognition, Asad's discursive tradition, Lindbeck's grammar model, Pargament's agency styles, VCE influencing-factor coding, Buddhist continuity-without-self debates, and prior Lumenary ledgers. The remaining contribution is a consolidated comparative coding hypothesis with explicit causal-priority tests.", "originality_status": "extended", "path": "reviews/originality/2026-05-26-continuity-ecology-under-negation-fd9108753ae68e6a.json", "practitioner_test": {"answers_that_reduce_originality": "Practitioners say this is standard no-self continuity, Other Power, practice-realization, guru-yoga, grace, upaya, spiritual materialism, or ordinary pastoral sequencing. They cannot identify new predictions, repairs, or failure clusters.", "answers_that_support_contribution": "Practitioners independently identify continuity holders and say the rubric helps predict concrete warnings, screening, sequencing, or repair instructions that existing lineage vocabulary did not make explicit.", "questions": ["Does this continuity ecology name something your lineage already teaches, or does it change diagnosis?", "Where is continuity actually held when self, effort, ownership, or agency is negated: attention, body, teacher, vow, grace, ritual, text, community, or something else?", "Can you name concrete student failure cases that follow from misplacing continuity?", "Does the rubric predict warnings or repairs you would not already derive from ordinary pedagogy, spiritual materialism, upaya, coping styles, or trauma-informed care?", "Are there cases in your lineage where the entire language of continuity placement is misleading?"], "relevant_practitioners": ["Theravada teachers familiar with anatta, fetters, and path verification", "Advaita Vedanta teachers familiar with neti-neti and teacher-led recognition", "Soto Zen teachers familiar with practice-realization", "Jodo Shinshu ministers familiar with shinjin, Other Power, and non-calculation", "Dzogchen or Mahamudra teachers familiar with recognition, guru reliance, and post-recognition conduct", "Christian contemplative directors familiar with grace, surrender, and apophasis", "Sufi teachers familiar with fana, baqa, adab, and shaykh relation", "Contemplative clinicians familiar with meditation-related difficulties"]}, "primary_text_close_read": {"primary_pair": ["SN 22.59 Anatta-lakkhana Sutta, https://www.dhammatalks.org/suttas/SN/SN22_59.html", "Chandogya Upanishad 6.8.7 and 6.14.1-2, https://shlokam.org/texts/Chandogya-6-8-7", "Brihadaranyaka Upanishad 3.7.23, https://www.brhat.in/openlibrary/special/brihadaranyaka-upanishad/3-7-23", "Tannisho, Taitetsu Unno translation, https://www.themathesontrust.org/papers/fareasternreligions/Tannisho-Unno.pdf; Collected Works of Shinran, https://shinranworks.com/commentaries/notes-on-once-calling-and-many-calling/"], "risk_of_overread": "High. Continuity ecology can become an analyst's umbrella that absorbs every support a tradition uses. It may also distort traditions that refuse self, agency, transfer, beginning, or support-locus accounting. Causal claims are especially risky unless doctrine, ecology, and failure modes are coded from independent corpora.", "secondary_literature_gap": "The audit used accessible primary translations and open academic sources, but did not fully read Collins, Siderits, Harvey, Albahari, Mahmood's Politics of Piety, Bourdieu, Rambo, Lave and Wenger, Shinran's full Kyogyoshinsho, Dogen scholarship, or Tibetan manuals beyond Longchen Rabjam. Pali, Sanskrit, Japanese, and Tibetan terms were not checked directly.", "structural_observation": "SN 22.59 negates ownership of all aggregates and moves through disenchantment, dispassion, and release, so continuity is carried by instruction, discernment, and practice process rather than an authorized self. Chandogya repeatedly authorizes an underlying Self, but 6.14 also uses a teacher and stepwise inquiry as the way a blindfolded person finds the way home. Brihadaranyaka 3.7.23 relocates continuity into an unseen inner controller. Tannisho relocates decisive support into Amida's vow, true entrusting, teacher lineage, and non-calculating nembutsu, while refusing ownership of disciples or practice. This close read strongly supports the candidate's comparative frame, but also shows that much of the structure is already explicit in primary texts."}, "recommended_scores": {"counterargument_quality": 0.91, "novelty": 0.56, "source_reliability": 0.8}, "run_ids": [], "title": "Continuity Ecology Under Negation", "unlike_statement": "Unlike extended mind religious cognition, Asad's discursive tradition, Lindbeck's doctrine-as-grammar, VCE, Pargament, Buddhist continuity-without-self literature, and prior Lumenary ledgers, this idea says that self-negating paths preserve transformability through a codable continuity ecology and predicts that dissolution target plus residue policy will partly forecast where continuity is stored after institutional, ritual, and historical controls."}
reviews/originality/audits.jsonl:27:{"agent": "codex", "anomaly_probe": {"anomaly_candidate": "Dogen-style practice-realization, inherited devotional practice, radical Other Power, and secular mindfulness adverse effects strain the model from different sides.", "confidence_effect": "The anomaly lowers confidence from candidate_discovery to extended. It does not refute the heuristic, but it requires analyst-frame-refusal values and baseline comparisons against ecology-only and clinical-risk models.", "why_it_breaks_or_strains_model": "Practice-realization can refuse a before-and-after account in which capacity remains and then receives a residue label. Inherited practice may work through ritual and community before explicit doctrine is understood. Other Power can treat naming receptivity as a capacity as a self-power distortion. Secular mindfulness adverse effects can occur without explicit self-negating residue policy, which may mean ecology, dose, arousal, vulnerability, and interpretation explain more than the proposed residue axis."}, "audit_id": "39a96b7ef7849b21", "claim_units": ["Self-negating or agency-negating contemplative paths still require usable operational capacities such as attention, memory, effort, reflexivity, receptivity, trust, or surrender.", "A path's residue policy determines what those remaining capacities are allowed to count as, such as causal process, conventional personhood, witness, Self, divine gift, vow, relation, or nothing ultimately ownable.", "Training ecology, including teacher, community, intensity, duration, screening, interpretation, and support, determines whether the operational demand stabilizes or destabilizes the practitioner.", "Safeguards, warnings, verification methods, and crisis patterns should be predicted by the interaction of capacity profile, residue policy, and ecology better than by self-doctrine alone."], "confidence": 0.83, "created_at": "2026-05-26T18:07:48-07:00", "cross_domain_prediction": {"domain": "Psychotherapy and behavior-change programs that weaken identity claims, such as exposure therapy, addiction recovery, identity-based coaching, or moral injury work.", "prediction": "Programs that dissolve maladaptive identity without preserving and authorizing enough operational capacity should show predictable failure modes: passivity, dissociation, shame, dependency, collapse of responsibility, or license. Programs with the same technique but different residue policy and ecology should require different safeguards.", "structural_translation": "Operational capacity becomes the psychological function that must stay usable, such as affect tolerance, memory, agency, trust, or self-monitoring. Residue policy becomes what the program says the remaining function means, such as illness process, responsibility, grace, values, role, or non-identification. Training ecology becomes therapist, peer group, dose, monitoring, crisis plan, and interpretive frame.", "would_count_against_it": "Identity-dissolving interventions show similar outcomes regardless of capacity demands, interpretive policy, and ecology, or ordinary variables such as therapeutic alliance, diagnosis, and dose fully explain failure patterns with no added predictive gain from the translated model."}, "exact_claim": "A contemplative path is shaped by three interacting factors: the operational capacities it requires, the residue policy it applies after negation, and the training ecology that calibrates those demands in lived practice. The model predicts that safeguards, warnings, verification methods, and crisis patterns emerge from the interaction of all three, not from self-doctrine alone.", "execution_id": "dialogue-bdbb62b82cefd5ea", "falsifiable_predictions": [{"expected_observation": "Blind coders should predict later warning clusters, such as striving, nihilism, dissociation, antinomian license, teacher-dependence, inflation, despair, or passivity, above chance and above doctrine-only or ecology-only baselines.", "if_model_is_right": "Initial doctrine or entry texts can be coded for operational capacities and residue policy independently from later warnings and repairs.", "test_surface": "Split-source blind coding of primary manuals, followed by comparison with separate warning sections, adverse-event reports, and teacher interviews.", "would_weaken_or_falsify": "Inter-rater reliability on capacity and residue codes is poor, or predictions disappear once intensity, teacher quality, psychiatric vulnerability, social support, and reporting genre are controlled."}, {"expected_observation": "Paths that both deny ultimate self-ownership but train different operations, for example analytic noting and open sitting, should warn against and repair different failure modes.", "if_model_is_right": "Traditions with similar residue policies but different operational capacity profiles should generate different safeguards and crisis patterns.", "test_surface": "Matched comparison of Theravada vipassana manuals, Soto shikantaza sources, and practitioner interviews.", "would_weaken_or_falsify": "Matched cases show similar warnings and repairs despite different operational profiles, or differences are better explained by retreat intensity, institution, teacher style, or culture."}, {"expected_observation": "Practices that train attention, disidentification, and stable witnessing should diverge in whether the remainder is framed as conventional process, witness, Self, grace, vow, or non-ownable event, and these labels should forecast verification and warning practices.", "if_model_is_right": "Traditions with similar operational demands but different residue policies should interpret the same phenomenological event differently and verify it differently.", "test_surface": "Cross-coding Advaita self-inquiry, Buddhist de-identification, Mahamudra or Dzogchen recognition, Shin entrusting, and Christian surrender materials.", "would_weaken_or_falsify": "Practitioner reports and manuals interpret similar events without residue-policy effects, or the interpretive difference has no impact on verification, repair, or safety guidance."}, {"expected_observation": "High-intensity, low-supervision, weak-community settings should produce more adverse or confused reports when operational demands are high and residue policy is easily misunderstood.", "if_model_is_right": "Training ecology moderates the risk created by capacity and residue mismatch.", "test_surface": "Retreat adverse-event datasets, Cheetah House style case intake data, and prospective Lumenary practice-seed safety tracking.", "would_weaken_or_falsify": "Ecology does not moderate outcomes after controlling for baseline vulnerability and practice dose, or mismatch cases do not show distinct repair needs."}], "idea_id": "2a66e120bafebae3", "idea_path": "observations/codex/2026-05-26-operational-remainder-ecology.md", "literature_search_queries": ["operational capacities residue policy contemplative self negation practice ecology", "meditation adverse effects influencing factors teacher community intensity screening Britton Lindahl", "Varieties of Contemplative Experience influencing factors practice practitioner relationship health worldview remedies", "Engler therapeutic aims psychotherapy meditation somebody before nobody self observation ego strength", "religious coping self-directing deferring collaborative Pargament agency styles", "doctrine as grammar Lindbeck religion rules practice discourse attitude action", "Asad discursive tradition religious practice authority discipline", "upaya skillful means capacity pedagogy Buddhist practice", "Mahasi Manual of Insight progress of insight noting teacher warnings", "SN 22.59 anatta operational continuity practice capacity", "Tannisho Other Power self-power calculation warning license", "Brihadaranyaka 3.7.23 inner controller unseen seer"], "markdown_path": "reviews/originality/2026-05-26-operational-remainder-ecology-39a96b7ef7849b21.md", "near_neighbors": [{"difference": "The new record adds a cleaner three-factor interaction frame and makes adverse-event prediction more explicit.", "novelty_impact": "Large internal reduction. Treat as consolidation and extension, not an independent discovery.", "overlap": "Extremely close. The candidate explicitly consolidates operational capacity, residue policy, support locus, training ecology, warnings, verification, and failure-mode prediction already developed across prior Lumenary audits.", "source": "Prior Lumenary records in the prompt, especially Every Path Needs What Its Teaching Dissolves, Residual Burden of Proof After Negation, Capacity Ledger, Forbidden Claimant Rubric, Credit Distribution, Handoff Point, Entry-Claimant Grammar, Claimability and Support Rubric, and Continuity Ecology Under Negation"}, {"difference": "VCE is a descriptive and clinical taxonomy, not a cross-tradition model linking operational capacities and residue policy after negation to predicted safeguards.", "novelty_impact": "Large reduction. The ecology and adverse-effect claims are already strongly anticipated.", "overlap": "Very close for the training ecology side. VCE studies meditation-related challenges through practice factors, practitioner factors, relationships, health behaviors, teachers, communities, worldviews, appraisals, and remedies.", "source": "Lindahl, Fisher, Cooper, Rosen, and Britton, The Varieties of Contemplative Experience, https://journals.plos.org/plosone/article?id=10.1371/journal.pone.0176239"}, {"difference": "It does not formalize residue policy after self-negation or combine worldview with operational capacity coding.", "novelty_impact": "Moderate to large reduction. Residue policy may be a narrower name for worldview and doctrinal interpretation unless it predicts more.", "overlap": "Close for the residue-policy component. The paper treats worldviews as risk factors, remedies, and meaning-making frames that shape the trajectory of meditation-related challenges.", "source": "Lindahl, Palitsky, Cooper, and Britton, The roles and impacts of worldviews in meditation-related challenges, https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/36476189/"}, {"difference": "It does not provide a self-negation or residue-policy typology.", "novelty_impact": "Moderate reduction. Teacher ecology is prior art, not a novel component.", "overlap": "Close for the role of teacher relationship, guidance quality, support, and interpretive response in meditation-related difficulty trajectories.", "source": "Britton et al., The Teacher Matters, https://www.tandfonline.com/doi/abs/10.1080/14639947.2025.2485677"}, {"difference": "Engler's model is developmental and psychotherapeutic rather than a three-axis comparative rubric with residue policy and ecology.", "novelty_impact": "Large reduction for the capacity thesis. The candidate extends, rather than discovers, this pressure.", "overlap": "Very close for the claim that no-self practice presupposes functional ego capacities, especially self-observation, and can be destabilizing without them.", "source": "Jack Engler, Therapeutic Aims in Psychotherapy and Meditation, https://www.atpweb.org/jtparchive/trps-16-84-01-025.pdf; interview summary, https://inquiringmind.com/article/0501_1_engler-interview/"}, {"difference": "Pargament is not focused on contemplative negation or verification after self-dissolution.", "novelty_impact": "Moderate reduction. The support-locus and gift-effort categories need baseline comparison against religious coping styles.", "overlap": "Close for distributing agency and control across self, deity, collaboration, deferral, and surrender, with practical consequences for coping.", "source": "Pargament et al., Religion and the Problem-Solving Process: Three Styles of Coping, https://icmglt.org/icmlibrary/religion-and-the-problem-solving-process-three-styles-of-coping/"}, {"difference": "The candidate narrows grammar into residue policy and asks whether it predicts safeguards and crisis patterns.", "novelty_impact": "Moderate reduction. Residue policy may be a specialized rule-theory application.", "overlap": "Close for treating doctrine as rules that regulate religious speech, attitude, action, and communal formation rather than as isolated propositions.", "source": "George Lindbeck doctrine-as-grammar discussions, https://www.repository.cam.ac.uk/items/351e3c35-6838-49bc-9b33-3ae66dd1fea5"}, {"difference": "Asad does not build a comparative safety rubric for self-negating contemplative paths.", "novelty_impact": "Moderate to large reduction for the anti-doctrine-alone and practice-ecology claims.", "overlap": "Close for the claim that practice, discipline, authority, embodiment, institutions, and historical tradition shape religious subject formation, so doctrine alone cannot explain outcomes.", "source": "Talal Asad, The Idea of an Anthropology of Islam, https://bpb-ap-se2.wpmucdn.com/thinkspace.csu.edu.au/dist/c/3891/files/2020/10/Asad-Anthropology.pdf"}, {"difference": "Upaya does not by itself code residue policies across Buddhist, Vedantic, Shin, Christian, and clinical contexts.", "novelty_impact": "Moderate reduction. Capacity calibration is old. The possible novelty is in the comparative interaction test.", "overlap": "Close for adapting teachings to practitioner capacity, stage, disposition, and risk of misunderstanding.", "source": "Buddhist upaya and capacity pedagogy, for example https://plato.stanford.edu/entries/buddhism-mahayana/ and https://link.springer.com/article/10.1007/s12671-024-02425-3"}, {"difference": "These studies do not focus on spiritual residue policy, but they supply strong rival explanations for crisis patterns.", "novelty_impact": "Moderate to large reduction. The candidate must show added predictive value beyond existing adverse-effect variables.", "overlap": "Close for empirical-adjacent prediction of meditation difficulty from complex contextual factors, practice type, arousal, dissociation, and reporting method.", "source": "Schlosser et al., Unpleasant meditation-related experiences in regular meditators, https://journals.plos.org/plosone/article?id=10.1371/journal.pone.0216643; Britton et al., Defining and measuring meditation-related adverse effects, https://pmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/articles/PMC8845498/"}], "next_loop_instructions": ["Do not publish as doctrine. Treat as a comparative research heuristic and safety-oriented practice-design control.", "Reduce the model to a testable coding sheet with fields for operational capacity, residue policy, training ecology, safeguard, warning, verification, crisis pattern, repair, evidence passage, and analyst-frame refusal.", "Use split-source blind coding: code operational capacity and residue policy from entry or doctrine texts, then predict warnings, safeguards, and repairs from separate manuals or practitioner interviews.", "Add mandatory anomaly values for practice-realization, inherited practice, no-threshold practice, Other Power refusal, grace-held support, teacher-recognition support, secular extraction, psychiatric vulnerability, and undecidable.", "Compare predictive power against VCE influencing factors, Cheetah House adverse-event categories, Engler's developmental warning, Pargament agency styles, Lindbeck grammar, Asad discursive tradition, upaya pedagogy, and prior Lumenary ledgers.", "Run practitioner interviews for concrete failed-student cases and repair instructions rather than agreement with the model.", "Do not raise above extended unless inter-rater coding shows that the three-factor interaction predicts warning clusters, verification practices, or repairs better than doctrine-only, ecology-only, clinical-risk, and prior-ledger baselines."], "novelty_adjustment": "Reduce novelty from 0.82 to about 0.53. The idea is useful and testable, but its main components are strongly anticipated by prior Lumenary ledgers, VCE and Cheetah House style adverse-effects research, Engler's functional ego warning, Pargament's agency and coping styles, Lindbeck's grammar model, Asad's discursive-tradition account, upaya capacity pedagogy, and primary-text evidence. The remaining contribution is a clearer three-factor interaction hypothesis and a split-source testing protocol.", "originality_status": "extended", "path": "reviews/originality/2026-05-26-operational-remainder-ecology-39a96b7ef7849b21.json", "practitioner_test": {"answers_that_reduce_originality": "Practitioners say this is standard pedagogy: know the student's capacity, avoid nihilism or inflation, provide teacher and community support, and interpret experiences according to doctrine. They cannot name any new screening, sequencing, warning, or repair produced by the three-factor model.", "answers_that_support_contribution": "Practitioners independently identify cases where the same self-negating instruction became safe or unsafe depending on the interaction of capacity, permitted meaning, and ecology, and they say the rubric would change screening, sequencing, or repair decisions.", "questions": ["Is the three-part distinction between operational capacity, residue policy, and training ecology obvious in your lineage, or does it change diagnosis?", "Can you name concrete student failures that came from misreading what must remain operational after self, effort, or ownership was negated?", "Does the model predict safeguards or repairs you would not already derive from upaya, spiritual materialism, trauma-informed care, religious coping, or ordinary teacher experience?", "Are there practices in your lineage where the language of remainder, capacity, or support locus distorts the path?", "Would you change screening, sequencing, intensity, or stopping rules if a student's capacity profile and residue interpretation were coded separately?"], "relevant_practitioners": ["Theravada vipassana teachers familiar with Mahasi-style noting, progress of insight, and anatta", "Soto Zen teachers familiar with shikantaza and practice-realization", "Advaita Vedanta teachers familiar with neti-neti, witness practice, and self-inquiry", "Jodo Shinshu ministers familiar with shinjin, Other Power, and non-calculation", "Dzogchen or Mahamudra teachers familiar with recognition, guru relation, and post-recognition conduct", "Christian contemplative directors familiar with grace, surrender, apophasis, and discernment", "Contemplative clinicians or researchers familiar with meditation-related difficulties"]}, "primary_text_close_read": {"primary_pair": ["SN 22.59 Anatta-lakkhana Sutta, https://www.dhammatalks.org/suttas/SN/SN22_59.html", "Brihadaranyaka Upanishad 3.7.23, https://www.brhat.in/openlibrary/special/brihadaranyaka-upanishad/3-7-23", "Tannisho, Taitetsu Unno translation, https://www.themathesontrust.org/papers/fareasternreligions/Tannisho-Unno.pdf", "Mahasi Sayadaw, Manual of Insight, https://wisdomexperience.org/product/manual-insight/"], "risk_of_overread": "High. The model can absorb nearly every tradition by redescribing prerequisites as capacities, doctrine as residue policy, and pedagogy as ecology. It also risks circularity if warnings and crisis patterns are used both to infer the three variables and to confirm that the variables predict those same warnings and crises.", "secondary_literature_gap": "This audit used accessible primary translations and open academic sources, but did not fully reread Collins, Siderits, Harvey, Albahari, Wilber, Engler's full chapter context, Shinran's Kyogyoshinsho, Dogen scholarship, Dzogchen and Mahamudra manuals, or Britton's full adverse-effects corpus. Pali, Sanskrit, Japanese, and Burmese terms were not checked directly. Stronger novelty would require split-source coding and practitioner interviews.", "structural_observation": "SN 22.59 negates ownership and mastery over the five aggregates, yet the discourse depends on instruction, discernment, memory, and a sequence from seeing to disenchantment and release. Brihadaranyaka 3.7.23 refuses ordinary objectification of the seer and knower, but authorizes the remainder as the inner ruler and Self. Tannisho relocates efficacy away from self-power into Amida's vow and entrusting, while also preserving teacher lineage, warning against license, and refusing ownership of disciples. Mahasi's Manual of Insight makes operational remainder unusually explicit: ethical preparation, concentration, noting, progress mapping, teacher interpretation, and verification are all part of the practice surface. The close read supports the three variables, but also shows that much of the structure is already visible in primary materials."}, "recommended_scores": {"counterargument_quality": 0.91, "novelty": 0.53, "source_reliability": 0.78}, "run_ids": [], "title": "Operational Remainder Ecology", "unlike_statement": "Unlike VCE, Britton's adverse-effects work, Engler, Pargament, Lindbeck, Asad, upaya pedagogy, and prior Lumenary ledgers, this idea says that self-negating contemplative paths can be coded along three independent axes, operational capacity, residue policy, and training ecology, and that the interaction among those axes will predict safeguards, warnings, verification methods, and crisis patterns better than any one axis alone."}
reviews/originality/audits.jsonl:28:{"agent": "codex", "anomaly_probe": {"anomaly_candidate": "Dogen-style practice-realization, inherited communal practice, and radical Other Power cases where the analyst cannot cleanly separate custody, entry, and receiving surface.", "confidence_effect": "Lowers confidence from candidate discovery to extended. The model needs analyst-frame-refused, no-threshold, inherited-practice, practice-realization, radical-other-power, and undecidable values before use.", "why_it_breaks_or_strains_model": "If practice and realization are nondual, there may be no discrete landing event and no separate receiving surface. If a person is gradually formed by inherited communal participation before explicit assent, the receiving surface may be socialized rather than locally chosen. If radical Other Power refuses any self-power residue, calling entrusting a human surface may distort the doctrine by reintroducing the agency it rejects."}, "audit_id": "255ec907071592a1", "claim_units": ["Self-weakening contemplative paths relocate transformation functions rather than simply deleting agency.", "Custody assignment can be coded separately from practitioner-side availability.", "Receiving surface may be an independent variable rather than only the local expression of custody.", "The model should predict failure modes, teacher interventions, sequencing, and verification practices.", "The claim is a comparative heuristic and test protocol, not a metaphysical claim about what causes liberation."], "confidence": 0.74, "created_at": "2026-05-26T18:26:38-07:00", "cross_domain_prediction": {"domain": "Psychotherapy and behavior-change programs", "prediction": "Programs with the same custody assignment but different receiving surfaces will produce different dropout, resistance, and repair patterns. For example, therapist-guided treatments requiring exposure tolerance should fail and be repaired differently from therapist-guided treatments requiring cognitive insight or relational trust.", "structural_translation": "Custody becomes the assigned change agent: client agency, therapist, medication, group, protocol, exposure mechanism, sponsor, or higher power. Receiving surface becomes participant availability: insight, compliance, surrender, emotional exposure, behavioral rehearsal, trust, somatic tolerance, or relational openness.", "would_count_against_it": "If change-agent assignment, diagnosis, severity, therapeutic alliance, treatment dose, and social support explain dropout and repair patterns without an independent availability-mode variable."}, "exact_claim": "A contemplative path that weakens ordinary self-ownership needs both a custody architecture and a local human receiving surface. Custody names where transformation functions are assigned, such as causal process, hidden Self, teacher, vow, grace, community, ritual, God, or individual practitioner. Receiving surface names what must remain available in the practitioner, such as investigation, entrusting, recognition, loving attention, non-fabrication, or embodied presence. The strongest defensible version is a coding framework that tests whether receiving surface predicts failures, interventions, sequencing, and verification beyond custody assignment alone.", "execution_id": "dialogue-cf1bf0e51a293036", "falsifiable_predictions": [{"expected_observation": "Within the same custody class, such as vow-held, grace-held, or teacher-held paths, different receiving surfaces will correlate with different warning profiles and repair instructions. Entrusting failures should be repaired differently from recognition failures, investigation failures, or loving-attention failures.", "if_model_is_right": "Receiving surface is not reducible to custody assignment.", "test_surface": "Split-source blind coding of Pure Land, Christian contemplation, Dzogchen or Mahamudra, Theravada insight, and Advaita manuals, followed by practitioner interviews.", "would_weaken_or_falsify": "If custody assignment alone predicts warnings, sequencing, verification, and repairs as well as the two-variable model, receiving surface is redundant."}, {"expected_observation": "Recognition, entrusting, waiting, loving attention, non-fabrication, or investigation should appear in more than one custody grammar, while their risks shift according to custody.", "if_model_is_right": "The same receiving surface can appear under different custody systems.", "test_surface": "Matched primary-text pairs and inter-rater coding across traditions.", "would_weaken_or_falsify": "If each receiving surface is tradition-specific and never appears independently of one custody grammar, the model is a descriptive relabeling rather than a transferable structure."}, {"expected_observation": "Practitioners trained in investigation-heavy paths should show predictable difficulty entering entrusting, waiting, or non-fabricating paths, and the reverse should also occur, beyond doctrine, teacher style, temperament, and clinical-risk variables.", "if_model_is_right": "Receiving-surface mismatch predicts cross-training difficulty.", "test_surface": "Dual-practitioner interviews and preregistered coding of switching and hybrid-practice cases.", "would_weaken_or_falsify": "Smooth cross-training with no predictable mismatch pattern, or mismatch fully explained by social ecology, identity investment, trauma history, or teacher competence."}, {"expected_observation": "Manuals and teachers will correct how the practitioner investigates, entrusts, recognizes, waits, loves, relaxes, or embodies, even when the official custody claim remains stable.", "if_model_is_right": "Teacher interventions will target the receiving surface, not only belief about custody.", "test_surface": "Manual coding and teacher interviews asking for concrete failed-student cases and repair instructions.", "would_weaken_or_falsify": "If interventions mainly correct agency belief, ritual obedience, community conformity, or doctrinal interpretation without separable availability-mode corrections."}], "idea_id": "fd17456ae47234c8", "idea_path": "observations/codex/2026-05-26-custody-and-receiving-surface.md", "literature_search_queries": ["Pargament religion problem-solving self-directing deferring collaborative coping agency God practitioner", "Pure Land Other Power shinjin self-power calculation Tannisho entrusting vow", "Christian infused contemplation grace human receptivity loving attention spiritual direction", "Simone Weil attention prayer receptivity Waiting for God school studies", "Dzogchen Mahamudra pointing-out instruction recognition teacher readiness", "Varieties of Contemplative Experience meditation challenges teacher worldview influencing factors", "Lindbeck doctrine as grammar cultural linguistic rules practice", "Talal Asad discursive tradition correct form purpose practice authority", "Buddhist upaya skillful means capacity pedagogy practitioner needs", "Dogen Bendowa practice realization one no-threshold practice-realization"], "markdown_path": "reviews/originality/2026-05-26-custody-and-receiving-surface-255ec907071592a1.md", "near_neighbors": [{"difference": "The current idea gives the practitioner-side variable a clearer name, receiving surface, and proposes a direct separability test against custody assignment.", "novelty_impact": "Large reduction. Treat as consolidation and extension unless the receiving-surface variable shows independent predictive value beyond prior ledgers.", "overlap": "Extremely close. Prior Lumenary work already separates support locus, claimant rules, agency distribution, handoff timing, residue policy, operational capacity, training ecology, safeguards, failure modes, repairs, and verification.", "source": "Prior Lumenary records in prompt: Capacity Ledger, Forbidden Claimant Rubric, Credit Distribution, Handoff Point, Entry-Claimant Grammar, Claimability and Support Rubric, Continuity Ecology Under Negation, Operational Remainder Ecology"}, {"difference": "Pargament studies religious problem-solving and coping, not self-weakening contemplative paths with separate receiving-surface coding and verification practices.", "novelty_impact": "Moderate to large reduction. Custody assignment must be baseline-tested against religious coping and locus-of-control models.", "overlap": "Close for agency distribution across person and sacred power. Self-directing, deferring, and collaborative styles already code different relationships between individual action and divine control.", "source": "Pargament et al., Religion and the Problem-Solving Process: Three Styles of Coping, Journal for the Scientific Study of Religion, 1988, https://icmglt.org/icmlibrary/religion-and-the-problem-solving-process-three-styles-of-coping/"}, {"difference": "VCE is empirical and clinical-descriptive rather than a cross-tradition coding model for custody and receiving surface.", "novelty_impact": "Large reduction for failure-mode and intervention prediction. The candidate must prove added predictive value beyond VCE variables.", "overlap": "Very close for predicting difficulty from practitioner-level factors, practice-level factors, relationships, teachers, communities, worldviews, appraisals, and remedies.", "source": "Lindahl, Fisher, Cooper, Rosen, and Britton, The Varieties of Contemplative Experience, PLOS ONE, 2017, https://journals.plos.org/plosone/article?id=10.1371/journal.pone.0176239"}, {"difference": "It does not distinguish where transformation custody is assigned from what local availability the practitioner must maintain.", "novelty_impact": "Moderate reduction. Custody may partly rename worldview and appraisal unless it predicts more.", "overlap": "Close for the claim that worldview and interpretive framing can worsen, mitigate, or recontextualize contemplative difficulties.", "source": "Lindahl, Palitsky, Cooper, and Britton, The roles and impacts of worldviews in meditation-related challenges, 2023, https://pmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/articles/PMC11292974/"}, {"difference": "It does not build a cross-tradition taxonomy of custody holders and receiving surfaces.", "novelty_impact": "Moderate reduction. Teacher custody and intervention prediction are strongly anticipated.", "overlap": "Close for teacher-held guidance, teacher-student relationship, surrender, dependency, authority, and support during meditation-related challenges.", "source": "Britton et al., The Teacher Matters, Contemporary Buddhism, 2025, https://www.tandfonline.com/doi/full/10.1080/14639947.2025.2485677"}, {"difference": "The candidate narrows grammar into custody and receiving-surface fields and asks for predictive testing of warnings and repairs.", "novelty_impact": "Moderate reduction. The model may be a specialized coding workflow for Lindbeck-style rule theory.", "overlap": "Close for treating doctrine as rule-governed grammar that shapes speech, action, perception, and community life.", "source": "George Lindbeck, The Nature of Doctrine and doctrine-as-grammar discussions, summarized in St Andrews Encyclopaedia of Theology, https://www.saet.ac.uk/Christianity/TheologicalLanguage"}, {"difference": "Asad does not propose a comparative safety rubric for self-weakening contemplative practices.", "novelty_impact": "Moderate reduction for the authority, training, and practice-ecology components.", "overlap": "Close for locating religious practice in discursive traditions that teach correct form and purpose through authority, institutions, history, and power relations.", "source": "Talal Asad, The Idea of an Anthropology of Islam, https://voidnetwork.gr/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/The-Idea-of-an-Anthropology-of-Islam-by-Talal-Asad.pdf"}, {"difference": "The candidate tries to separate capacity-like receiving surface from custody assignment and support locus.", "novelty_impact": "Moderate reduction. Receiving surface may be renamed capacity pedagogy unless bounded and tested.", "overlap": "Close for adapting teaching and method to practitioner needs, capacities, stage, and risk of misunderstanding.", "source": "Buddhist upaya or skillful means literature, for example Encyclopedia of Buddhism, https://encyclopediaofbuddhism.org/wiki/Upaya-kaushalya"}, {"difference": "The candidate generalizes the structure across traditions and asks whether entrusting-like surfaces differ from custody itself.", "novelty_impact": "Large reduction for Pure Land examples. Novelty can only be comparative and predictive.", "overlap": "Very close for vow-held custody plus entrusting as the human-side interface. Self-power calculation already functions as a named failure mode.", "source": "Tannisho and Jodo Shinshu Other Power sources, https://bdk.or.jp/document/dgtl-dl/dBET_Tannisho-Ofumi_1996.pdf"}, {"difference": "Weil gives a Christian-philosophical account of attention and prayer, not a cross-tradition custody and failure-mode coding framework.", "novelty_impact": "Moderate reduction for the receiving-surface concept.", "overlap": "Very close for attention as a non-possessive, receptive human posture that is neither ordinary effort nor nothing. It anticipates receiving surface as availability.", "source": "Simone Weil, Reflections on the Right Use of School Studies with a View to the Love of God, https://www.themathesontrust.org/library/weil-reflections-on-the-right-use"}, {"difference": "The candidate compares recognition with entrusting, investigation, loving attention, non-fabrication, and embodied presence under one rubric.", "novelty_impact": "Moderate reduction. The recognition case is not new, but cross-case separability testing may add value.", "overlap": "Close for teacher-mediated recognition, readiness, recognition failure, and post-recognition stabilization.", "source": "Dzogchen and Mahamudra pointing-out instruction literature and practitioner-facing sources, for example https://vajrayana.tergar.org/course/dzogchen-three-words-immersion"}], "next_loop_instructions": ["Do not publish as doctrine. Treat as a comparative and practitioner-facing coding heuristic.", "Merge or cross-index with Capacity Ledger, Credit Distribution, Handoff Point, Entry-Claimant Grammar, Claimability and Support Rubric, Continuity Ecology Under Negation, and Operational Remainder Ecology unless separability testing proves independent value.", "Build a bounded coding sheet with fields for custody assignment, receiving surface, stage, failure mode, teacher intervention, sequencing, verification, evidence passage, analyst-frame refusal, and confidence.", "Add mandatory custody values: vow-held, grace-held, teacher-held, causal-process-held, community-held, ritual-held, hidden-Self-held, practitioner-held, practice-realization, inherited-practice, no-threshold, radical-other-power, no-custody-frame, and undecidable.", "Define receiving-surface values before further use: investigating, entrusting, recognizing, waiting, loving attention, non-fabricating, embodied presence, ritual participation, no-receiving-frame, analyst-frame-refused, and undecidable.", "Use split-source blind coding: code custody and receiving surface from entry or doctrinal texts, then predict warnings, safeguards, repairs, and verification from separate manuals or practitioner interviews.", "Compare predictive value against Pargament agency styles, Lindbeck grammar, Asad discursive tradition, VCE variables, upaya capacity pedagogy, grace theology, Other Power scholarship, pointing-out instruction literature, and prior Lumenary ledgers.", "Ask practitioners for concrete failed-student and repair cases, not agreement with the model.", "Do not raise above extended unless receiving surface adds predictive power beyond custody assignment, social ecology, teacher style, practitioner capacity, worldview, and clinical-risk variables."], "novelty_adjustment": "Reduce novelty from 0.77 to about 0.55. The idea is useful and testable, but most components are strongly anticipated by prior Lumenary ledgers, Pargament's religious coping styles, Lindbeck's doctrine-as-grammar, Asad's discursive tradition, VCE and teacher-factor research, upaya capacity pedagogy, Pure Land Other Power, Christian attention and grace theology, and pointing-out models. The remaining contribution is the explicit separability test between custody assignment and receiving surface.", "originality_status": "extended", "path": "reviews/originality/2026-05-26-custody-and-receiving-surface-255ec907071592a1.json", "practitioner_test": {"answers_that_reduce_originality": "Practitioners say this is standard pedagogy in new jargon: know who or what saves, trains, authorizes, or carries, know what the student must do or stop doing, and adjust instruction accordingly. They cannot name new predictions, repairs, or safeguards produced by the two-variable model.", "answers_that_support_contribution": "Practitioners identify concrete cases where agency locus and practitioner availability came apart, and they say the model would change screening, sequencing, repair, cross-training guidance, or stopping rules.", "questions": ["Is the distinction between custody and receiving surface obvious in your lineage, or does it change how you diagnose student failures?", "Can you name cases where the official agency holder was understood correctly, but the practitioner's receiving surface was wrong?", "Do your repair instructions target entrusting, recognition, investigation, waiting, loving attention, non-fabrication, or embodiment differently?", "Does this model predict any sequencing or safeguard you would not already derive from upaya, grace theology, Other Power teaching, spiritual direction, teacher experience, or adverse-effects research?", "Are there parts of your tradition where the language of custody or receiving surface distorts the practice?"], "relevant_practitioners": ["Jodo Shinshu ministers familiar with shinjin, Other Power, and non-calculation", "Christian contemplative directors familiar with grace, surrender, infused contemplation, loving attention, and discernment", "Dzogchen or Mahamudra teachers familiar with pointing-out, recognition, guru relation, and stabilization", "Theravada vipassana teachers familiar with investigation, noting, anatta, and progress maps", "Advaita Vedanta teachers familiar with self-inquiry, witness recognition, and neti-neti", "Soto Zen teachers familiar with shikantaza and practice-realization", "Contemplative clinicians and researchers familiar with meditation-related adverse effects"]}, "primary_text_close_read": {"primary_pair": ["Tannisho, BDK translation, especially chapters 1, 6, 8, 10, 11 and Rennyo postscript, https://bdk.or.jp/document/dgtl-dl/dBET_Tannisho-Ofumi_1996.pdf", "SN 22.59 Anatta-lakkhana Sutta, Thanissaro Bhikkhu translation, https://www.dhammatalks.org/suttas/SN/SN22_59.html", "Brihadaranyaka Upanishad 3.7.23, https://www.brhat.in/openlibrary/special/brihadaranyaka-upanishad/3-7-23 and https://vivekavani.com/bru3c7v23/", "Dogen, Bendowa practice-realization sources, for anomaly pressure, https://everydayzen.org/teachings/dogens-bendowa-part-2-of-3/"], "risk_of_overread": "High. The model can absorb nearly any tradition by assigning a custom custody holder and custom receiving surface. It also risks translating devotional, ritual, lineage, and metaphysical claims into systems vocabulary that practitioners may reject. The key circularity risk is using warnings and repairs both to infer receiving surface and to confirm that receiving surface predicts warnings and repairs.", "secondary_literature_gap": "This audit used accessible translations and open academic or practitioner-facing sources. It did not fully close-read Shinran's Kyogyoshinsho, Dogen scholarship, Dzogchen or Mahamudra manuals, John of the Cross, Teresa of Avila, Christian grace controversy sources, or Sanskrit, Pali, Japanese, Tibetan, and Latin originals. It also did not run practitioner interviews. Novelty should not rise without split-source coding and interview evidence.", "structural_observation": "Tannisho strongly supports vow-held custody: Amida's vow carries salvific efficacy and self-power calculation is treated as deviation. Yet it still requires hearing, entrusting, teacher lineage, and restricted readiness, so a receiving surface remains visible. SN 22.59 negates ownership and mastery over the aggregates, but the discourse still depends on instruction, discernment, memory, and seeing with right understanding, so causal-process custody does not eliminate local investigation. Brihadaranyaka 3.7.23 gives the opposite residue policy: ordinary objectification fails, but the hidden knower or inner controller is authorized as the remainder. Dogen's practice-realization strains the model because practice and realization are not cleanly separable stages, making custody and receiving surface look like an analyst-imposed split. These primary texts support the distinction as a useful coding question, but not as a proven independent structure."}, "recommended_scores": {"counterargument_quality": 0.91, "novelty": 0.55, "source_reliability": 0.77}, "run_ids": [], "title": "Custody and Receiving Surface", "unlike_statement": "Unlike Pargament's agency styles, Lindbeck's doctrine-as-grammar, Asad's discursive tradition, VCE adverse-effects research, upaya capacity pedagogy, Pure Land Other Power, Christian attention and grace theology, pointing-out instruction, and prior Lumenary ledgers, this idea says that the assigned holder of transformation and the practitioner's required mode of availability should be coded separately, then tested to see whether the second variable predicts warnings, sequencing, teacher repairs, and verification beyond the first."}
reviews/originality/audits.jsonl:38:{"agent": "codex", "anomaly_probe": {"anomaly_candidate": "Dogen practice-realization identity, radical Other Power in Tannisho, inherited communal religion, and apophatic refusal in Dionysius.", "confidence_effect": "Lowers confidence from candidate discovery to extended. The model needs mandatory no-threshold, practice-realization, radical Other Power, inherited continuity, apophatic refusal, no-custody-frame, continuous authorization, and analyst-frame-refused values.", "why_it_breaks_or_strains_model": "Dogen removes the gap between method and result, so there may be no threshold where boundary and custody can be assigned. Tannisho places decisive working in Amida's vow while warning against self-calculation, so calling entrusting a local custody handoff can reintroduce the self-power frame the text resists. Inherited religion may mature by continuity and ritual participation rather than by a discernible handoff. Dionysius places the divine Cause beyond affirmation and negation, which destabilizes God as a simple custody recipient."}, "audit_id": "c79517a2a7daa9cc", "claim_units": ["Self-weakening contemplative practice creates a threshold where ordinary ownership of attention and authority is weakened.", "Boundary operation is a variable: the method may validate itself, undermine itself, become irrelevant, or need another value such as practice-realization identity.", "Custody rule is a variable: freed attention or authority may be assigned to no owner, Self, God, teacher, lineage, vow, conduct, Prajnaparamita, embodied responsiveness, or no custody frame.", "The interaction of boundary operation and custody rule may predict verification architecture, teaching strategy, and reentry better than doctrine, boundary alone, or custody alone.", "The claim must be tested by independent coding, not inferred from the same passages used to confirm predictions."], "confidence": 0.77, "created_at": "2026-05-26T20:53:53-07:00", "cross_domain_prediction": {"domain": "Psychotherapy, clinical supervision, and professional formation.", "prediction": "Training systems that alter identity or attention should show distinct termination, supervision, relapse, and ethical-reentry patterns based on the interaction between method-boundary and custody. For example, a protocol that is later internalized should differ from one that is explicitly released, and both should differ when responsibility is held by client values, supervisor authority, group accountability, or professional ethics.", "structural_translation": "Boundary operation becomes how a method treats itself at maturity: retained protocol, self-undermining tool, embodied skill, or practice-identity. Custody rule becomes where authority and responsibility move after change: client agency, therapist, supervisor, group, protocol, medication, values, professional ethics, or embodied responsiveness.", "would_count_against_it": "If outcomes, supervision failures, termination protocols, and ethical repairs are predicted just as well by diagnosis, alliance, institution policy, practitioner experience, or generic risk management, with no added value from boundary-custody interaction."}, "exact_claim": "When contemplative practice weakens ordinary self-ownership of attention and authority, two candidate variables shape what follows: boundary operation and custody rule. Boundary operation asks whether the method validates itself, undermines itself, or becomes irrelevant as the practitioner matures beyond method-talk. Custody rule asks where freed attention and authority may belong afterward: no owner, hidden Self, God, teacher, lineage, vow, conduct, Prajnaparamita, or embodied responsiveness. Their interaction may predict verification architecture, teaching strategy, and reentry more precisely than doctrinal content, boundary operation alone, or custody alone.", "execution_id": "dialogue-b606b887e2f0fff3", "falsifiable_predictions": [{"expected_observation": "Split-source coders who code boundary operation from one corpus and custody rule from another should predict held-out verification signs, teaching permission, warning profiles, and reentry disciplines above tradition-label, doctrine-only, boundary-only, and custody-only baselines.", "if_model_is_right": "Boundary operation and custody rule interact rather than merely adding two descriptive labels.", "test_surface": "Pre-registered coding of Advaita, Theravada, Rinzai, Soto, Dzogchen or Mahamudra, Jodo Shinshu, Christian apophatic practice, and Sufi fana or baqa sources.", "would_weaken_or_falsify": "The interaction term adds no predictive power, or the same predictions are explained by institution type, teacher style, stage sequence, social ecology, or clinical-risk variables."}, {"expected_observation": "Cases with similar boundary cancellation but different custody rules, such as Heart Sutra reliance, Eckhartian Gelassenheit, and Madhyamaka non-positioning, should diverge in verification and reentry. Cases with similar vow or grace custody but different boundary operations should diverge in method retention and warning style.", "if_model_is_right": "Pairs sharing one axis but differing on the other should diverge predictably.", "test_surface": "Matched primary-text pairs and held-out manuals, plus blind clustering against coded outcomes.", "would_weaken_or_falsify": "Pairs cluster mainly by broad tradition, institution, genre, teacher lineage, or language family rather than by boundary-custody pairing."}, {"expected_observation": "Teachers should report concrete cases where the boundary operation was understood but custody was misassigned, or custody was understood but the method-boundary was mishandled, and they should prescribe different repairs for each.", "if_model_is_right": "The variables are observable to practitioners as actual repair distinctions, not just analyst vocabulary.", "test_surface": "Structured interviews with teachers and senior practitioners, asking for failed-student and cross-training cases rather than agreement with the theory.", "would_weaken_or_falsify": "Practitioners say the distinction is standard lineage discernment with new labels, or cannot name any repair that differs from ordinary pedagogy, upaya, grace, vow, or supervision."}, {"expected_observation": "Independent coders should reach acceptable agreement on boundary operation, custody rule, stage, source layer, and analyst-frame refusal before seeing warnings, verification, and repair passages.", "if_model_is_right": "The model can be coded reliably before outcome inspection.", "test_surface": "Inter-rater reliability trial using redacted entry, instruction, completion, and authorization passages.", "would_weaken_or_falsify": "Coders cannot distinguish boundary from custody, or agreement appears only after outcome passages are revealed."}], "idea_id": "41eccaa10cea51c9", "idea_path": "observations/codex/2026-05-26-boundary-and-custody-at-the-threshold.md", "literature_search_queries": ["contemplative practice authorization transmission teacher recognition realization conduct verification authority comparative mysticism", "Talal Asad discursive tradition authorized practice correct form purpose religion authority", "Robert Sharf Buddhist Modernism rhetoric meditative experience final experience authority PDF", "G. Victor Sogen Hori Koan and Kensho in the Rinzai Zen Curriculum teacher testing", "George Lindbeck doctrine as grammar cultural linguistic rule theory", "Varieties of Contemplative Experience influencing factors teacher community practice worldview", "Pargament religion problem-solving self-directing deferring collaborative coping agency God practitioner", "Dogen practice realization verification Genjokoan Bendowa", "Heart Sutra no attainment relying on Prajnaparamita", "Tannisho Other Power Original Vow no practice no good teacher maturity faith"], "markdown_path": "reviews/originality/2026-05-26-boundary-and-custody-at-the-threshold-c79517a2a7daa9cc.md", "near_neighbors": [{"difference": "The current idea adds custody rule as a second axis beside boundary operation.", "novelty_impact": "Very high reduction. This should be cross-indexed with authority-boundary work rather than published as a standalone discovery.", "overlap": "Very close. It already says to establish native authority-boundaries, then test whether reflexive operations predict authorization, transmission, teaching strategy, and ethical reentry beyond doctrine and tradition membership.", "source": "Prior Lumenary audit, Authority-Boundary Ecology, reviews/originality/2026-05-26-authority-boundary-ecology-0739a5567c106853.json, and dialogue Can native verification or authority boundaries be identified non-circularly, findings/convergences/2026-05-26-can-native-verification-or-authority-boundaries-be-identified-non-circularly-acro.md"}, {"difference": "The current idea links custody to method-boundary operation instead of treating it primarily as a post-negation or receiving-surface variable.", "novelty_impact": "High reduction. The surviving contribution is an interaction test between two already developed Lumenary variables.", "overlap": "Very close. These records already code where loosened attention, agency, and transformation functions are held, and whether practitioner-side availability predicts warnings, repairs, sequencing, and verification.", "source": "Prior Lumenary audits, The Custody of Unclaimed Attention and Custody and Receiving Surface, reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-custody-of-unclaimed-attention-65ed649d8eab67cd.json and reviews/originality/2026-05-26-custody-and-receiving-surface-255ec907071592a1.json"}, {"difference": "Asad is not specifically modeling contemplative threshold operations or custody of freed attention.", "novelty_impact": "High reduction for the authority-first and native-practice-first move.", "overlap": "Close structural prior. Asad's discursive tradition foregrounds authorized instruction about correct practice, tradition, power, and the regulation of proper performance.", "source": "Talal Asad, The Idea of an Anthropology of Islam, https://voidnetwork.gr/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/The-Idea-of-an-Anthropology-of-Islam-by-Talal-Asad.pdf"}, {"difference": "The candidate operationalizes a narrower threshold codebook for boundary, custody, verification, and reentry.", "novelty_impact": "Moderate to high reduction. The model may be a specialized comparative workflow for doctrine-as-grammar.", "overlap": "Close. Lindbeck already treats doctrine as a grammar that shapes religious speech, perception, action, and communal rules.", "source": "George Lindbeck, doctrine as grammar and cultural-linguistic rule theory, overview at https://www.saet.ac.uk/Christianity/TheologicalLanguage"}, {"difference": "Sharf does not offer a boundary-custody interaction test.", "novelty_impact": "High reduction against treating the threshold as a direct phenomenological fact.", "overlap": "Close pressure source. Sharf challenges the use of private meditative experience as a stable comparative unit and emphasizes rhetoric, institution, and authority around experience claims.", "source": "Robert H. Sharf, Buddhist Modernism and the Rhetoric of Meditative Experience, DeepBlue record, https://deepblue.lib.umich.edu/items/25b7e9d4-d1f3-4280-8d53-95fa0b53db5c"}, {"difference": "It is not a cross-tradition two-axis model.", "novelty_impact": "High reduction for Zen evidence and for any claim that verification architecture is newly noticed.", "overlap": "Close single-tradition prior. Hori shows ritual formalism and mystical insight working together in Rinzai training, which anticipates the link between method, testing, teacher authority, and transmission.", "source": "G. Victor Sogen Hori, Teaching and learning in the Rinzai Zen monastery, Cambridge record, https://www.cambridge.org/core/books/abs/teaching-and-learning-in-japan/teaching-and-learning-in-the-rinzai-zen-monastery/06E010651A6042E1FF3EC9BE242460D9"}, {"difference": "Pargament studies coping and God-related agency, not contemplative boundary operations after self-weakening practice.", "novelty_impact": "Moderate reduction. Custody rules need baseline comparison against established religious agency models.", "overlap": "Close for agency and custody distribution across human and divine roles: self-directing, deferring, and collaborative patterns already formalize different responsibility allocations.", "source": "Pargament et al., Religion and the Problem-Solving Process: Three Styles of Coping, accessible summary, https://icmglt.org/icmlibrary/religion-and-the-problem-solving-process-three-styles-of-coping/"}, {"difference": "VCE does not isolate boundary operation plus custody rule as an interaction predicting verification and reentry.", "novelty_impact": "High methodological reduction. The candidate must outperform VCE-style multidimensional coding.", "overlap": "Close methodological prior. VCE separates phenomenology, interpretation, teacher and community factors, practice factors, remedies, impairment, and integration.", "source": "Lindahl et al., The Varieties of Contemplative Experience, PLOS ONE, https://journals.plos.org/plosone/article?id=10.1371/journal.pone.0176239"}, {"difference": "The text is not a general comparative taxonomy and does not add custody recipients beyond the Dhamma's proper use.", "novelty_impact": "High reduction for the method-validates-then-releases structure.", "overlap": "Very close primary-text prior for boundary operation. The method is useful for crossing but not for holding onto afterward.", "source": "MN 22 Alagaddupama Sutta, raft simile, https://www.dhammatalks.org/suttas/MN/MN22.html"}, {"difference": "The candidate generalizes the pattern and asks whether it predicts verification and reentry across traditions.", "novelty_impact": "High reduction and a key anomaly against simple boundary categories.", "overlap": "Very close primary-text prior for cancellation plus retained custody: no attainment, yet reliance on Prajnaparamita remains operative.", "source": "Heart Sutra, no attainment and reliance on Prajnaparamita, https://rctbt.org/heartsutra/"}], "next_loop_instructions": ["Do not publish as doctrine or standalone candidate discovery. Cross-index with The Method's Reckoning, The Custody of Unclaimed Attention, Authority-Boundary Ecology, Custody and Receiving Surface, Claimability and Support Rubric, and Operational Remainder Ecology.", "Rename the contribution as a test protocol: boundary-custody interaction coding at contemplative thresholds.", "Build a pre-registered codebook with fields for source layer, stage, native authorization unit, boundary operation, custody rule, verification sign, teaching permission, reentry rule, warning, repair, evidence passage, analyst-frame refusal, and confidence.", "Do not let the same passage code boundary, custody, and the predicted warning or repair. Use split-source or held-out coding.", "Add mandatory values for no-threshold, practice-realization, retained method, released method, self-undermining method, embodied method, radical Other Power, vow-held, grace-held, teacher-held, conduct-held, community-held, Prajnaparamita-held, no-custody-frame, continuous authorization, inherited practice, apophatic refusal, and undecidable.", "Compare predictive value against Asad discursive tradition, Lindbeck grammar, Weberian authority, Sharf and Katz contextualism, Pargament agency styles, upaya pedagogy, VCE variables, institution type, teacher style, social ecology, clinical risk, and prior Lumenary ledgers.", "Run inter-rater reliability before public use. If coders cannot distinguish boundary operation from custody rule without outcome passages, downgrade the model to interpretive vocabulary.", "Close-read MN 22, Heart Sutra, Dogen Genjokoan or Bendowa, Tannisho, Cloud of Unknowing, Dionysius Mystical Theology, one Dzogchen or Mahamudra pointing-out source, and one Sufi fana or baqa source before further scoring.", "Interview practitioners for concrete failed-student, cross-training, premature-teaching, and reentry repair cases, not abstract agreement with the model.", "Do not raise above extended unless the boundary-custody interaction predicts held-out warnings, verification, teaching permission, or repair better than boundary alone, custody alone, doctrine, stage, institution, teacher style, and social ecology."], "novelty_adjustment": "Reduce novelty from 0.82 to about 0.42. The exact language is fresh, but both axes and much of the predictive burden are already present in prior Lumenary records: Method's Reckoning, Custody of Unclaimed Attention, Authority-Boundary Ecology, Custody and Receiving Surface, and related entry and support ledgers. External prior art also strongly anticipates the components: Asad and Lindbeck for native authority and grammar, Sharf and Katz-style contextualism for suspicion of experience-first comparison, Hori for Zen training and verification, Pargament for agency distribution, VCE for multidimensional contemplative difficulty coding, MN 22 for validated-then-released method, Heart Sutra for no-attainment plus reliance, Tannisho for Other Power custody, and Dogen for practice-realization anomaly. The surviving value is a bounded split-source interaction test, not a doctrine candidate or strong original discovery.", "originality_status": "extended", "path": "reviews/originality/2026-05-26-boundary-and-custody-at-the-threshold-c79517a2a7daa9cc.json", "practitioner_test": {"answers_that_reduce_originality": "Practitioners say the model is obvious lineage pedagogy, spiritual direction, vow theology, grace doctrine, upaya, teacher authorization, or religious coping language. They cannot identify repairs or predictions that differ from existing training judgments, or they reject custody and threshold as distorting terms.", "answers_that_support_contribution": "Practitioners identify non-obvious failure cases where boundary alone and custody alone mispredict the repair, while the interaction predicts the actual warning, support holder, verification sign, or reentry discipline before tradition label or teacher preference is revealed.", "questions": ["Is boundary operation plus custody rule more than standard lineage authorization, upaya, grace and effort, doctrine-as-grammar, or religious coping in new terms?", "Can you give a concrete case where a student understood the method but misplaced the custody of attention or authority afterward?", "Can you give a concrete case where a student accepted the custody rule but mishandled whether the method should be retained, released, undermined, or embodied?", "Would this model change screening, sequencing, warning, verification, teaching permission, or repair in your tradition?"], "relevant_practitioners": ["Rinzai Zen teachers familiar with koan curriculum and transmission", "Soto Zen teachers familiar with Dogen practice-realization", "Jodo Shinshu ministers familiar with Other Power and shinjin", "Theravada insight teachers familiar with anatta and relinquishment", "Advaita Vedanta teachers familiar with self-inquiry and witness language", "Dzogchen or Mahamudra teachers familiar with direct introduction and stabilization", "Christian apophatic spiritual directors", "Sufi teachers familiar with fana, baqa, and ijaza", "Contemplative science researchers familiar with VCE and meditation-related challenges", "Psychologists of religion familiar with Pargament's agency and coping work"]}, "primary_text_close_read": {"primary_pair": ["MN 22 Alagaddupama Sutta, raft simile, Thanissaro Bhikkhu translation, https://www.dhammatalks.org/suttas/MN/MN22.html", "Heart Sutra interactive Sanskrit, Chinese, English corpus, no attainment and reliance on Prajnaparamita, https://rctbt.org/heartsutra/", "Dogen, Genjokoan, Shohaku Okumura translation, https://brightwayzen.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/For-BWZ-Chant-Book-Genjokoan.pdf", "Tannisho, BDK English Tripitaka translation, https://bdk.or.jp/document/dgtl-dl/dBET_Tannisho-Ofumi_1996.pdf"], "risk_of_overread": "High. The model can become circular if boundary, custody, verification, and reentry are inferred from the same passage. It can also translate salvation, liberation, grace, lineage, conduct, and ritual into a modern governance vocabulary of attention and authority. Some traditions may refuse the threshold frame, especially Dogen practice-realization, inherited religion, radical Other Power, apophatic predication refusal, and traditions where authorization is political, communal, sacramental, or continuous rather than contemplative.", "secondary_literature_gap": "The audit used accessible primary translations, local Lumenary audits and dialogues, open academic records, and practitioner-facing sources. It did not read Japanese, Sanskrit, Pali, Tibetan, Greek, Arabic, or Latin originals, and it did not interview teachers. Further work should read Asad, Lindbeck, Weber, Sharf, Hori, Sells, Pargament, VCE research, Dogen scholarship, Pure Land scholarship, and apophatic theology in greater depth before any stronger novelty claim.", "structural_observation": "The primary texts partly support the model but mostly lower novelty. MN 22 already gives a boundary operation in which the Dhamma is valid for crossing and then not to be grasped, so method validation and method release are staged together. The Heart Sutra negates attainment but preserves reliance on Prajnaparamita, which is almost an exact prior structure for boundary cancellation plus retained custody. Tannisho relocates efficacy to Amida's Original Vow, denies self-powered merit, rejects teacher ownership, and restricts reading to those mature in faith, so custody, verification, and warning are already internally linked. Dogen strains the whole threshold premise: practice-enlightenment and verification by all things collapse the gap between method and completion, making boundary and custody look less like two variables and more like an analyst's grid imposed on a no-threshold practice field."}, "recommended_scores": {"counterargument_quality": 0.93, "novelty": 0.42, "source_reliability": 0.8}, "run_ids": [], "title": "Boundary And Custody At The Threshold", "unlike_statement": "Unlike Asad, Lindbeck, Sharf, Hori, Pargament, VCE research, MN 22, the Heart Sutra, and prior Lumenary authority and custody ledgers, this idea's surviving distinct claim is a narrow interaction protocol: code boundary operation and custody rule independently, then test whether their interaction predicts held-out verification, teaching permission, warning, repair, and reentry patterns better than doctrine, tradition label, stage, institution, boundary alone, or custody alone. Without that split-source predictive gain, it is mostly a consolidation of prior work."}
reviews/originality/audits.jsonl:84:{"agent": "claude", "anomaly_probe": {"anomaly_candidate": "A person with strong external supports collapses more severely because those supports are coercive, shaming, unreliable, or tied to performance, while a strongly self-directed person recovers faster through restored agency, sleep, treatment, and practical problem solving.", "confidence_effect": "Keeps the status at extended and lowers practice confidence until support quality, agency history, clinical risk, and event magnitude are coded separately from continuity location.", "why_it_breaks_or_strains_model": "The model assumes externalized holding is protective for the target cohort. If support safety and agency restoration matter more than support location, the core variable is not where continuity sits but whether the holder is trustworthy, noncoercive, and actually available. This also catches the non-fit case: people harmed by denied agency may be injured by surrender language."}, "audit_id": "e30798c2dedf5eaa", "claim_units": ["Continuity can be located in self-command, body, routines, relationships, duty, faith, vows, or community.", "Performance-owned continuity should predict more total destabilization when performance fails.", "The useful intervention is preventative relocation of some steadiness outside self-command, not post-collapse control rebuilding.", "The broad comparative continuity rubric is already duplicated inside Lumenary and in external literature.", "No-gap teachings strain the continuity-across-a-threshold frame because there is no gap to carry continuity across.", "The human-condition fit is narrow: achievement-contingent self-worth and burnout collapse, not denied agency, abuse, acute crisis, or severe clinical distress."], "confidence": 0.78, "created_at": "2026-05-30T14:03:30+02:00", "cross_domain_prediction": {"domain": "Organizational resilience and knowledge work", "prediction": "Teams, families, or care systems with distributed continuity before a disruption will recover faster and with less identity crisis than systems held mainly by one heroic performer, after controlling for disruption size and resources.", "structural_translation": "A system whose continuity is held by one performative node collapses harder when that node fails than a system whose continuity is distributed across routines, documentation, relationships, backups, and role redundancy.", "would_count_against_it": "Event magnitude, funding, staffing, and prior load explain recovery completely, and pre-break continuity distribution adds no measurable predictive value."}, "exact_claim": "For people whose steadiness and worth were held mostly by performance and self-command, collapse should be more total than for people whose continuity already lived partly in body, relationship, routine, duty, faith, or recovery support. The broad comparative claim about continuity after self-negation is old and overbuilt. The defensible contribution is a narrow person-level prediction plus a boundary condition: no-gap paths such as Dogen-style practice-realization should not be forced into a carry-across-a-threshold model.", "execution_id": "parallel-20260530-135009-20260530-135009", "falsifiable_predictions": [{"expected_observation": "Among people recovering from burnout, grief, caregiving overload, or early addiction recovery, those whose steadiness was mostly performance-owned should report more total destabilization than matched peers whose steadiness was distributed across relationships, routines, body, faith, duty, or recovery groups.", "if_model_is_right": "Pre-collapse continuity location is a real vulnerability variable.", "test_surface": "Prospective or retrospective coded interviews with burnout clinicians, recovery sponsors, chaplains, caregivers, founders, and high-achieving professionals.", "would_weaken_or_falsify": "Collapse severity is fully explained by sleep loss, trauma history, event magnitude, financial precarity, clinical diagnosis, and support quality, with no independent effect for continuity location."}, {"expected_observation": "Screened high-achievement participants using the practice for two weeks show reduced self-worth conversion, less grip, more concrete help-seeking or routine use, and no increase in helplessness or guilt compared with ordinary rest-and-ask-for-help and planning prompts.", "if_model_is_right": "The practice Name What Carries You addresses the named wound better than generic reflection.", "test_surface": "Small randomized pilot with achievement-contingent self-worth, burnout, rumination, help-seeking, shame, action completion, and adverse-effect measures.", "would_weaken_or_falsify": "The practice increases dependency, guilt, helplessness, self-monitoring, avoidance, or performs no better than ordinary social support and rest."}, {"expected_observation": "Dogen, Huangbo, and Dzogchen direct-recognition sources should not describe continuity as something carried across a before-after threshold; they should emphasize present practice, direct recognition, or search refusal instead.", "if_model_is_right": "The no-gap boundary is real.", "test_surface": "Split-source close reading of Bendowa, Genjokoan or Uji, Huangbo transmission texts, one Dzogchen or Mahamudra pointing-out manual, and practitioner interviews.", "would_weaken_or_falsify": "Close reading finds robust threshold-carry language in no-gap sources, or practitioners report that continuity migration is a native teaching in those settings."}, {"expected_observation": "Blind readers can state the added variables: pre-collapse continuity location, collapse severity, and no-gap exclusion.", "if_model_is_right": "The new claim is distinguishable from the prior continuity cluster.", "test_surface": "Blind distinct-content coding of recent Lumenary continuity and support-holder records with titles removed.", "would_weaken_or_falsify": "Blind readers cannot distinguish this record from Continuity Ecology Under Negation, Operational Remainder Ecology, Custody and Receiving Surface, or Some Help Should Not Be Managed."}], "idea_id": "84b6d1547156a7e8", "idea_path": "observations/claude/2026-05-30-what-holds-you-that-you-did-not-build.md", "literature_search_queries": ["Pargament religious coping deferring collaborative self-directing coping styles", "Jack Engler you have to be somebody before you can be nobody spirituality psychology", "Clark Chalmers extended mind religious cognition Krueger religious cognition extended mind", "SN 45.8 Magga vibhanga right effort desire persistence intent translation", "Shinran Tannisho Other Power self power divergence teacher correction", "Dogen Bendowa practice realization shusho itto no gap practice realization one", "attachment theory secure base stress regulation social support review Bowlby secure base", "Linville self-complexity buffer stress depression mixed support", "Crocker Wolfe contingencies of self-worth achievement failure self-esteem", "Alcoholics Anonymous Twelve Steps power greater than ourselves social support recovery"], "markdown_path": "reviews/originality/2026-05-30-what-holds-you-that-you-did-not-build-e30798c2dedf5eaa.md", "near_neighbors": [{"difference": "This candidate narrows the ambition to one person-level prediction about pre-collapse continuity location and adds a no-gap exclusion test.", "novelty_impact": "Major downgrade. Treat as an extension and consolidation unless the collapse-severity prediction shows independent value.", "overlap": "Very close. The same variables recur: dissolution target, residue policy, support holder, receiving surface, failure mode, and a warning that the model is too elastic without split-source coding.", "source": "Internal Lumenary continuity cluster: Continuity Ecology Under Negation, Distributed Continuity Architecture, Continuity Location Under Transformative Practice, Operational Remainder Ecology, Custody and Receiving Surface, plus the candidate file observations/claude/2026-05-30-what-holds-you-that-you-did-not-build.md"}, {"difference": "The candidate widens the holder set beyond God to body, routine, relationship, duty, and prior promises, and predicts collapse severity in performance-owned lives.", "novelty_impact": "Strong reduction for support-locus originality, partial preservation for the burnout-specific prediction.", "overlap": "Very close on responsibility location. Self-directing, deferring, and collaborative coping already code whether the person, God, or a shared relation carries problem-solving.", "source": "Pargament et al., Religion and the Problem-Solving Process: Three Styles of Coping, 1988, indexed at https://icmglt.org/icmlibrary/religion-and-the-problem-solving-process-three-styles-of-coping/ and https://www.kennethpargament.com/rs-coping-measures-dev-gen-rel"}, {"difference": "The candidate translates extension into collapse vulnerability and practice design for achievement-contingent self-worth.", "novelty_impact": "Moderate to strong downgrade. The external-holder ontology is known; the practice-fit and collapse prediction are the local extension.", "overlap": "Close. External artifacts, language, culture, ritual, sacred spaces, songs, relics, and other persons can be part of cognition or religious cognition rather than merely background aids.", "source": "Clark and Chalmers, The Extended Mind, https://consc.net/papers/extended.html, and Joel Krueger, Extended Mind and Religious Cognition, https://philarchive.org/rec/KRUTEM-2"}, {"difference": "The candidate is not merely about attachment figures. It includes bodily rhythms, routines, vows, duties, faith, and recovery supports, and it asks about performance collapse.", "novelty_impact": "Strong reduction for the human kernel that steadiness is partly externally supported.", "overlap": "Close. A person's exploration and stress regulation are supported by reliable others who provide a safe haven and secure base.", "source": "Attachment secure-base literature, for example Feeney and Thrush on secure base support in adulthood, https://pmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/articles/PMC2805473/, and Bowlby secure-base tradition indexed in attachment literature"}, {"difference": "The candidate targets non-addiction performance collapse and asks where continuity sat before the break, not only how recovery is held after admission of powerlessness.", "novelty_impact": "Major downgrade for surrender and externalized holding; partial novelty remains only if the pre-collapse-location measure predicts severity.", "overlap": "Close practitioner near-neighbor. AA explicitly externalizes recovery through a higher power, another human being, inventory, amends, service, meetings, and sponsorship-like community structures.", "source": "Alcoholics Anonymous official Twelve Steps, https://www.aa.org/the-twelve-steps, and AA social-network support literature such as https://pmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/articles/PMC2289871/"}, {"difference": "The candidate adds a continuity-location and collapse-severity hypothesis rather than only self-esteem contingency or perfectionism trend.", "novelty_impact": "Moderate downgrade. The wound is known; the proposed holder-map may be a useful practice-specific operationalization.", "overlap": "Close on the target wound. Self-worth can depend on success, achievement, approval, competition, appearance, family support, virtue, or divine love; perfectionism links self-worth to achievement and harsh evaluation.", "source": "Crocker and Wolfe contingencies of self-worth, summarized and tested in https://link.springer.com/article/10.1007/s12144-020-01007-5, and Curran and Hill on rising perfectionism, https://eprints.lse.ac.uk/101352/1/Curran_Hill2018.pdf"}, {"difference": "The candidate uses Dogen not as support but as a boundary condition against overgeneralized continuity-across-threshold models.", "novelty_impact": "Useful boundary, but not a discovery. It prevents overreach more than it creates a new doctrine.", "overlap": "The no-gap anomaly is not new. Practice-realization unity is a known Soto Zen frame, and the literature already resists treating practice as a means to a later result.", "source": "Dogen shusho itto and Bendowa materials, https://global.sotozen-net.or.jp/eng/library/key_terms/pdf/key_terms07.pdf and https://afe.easia.columbia.edu/ps/japan/dogen.pdf"}], "next_loop_instructions": ["Do not publish as a standalone discovery. Cross-index with Continuity Ecology Under Negation, Operational Remainder Ecology, Custody and Receiving Surface, Some Help Should Not Be Managed, and Keep What Can Correct You.", "Build a bounded codebook with fields for pre-collapse continuity locus, support quality, agency history, collapse severity, clinical risk, event magnitude, sleep, trauma history, and repair path.", "Run the blind distinct-content test on the continuity cluster before generating another support-holder rubric.", "Close-read Dogen, Huangbo, Dzogchen, Shinran, and SN 45.8 for threshold-carry language versus present-act, vow-held, or effort-held language.", "Pilot Name What Carries You only with screened stable high performers and caregivers. Compare against ordinary rest, social support, and planning prompts.", "Add explicit stop rules for denied agency, coercion, spiritual abuse, severe depression, mania, psychosis, addiction withdrawal, acute crisis, and cases where no real support is available."], "novelty_adjustment": "Lower novelty from 0.42 to 0.36. The broad structure is known through internal Lumenary rubrics, Pargament, extended mind, secure-base theory, AA, and self-worth research. Keep as an extended, testable person-level hypothesis only if pre-collapse continuity location and the no-gap exclusion add predictive power.", "originality_status": "extended", "path": "reviews/originality/2026-05-30-what-holds-you-that-you-did-not-build-e30798c2dedf5eaa.json", "practitioner_test": {"answers_that_reduce_originality": "Originality falls if clinicians and practitioners say the useful part is standard social support, secure-base work, recovery surrender, religious coping, self-complexity, or self-worth contingency work, and if the continuity-location code adds no prediction beyond support quality and clinical risk.", "answers_that_support_contribution": "Support rises if practitioners can code pre-collapse continuity location reliably, if that code predicts severity or repair beyond ordinary supports, and if no-gap teachers confirm that the carry-across-threshold model is a category error in their setting.", "questions": ["In concrete collapse cases, do people whose identity was mainly performance-held collapse more totally than people whose continuity was already distributed?", "Is this just secure-base theory, religious coping, recovery surrender, and contingencies of self-worth in new language?", "Would the practice change what you recommend, or would ordinary rest, social support, therapy, and asking for help do the same work?", "Can you name cases where leaning on what the person did not build increased dependency, shame, helplessness, or exposure to unsafe authority?", "Do no-gap traditions you know reject the carry-across-threshold frame, or do they have native language for continuity being held across a shift?"], "relevant_practitioners": ["burnout clinicians", "occupational health researchers", "addiction recovery sponsors", "chaplains and pastoral caregivers", "Jodo Shinshu teachers or scholars", "Soto Zen teachers or scholars", "Theravada teachers", "attachment researchers", "perfectionism and self-worth researchers", "caregiver support practitioners"]}, "primary_text_close_read": {"primary_pair": ["Shinran, Tannisho, especially chapters 1, 3, 6, 8, and 11, https://jodoshinshu.faith/tannisho-a-record-in-lament-of-divergences/, read against SN 45.8 Magga-vibhanga Sutta, https://www.accesstoinsight.org/tipitaka/sn/sn45/sn45.008.than.html", "Dogen practice-realization as anomaly, using Bendowa excerpt https://afe.easia.columbia.edu/ps/japan/dogen.pdf and Soto Zen shusho itto note https://global.sotozen-net.or.jp/eng/library/key_terms/pdf/key_terms07.pdf"], "risk_of_overread": "Moderate to high. Shinran's Vow is not merely psychological support, and SN 45.8 right effort is not simple self-command. The no-gap boundary could become too elastic if analysts say practice itself holds continuity in every case. Human-condition fit is real but narrow: it may help stable high performers, founders, caregivers, and perfectionists, but it can harm people whose wound is denied agency, coercive dependence, abusive religion, acute crisis, severe depression, mania, psychosis, addiction withdrawal, or lack of actual support.", "secondary_literature_gap": "Before any stronger novelty claim, read Shinran scholarship on Other Power, hakarai, jinen, and Tannisho transmission; Dogen scholarship on shusho itto and honsho myoshu; Engler on self development before no-self work; Bowlby, Ainsworth, and adult secure-base literature; Linville and later mixed findings on self-complexity as a stress buffer; Crocker and Wolfe on contingencies of self-worth; Pargament on religious coping; AA social-network outcome literature; burnout and perfectionism studies; and practitioner-facing recovery and chaplaincy sources.", "structural_observation": "Tannisho relocates decisive efficacy away from self-powered practice and into Amida's Vow, while still preserving teacher, transmission, and warnings against divergent interpretation. SN 45.8 defines right effort through desire, persistence, intent, and maintenance of skillful qualities, so the practitioner remains an active support locus. The Soto shusho itto material says practice and realization are inseparable and that practice is necessary because realization is already present. This supports the candidate's boundary pressure: some sources contrast support loci, but Dogen does not describe a result carried over a before-after gap."}, "recommended_scores": {"counterargument_quality": 0.9, "novelty": 0.36, "source_reliability": 0.82}, "run_ids": ["20260530-135009-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-", "20260530-135009-codex-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-"], "title": "What Holds You That You Did Not Build", "unlike_statement": "Unlike Pargament's coping styles, extended mind, secure-base theory, AA surrender, contingencies of self-worth, and prior Lumenary continuity rubrics, this idea's specific contribution is to predict that pre-collapse continuity location will add explanatory value for burnout collapse severity, and to exclude no-gap practice-realization cases from a carry-across-threshold model."}
reviews/originality/audits.jsonl:85:{"agent": "codex", "anomaly_probe": {"anomaly_candidate": "A radical no-seeking or direct-recognition setting where a practitioner matures ethically and relationally without any identifiable external correction holder, or where naming support itself reintroduces the very search, calculation, or self-effort the teaching cuts.", "confidence_effect": "Keeps the status at extended and prevents publication as doctrine. It demands native-source coding, valid-solitude categories, unsafe-holder categories, and practitioner interviews before any public teaching.", "why_it_breaks_or_strains_model": "If no-distance practice can function without codeable correction holders, or if the native warning is against every support-seeking gesture, then the candidate's support rule is an analyst imposition. A second anomaly is abusive correction: support can be the failure source rather than the remedy."}, "audit_id": "5e945a54e9681489", "claim_units": ["No-distance does not mean no support.", "Anti-ownership should be coded before remainder, residue, or completion variables.", "If practitioner ownership is refused, correction may be held by teacher, text, vow, practice form, community, conduct, ritual, ordinary duty, or clinical support.", "No-distance failures should cluster around privatization, passivity, performance, or loss of correction.", "The human-condition fit is stable over-managers and isolated practitioners who turn relief or insight into private performance.", "The claim is not for acute crisis, abusive teacher settings, severe depression, dissociation, addiction withdrawal, or cases needing direct clinical care or protection."], "confidence": 0.8, "created_at": "2026-05-30T14:03:30+02:00", "cross_domain_prediction": {"domain": "AI automation and operational governance", "prediction": "AI or automation systems marketed as autonomous will fail more safely when correction channels remain external and concrete. Teams that remove ownership and monitoring together will show more uncorrected drift, brittle confidence, and harder incident recovery.", "structural_translation": "A system that removes manual ownership or promises autonomous operation still needs observability, rollback, escalation, monitoring, and accountable maintenance. No manual path is not no care.", "would_count_against_it": "Fully autonomous systems without independent monitoring, escalation, rollback, or human accountability perform as safely and adaptively as systems with correction channels across drift, edge cases, and user harm."}, "exact_claim": "No-distance teachings may remove the private project of becoming spiritual, but they do not thereby remove care, correction, companionship, schedule, teacher, text, vow, or ordinary accountability. Before asking what remains after self-negation, code whether the path grants the practitioner ownership at all. If ownership is refused, the key question is where correction is held and whether failures cluster when students privatize the insight, abandon correction, become passive, or turn relief into performance.", "execution_id": "parallel-20260530-135009-20260530-135009", "falsifiable_predictions": [{"expected_observation": "Split-source coding of Dogen, Huangbo, Shinran, Dzogchen, and Mahamudra sources will find ownership refusal in one layer and held-out warnings, teacher checks, vow, practice form, text, community, conduct, or reentry rules in another.", "if_model_is_right": "No-distance teachings refuse private ownership but preserve some concrete correction or care holder.", "test_surface": "Pre-registered primary-text codebook with source layer, ownership, after, correction holder, support holder, warning, repair, and analyst-frame refusal.", "would_weaken_or_falsify": "Sources deny both private ownership and codeable correction holders, or coders cannot distinguish support from the mere existence of a tradition."}, {"expected_observation": "Practitioner and teacher reports should cluster around private certainty, passivity, social withdrawal, inflated no-practice claims, or turning relief into performance when healthy support is absent or rejected.", "if_model_is_right": "Loss of correction support predicts specific no-distance failures.", "test_surface": "Teacher interviews, Cheetah House or VCE-style adverse-event coding, retreat reentry reports, and no-distance online community case coding.", "would_weaken_or_falsify": "Failures are better explained by practice intensity, sleep loss, trauma, teacher abuse, clinical risk, social isolation, or doctrine alone, with no added value from support-holder loss."}, {"expected_observation": "Stable over-managers using the check after insight or relief report less private auditing, more reachability, and more concrete duty return than journaling-only controls, without increased dependency, shame, or self-monitoring.", "if_model_is_right": "The Support Check helps only the named modern cohort.", "test_surface": "Two-week low-risk pilot with stable self-directed practitioners, app meditators, and self-improvers, excluding acute crisis and clinical non-fit cases.", "would_weaken_or_falsify": "The check increases rumination, dependence, unsafe authority-seeking, avoidance, burden, or performs no better than ordinary social contact and rest."}, {"expected_observation": "Blind coders can use anti-ownership and correction-holder fields to predict held-out warnings and repairs in no-distance cases better than Keep What Can Correct You, Some Help Should Not Be Managed, tradition label, or generic VCE factors alone.", "if_model_is_right": "Anti-ownership support coding adds decision power beyond prior Lumenary records.", "test_surface": "A/B coding comparison on Dogen, Huangbo, Tannisho, Dzogchen, Mahamudra, Pure Land, and one causal Theravada path.", "would_weaken_or_falsify": "The new fields do not change decisions, or blind readers cannot state the difference from existing correction-holder and no-management records."}], "idea_id": "9acdff6fe237d648", "idea_path": "observations/codex/2026-05-30-even-no-path-needs-care.md", "literature_search_queries": ["Dogen Bendowa practice realization shusho itto no gaining practice realization one", "Huangbo Transmission of Mind no seeking objective path teacher support correction", "Shinran Tannisho Other Power self power divergence true teacher correction", "Talal Asad discursive tradition correct model practice authority orthodoxy", "George Lindbeck doctrine as grammar cultural linguistic practice training", "Varieties of Contemplative Experience meditation difficulties teacher community relationships support", "spiritual bypassing spiritual practice avoidance correction community support research", "mindfulness optimization pressure burnout self optimization Sauerborn Sokefeld Neckel 2022", "Cheetah House meditation related difficulties support groups teacher community", "Dzogchen direct introduction support teacher correction no path practice"], "markdown_path": "reviews/originality/2026-05-30-even-no-path-needs-care-5e945a54e9681489.md", "near_neighbors": [{"difference": "The present candidate narrows that rule to no-distance and anti-ownership teachings and predicts failure clusters when support is abandoned.", "novelty_impact": "Major downgrade. The teaching candidate even reuses the earlier title. Treat as an extension, not a standalone discovery.", "overlap": "Extremely close. It already says serious results remain immature if they remove trustworthy correction paths such as teacher, text, community, conduct, duty, or clinical boundary.", "source": "Internal Lumenary prior: Keep What Can Correct You, originality audit 2026-05-29, reviews/originality/2026-05-29-keep-what-can-correct-you-*.md"}, {"difference": "This record applies that holder-routing logic to no-distance teachings and asks specifically where correction is held when ownership is refused.", "novelty_impact": "Major downgrade. The new contribution is a domain-specific scope condition.", "overlap": "Very close. That audit already says some help is distorted by private management and asks whether ownership, a permitted after, and spare agency exist before prescribing review, with alternative holders such as community, vow, conduct, rest, teacher, or support.", "source": "Internal Lumenary prior: Some Help Should Not Be Managed, reviews/originality/2026-05-30-some-help-should-not-be-managed-fa2107c4aba3ff90.md"}, {"difference": "Asad does not isolate no-distance teachings or predict privatization, passivity, or performance failures after ownership refusal.", "novelty_impact": "Strong downgrade for the claim that practice meaning and correction are tradition-held.", "overlap": "Close structural prior. Asad treats correct practice, authorization, teaching, power, and argument as internal to tradition rather than optional social context.", "source": "Talal Asad, The Idea of an Anthropology of Islam, https://voidnetwork.gr/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/The-Idea-of-an-Anthropology-of-Islam-by-Talal-Asad.pdf"}, {"difference": "The candidate turns this into a no-distance safety and failure-prediction codebook.", "novelty_impact": "Moderate to strong downgrade. The anti-private-experience posture is known.", "overlap": "Close. Lindbeck's cultural-linguistic model already makes religion prior to the individual and treats doctrine as grammar learned through practice and training.", "source": "George Lindbeck, The Nature of Doctrine, summarized at https://people.bu.edu/wwildman/bce/mwt_themes_862_lindbeck.htm and indexed at https://books.google.com/books/about/The_Nature_of_Doctrine.html?id=_fbYAAAAMAAJ"}, {"difference": "VCE is empirical safety taxonomy, not a no-distance doctrinal coding rule.", "novelty_impact": "Strong reduction for the practitioner-safety and support-holder piece.", "overlap": "Very close in practice safety. VCE separates experience, interpretation, management, teacher and community relationships, support, impairment, health behavior, and social functioning. Cheetah House provides support routing for meditation-related difficulties.", "source": "Lindahl et al., The Varieties of Contemplative Experience, PLOS One 2017, https://journals.plos.org/plosone/article?id=10.1371/journal.pone.0176239, and Cheetah House FAQ, https://www.cheetahhouse.org/faq"}, {"difference": "The candidate ties misuse to no-distance anti-ownership language and correction-holder loss.", "novelty_impact": "Moderate downgrade for the modern human-condition mechanism.", "overlap": "Close on modern misuse. Mindfulness can become both escape from optimization pressure and symptom of it, while spiritual bypassing names avoidance through spiritual language.", "source": "Sauerborn, Sokefeld, and Neckel, Paradoxes of mindfulness, https://journals.sagepub.com/doi/abs/10.1177/00380261221108570, plus spiritual bypassing research such as https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/34025522/"}, {"difference": "The candidate generalizes this into a comparative rule across no-distance teachings and support ecologies.", "novelty_impact": "Major reduction for Dogen-specific originality, partial preservation for cross-case testing.", "overlap": "It already states that practice and realization are inseparable while Dogen strongly emphasizes active practice, so no-gap is not no-practice.", "source": "Soto Zen shusho itto source, https://global.sotozen-net.or.jp/eng/library/key_terms/pdf/key_terms07.pdf"}, {"difference": "The candidate may overuse Huangbo as support for correction when his discourse also cuts support-seeking itself.", "novelty_impact": "Acts more as anomaly than support. It lowers confidence unless coded natively.", "overlap": "Huangbo already supplies the no-seeking pressure and warnings about false teachers, casual pilgrimage, and conceptual path-making.", "source": "Huangbo, Transmission of Mind, Blofeld record https://merton.bellarmine.edu/s/merton/media/51897 and searchable PDF https://wayofsuddenawakening.org/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/Huang-Po-The-Transmission-of-Mind.pdf"}], "next_loop_instructions": ["Do not publish as a standalone discovery. Cross-index with Keep What Can Correct You, Some Help Should Not Be Managed, When Tools Become Judges, Who Holds The Gate, and Not Every Check Should Be Yours.", "Build a pre-remainder codebook with fields for ownership grant, no-distance grammar, permitted after, correction holder, support holder, warning, repair, unsafe holder, valid solitude, clinical exclusion, and analyst-frame refusal.", "Use split-source coding. Do not let one passage establish ownership refusal and confirm the predicted warning or repair.", "Test Dogen, Huangbo, Tannisho, Dzogchen or Mahamudra direct introduction, Pure Land, and one causal Theravada path before broad tradition claims.", "Run practitioner interviews for concrete failed-student and repair cases, not agreement with the slogan.", "Pilot the Support Check only with screened stable over-managers. Compare against ordinary journaling, social contact, teacher check-in, and rest prompts.", "Add stop rules for OCD or scrupulosity, dependency, shame, dissociation, severe depression, mania, psychosis, addiction withdrawal, trauma activation, unsafe authority, coercive groups, and acute crisis."], "novelty_adjustment": "Lower novelty from 0.62 to 0.34. The core rule is heavily anticipated by internal correction-holder records, Some Help Should Not Be Managed, Asad, Lindbeck, VCE, spiritual bypassing research, and Soto practice-realization sources. Retain only as an extended no-distance scope test if split-source coding shows predictive gain.", "originality_status": "extended", "path": "reviews/originality/2026-05-30-even-no-path-needs-care-5e945a54e9681489.json", "practitioner_test": {"answers_that_reduce_originality": "Originality falls if practitioners say the rule is standard lineage pedagogy, spiritual direction, sangha correction, Soto practice-realization, Shin Other Power instruction, or meditation-safety triage, and if the support check adds no decisions beyond existing practice guidance.", "answers_that_support_contribution": "Support rises if practitioners find that coding ownership refusal before remainder prevents real interpretive errors, predicts failure cases, and improves support routing without increasing self-effort, dependency, or unsafe authority.", "questions": ["When a no-distance teaching removes the private project of attainment, what if anything still corrects a mistaken interpretation?", "Is this just ordinary teacher, sangha, scripture, vow, spiritual direction, or VCE safety guidance in Lumenary language?", "Can you name cases where no-path language led to passivity, private certainty, social withdrawal, or performance of being beyond practice?", "Can you name cases where support checks themselves became self-effort, reassurance seeking, dependence, or obedience to unsafe authority?", "Would the pre-remainder ownership gate change screening, sequencing, warning, or repair instructions in your setting?"], "relevant_practitioners": ["Soto Zen teachers and scholars", "Chan or Zen teachers familiar with Huangbo", "Jodo Shinshu teachers and scholars", "Dzogchen or Mahamudra teachers", "Theravada teachers for contrast cases", "spiritual directors", "meditation-safety clinicians", "Cheetah House or VCE-informed researchers", "burnout clinicians", "self-directed app meditators and retreatants"]}, "primary_text_close_read": {"primary_pair": ["Dogen Bendowa and Soto shusho itto sources, https://afe.easia.columbia.edu/ps/japan/dogen.pdf and https://global.sotozen-net.or.jp/eng/library/key_terms/pdf/key_terms07.pdf, read against Huangbo, The Transmission of Mind, Blofeld record https://merton.bellarmine.edu/s/merton/media/51897 and searchable PDF used at https://wayofsuddenawakening.org/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/Huang-Po-The-Transmission-of-Mind.pdf", "Shinran, Tannisho, especially preface, chapters 1, 6, 8, 10, 11, and 12, https://jodoshinshu.faith/tannisho-a-record-in-lament-of-divergences/"], "risk_of_overread": "High. The model can become circular by counting any surviving text, teacher, or community as support. It can also domesticate Huangbo-style search-refusal by turning an anti-support discourse into analyst-defined support. It may hide abuse if correction holders are assumed safe, and it may pathologize valid solitude. Human-condition fit is clear but narrow: stable isolated over-managers, app meditators, retreatants, and self-improvers. It is not a loneliness cure by itself and can increase dependency, rumination, or unsafe authority compliance.", "secondary_literature_gap": "Read full Dogen Bendowa, Genjokoan, Uji, Eihei Shingi, and Soto scholarship; Huangbo in multiple translations plus Chan transmission studies; Shinran, Tannisho, jinen, hakarai, and Other Power scholarship; Dzogchen and Mahamudra direct introduction manuals; Asad, Lindbeck, MacIntyre, Bell, Sharf, Katz, spiritual bypassing research, VCE, Cheetah House, mindfulness optimization critique, and spiritual direction ethics. Interviews with no-distance practitioners are essential.", "structural_observation": "Dogen's practice-realization unity rejects practice as a cause separate from later realization, but Soto explanatory material also says Dogen emphasized active practice because realization is already present. Huangbo is a sharper anomaly: he rejects objective seeking and objective path language, yet the record is itself teacher discourse and includes testing a teacher's groundedness and warning against casual pilgrimage. Tannisho denies self-powered practice and calculation, yet it opens by lamenting divergences, relies on true teachers, and preserves Vow, teacher, and correction. The candidate's narrow claim survives as a hypothesis: no-distance language is not automatically support-free, but the specific holder must be coded natively."}, "recommended_scores": {"counterargument_quality": 0.91, "novelty": 0.34, "source_reliability": 0.82}, "run_ids": ["20260530-135009-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-", "20260530-135009-codex-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-"], "title": "Even No Path Needs Care", "unlike_statement": "Unlike Keep What Can Correct You, Some Help Should Not Be Managed, Asad, Lindbeck, VCE, spiritual bypassing research, and Soto practice-realization sources, this idea's specific contribution is to make anti-ownership a pre-remainder coding gate for no-distance teachings and to predict that loss of correction support will produce privatization, passivity, or performance failures."}
reviews/originality/audits.jsonl:86:{"agent": "claude", "anomaly_probe": {"anomaly_candidate": "Rinzai koan and huatou practice deliberately uses an impossible or destabilizing question to create great doubt, while Dzogchen can deny path and result yet still require direct introduction, teacher relation, and integration.", "confidence_effect": "Lowers confidence in a binary search-sequence versus search-refusal model. Raises confidence only for a more cautious codebook that includes search-refusal, question-as-medicine, no-distance-with-support, and undecidable.", "why_it_breaks_or_strains_model": "If a path uses an apparently malformed question as medicine, then question-refusal is not enough to decide that remainder pressure is analyst-made. If no-path language still depends on transmission and repair holders, then the residue question may be relocated to practice ecology rather than abolished."}, "audit_id": "d756c9bf775096c6", "claim_units": ["Some contemplative paths stage a search sequence, so they generate a legitimate downstream remainder question.", "Some paths refuse the search sequence itself, so remainder pressure is malformed there.", "A precondition test should precede continuity, custody, or residue coding.", "The modern harm clarified is achievement-contingent self-worth turned into compulsive auditing for emptiness, detachment, or egolessness."], "confidence": 0.84, "created_at": "2026-05-30T14:21:04+02:00", "cross_domain_prediction": {"domain": "psychotherapy and performance coaching", "prediction": "For stable clients using acceptance or values-based practices, asking how to prove acceptance will increase rumination and self-monitoring, while a permitted-question check followed by ordinary valued action will reduce over-control.", "structural_translation": "Some methods stage change as a sequence with a before and after, while acceptance-based or non-striving methods treat the attempt to prove change as part of the control agenda.", "would_count_against_it": "If outcomes are explained fully by trait rumination, therapist alliance, workload, sleep, or clinical risk, and permitted-question coding adds no predictive value."}, "exact_claim": "Before any continuity or residue analysis after self-negation, test whether the path stages self-negation as an event with an after. If a path refuses seeking, before-and-after, or self-owned attainment, the question of what remains may be an analyst artifact rather than a practitioner problem.", "execution_id": "parallel-20260530-140914-20260530-140914", "falsifiable_predictions": [{"expected_observation": "Blind coders using only doctrinal or instruction passages can sort cases into search-sequence, search-refusal, question-as-medicine, no-distance-with-support, and undecidable above chance before seeing warnings or repairs.", "if_model_is_right": "The precondition gate has independent coding value.", "test_surface": "Inter-rater coding on SN 22.59, SN 22.95, Huangbo, Bendowa, Tannisho, one Dzogchen direct-introduction source, and one Rinzai koan source.", "would_weaken_or_falsify": "Coders cannot agree, or their labels are just tradition labels, teacher style, or genre labels in disguise."}, {"expected_observation": "In search-sequence cases, warnings and repairs cluster around misidentification, clinging, effort, and post-release integration. In search-refusal cases, warnings cluster around seeking, monitoring, conceptualization, and self-grading.", "if_model_is_right": "Remainder pressure is not universal.", "test_surface": "Split-source coding, code path grammar from one corpus and predict held-out warnings, repairs, and practitioner failure cases.", "would_weaken_or_falsify": "Warnings and failures in search-refusal cases are predicted just as well by support-holder loss, teacher absence, trauma, sleep loss, or institutional harm without using the precondition gate."}, {"expected_observation": "Stable over-auditors using Stop the Emptiness Audit report less self-grading and faster return to ordinary care than journaling-only or rest-only controls, without increased avoidance or reassurance seeking.", "if_model_is_right": "The proposed practice serves only the named modern wound.", "test_surface": "Two-week pilot with screened perfectionistic meditators and self-improvers, excluding OCD, scrupulosity, dissociation, severe depression, mania, psychosis, addiction withdrawal, trauma activation, and acute crisis.", "would_weaken_or_falsify": "The practice becomes a new checking ritual, increases avoidance of needed repair, worsens rumination, or performs no better than ordinary rest or social contact."}], "idea_id": "85484e1aff3c6503", "idea_path": "observations/claude/2026-05-30-some-paths-refuse-the-question-of-what-remains.md", "literature_search_queries": ["Collingwood logic of question and answer every statement answer to a question hermeneutics", "Gadamer priority of the question hermeneutics Collingwood Truth and Method", "Huangbo Transmission of Mind no seeking using mind to seek Mind", "Dogen Bendowa practice realization one shusho itto practice verification", "Dzogchen no path no practice direct introduction teacher support", "spiritual bypassing self-monitoring meditation detachment empirical research"], "markdown_path": "reviews/originality/2026-05-30-some-paths-refuse-the-question-of-what-remains-d756c9bf775096c6.md", "near_neighbors": [{"difference": "This candidate makes a sharper precondition gate: does the path stage a negation event with an after at all?", "novelty_impact": "Major downgrade. Treat as a scope-condition extension of the no-custody and no-management cluster, not a standalone discovery.", "overlap": "These records already say some teachings reject separable result, ownership, management, and after-use framing, and that support holders must be coded before prescribing private review.", "source": "Internal Lumenary prior: When There Is Nothing To Keep Or Release, Not Every Practice Is a Tool, Some Help Should Not Be Managed, Even No Path Needs Care, and Operational Remainder Ecology, supplied in the prompt history"}, {"difference": "The candidate turns Huangbo's instruction into a comparative coding gate for residue analysis and a modern practice-safety rule.", "novelty_impact": "Strong downgrade for the core insight that the search itself can be the problem.", "overlap": "Huangbo already says seeking, conceptual road-making, and using mind to seek Mind are errors.", "source": "Huangbo, On the Transmission of Mind, https://selfdefinition.org/zen/huang-po/transmission/a1-chun-chou-record.htm and https://selfdefinition.org/zen/huang-po/transmission/a2-chun-chou-record-cont.htm"}, {"difference": "The candidate groups Dogen with search-refusal paths, but Dogen still insists on active, continuous practice.", "novelty_impact": "Moderate downgrade and anomaly pressure. Dogen supports the gate but resists any no-practice simplification.", "overlap": "Practice and realization are treated as inseparable, which already blocks a simple before-and-after result model.", "source": "Dogen Bendowa and Soto shusho itto, https://afe.easia.columbia.edu/ps/japan/dogen.pdf and https://global.sotozen-net.or.jp/eng/library/key_terms/pdf/key_terms07.pdf"}, {"difference": "The candidate applies that structure to contemplative self-negation and predicts practice failure from a malformed question.", "novelty_impact": "Moderate downgrade. The formal logic is known; the remainder-gate application is the extension.", "overlap": "Collingwood already makes questions and presuppositions determine what counts as an answer.", "source": "Collingwood, Stanford Encyclopedia of Philosophy, https://plato.stanford.edu/entries/collingwood/"}, {"difference": "The candidate narrows this to a before-remainder audit for no-distance teachings.", "novelty_impact": "Moderate downgrade for the hermeneutic claim.", "overlap": "Gadamer already gives priority to the question in understanding and treats interpretation as situated application.", "source": "Gadamer, Stanford Encyclopedia of Philosophy, https://plato.stanford.edu/entries/gadamer/"}, {"difference": "The candidate isolates self-auditing for spiritual residue as a specific mismatch caused by importing a search grammar.", "novelty_impact": "Downgrades safety originality while preserving a narrower hypothesis for coding.", "overlap": "They already show that meditation effects, interpretations, management strategies, teacher relations, community, trauma history, and support influence outcomes.", "source": "VCE and Cheetah House, https://journals.plos.org/plosone/article?id=10.1371/journal.pone.0176239 and https://www.cheetahhouse.org/faq"}], "next_loop_instructions": ["Do not publish as a standalone discovery. Cross-index with When There Is Nothing To Keep Or Release, Not Every Practice Is a Tool, Some Help Should Not Be Managed, Even No Path Needs Care, and The Question Can Make The Distance.", "Build a precondition codebook with values for search-sequence, search-refusal, no-distance-with-support, question-as-medicine, received-without-calculation, practice-realization, valid-solitude, unsafe-avoidance, clinical-routing, analyst-frame-refused, and undecidable.", "Use split-source coding. Do not let one passage both establish path grammar and confirm the predicted warning or repair.", "Add Rinzai koan practice and Dzogchen direct introduction as anomaly classes, not supporting examples.", "Run practitioner interviews for concrete over-auditing, avoidance, and repair cases. Do not ask only for agreement.", "For human-condition fit, keep the practice limited to stable over-managers and achievement-contingent self-worth. Exclude OCD, scrupulosity, dissociation, severe depression, mania, psychosis, addiction withdrawal, trauma activation, medical blackout concerns, unsafe authority, and acute crisis."], "novelty_adjustment": "Lower novelty from 0.46 to 0.36. The core no-seeking and no-result logic is old in Huangbo, Dogen, Dzogchen, Shinran-adjacent no-calculation sources, and prior Lumenary no-management records. Retain as an extended precondition-gate hypothesis only if split-source coding shows predictive gain.", "originality_status": "extended", "path": "reviews/originality/2026-05-30-some-paths-refuse-the-question-of-what-remains-d756c9bf775096c6.json", "practitioner_test": {"answers_that_reduce_originality": "Originality falls if practitioners say this is standard pedagogy under no-seeking, shusho itto, Other Power, direct introduction, koan great doubt, or ordinary spiritual-bypassing triage, and if the gate adds no decisions beyond existing teacher judgment.", "answers_that_support_contribution": "Support rises if practitioners can use the gate to predict distinct failure modes and repairs before knowing outcomes, especially when it prevents over-managers from turning no-distance teachings into private self-audits.", "questions": ["Does your path stage a real search or negation event with an after, or does it refuse that staging?", "When students ask what remains after letting go, is that a valid practice question, a beginner misunderstanding, an advanced koan-like medicine, or a safety concern?", "Can you name concrete cases where auditing emptiness, detachment, or egolessness helped, and cases where it became spiritual performance or avoidance?", "Would the precondition gate change screening, sequencing, warnings, or repairs in your teaching setting?"], "relevant_practitioners": ["Theravada teachers familiar with anatta investigation", "Soto Zen teachers and Dogen scholars", "Chan or Zen teachers familiar with Huangbo and Bankei", "Rinzai koan teachers", "Dzogchen or Mahamudra teachers", "Jodo Shinshu teachers for Other Power contrast", "meditation-safety clinicians and VCE researchers", "spiritual directors", "clinicians familiar with perfectionism, rumination, OCD, and scrupulosity"]}, "primary_text_close_read": {"primary_pair": ["SN 22.59 and SN 22.95, dhammatalks.org, https://www.dhammatalks.org/suttas/SN/SN22_59.html and https://www.dhammatalks.org/suttas/SN/SN22_95.html", "Huangbo, On the Transmission of Mind, Blofeld translation hosted at https://selfdefinition.org/zen/huang-po/transmission/a1-chun-chou-record.htm and https://selfdefinition.org/zen/huang-po/transmission/a2-chun-chou-record-cont.htm, read with Dogen Bendowa excerpts at https://afe.easia.columbia.edu/ps/japan/dogen.pdf and Soto shusho itto note at https://global.sotozen-net.or.jp/eng/library/key_terms/pdf/key_terms07.pdf"], "risk_of_overread": "High. The model can make search-refusal too clean. Huangbo taught through dialogue, Dogen built a practice institution, and Dzogchen no-path language often requires teacher transmission. The modern cohort is clear but narrow: stable over-managers and perfectionistic practitioners who audit their inner state. It is not for beginners needing inquiry, people using non-inquiry to avoid repair, OCD or scrupulosity, dissociation, severe depression, mania, psychosis, acute trauma, addiction withdrawal, or medical blackout concerns.", "secondary_literature_gap": "Search further in Collingwood on the logic of question and answer, Gadamer on the priority of the question, Asad on discursive tradition, Lindbeck on doctrine as grammar, Austin on felicity conditions, Sharf and Katz on contextualism, Dogen scholarship on shusho itto, Chan studies on Huangbo and Bankei, Dzogchen direct-introduction literature, VCE and Cheetah House safety literature, and spiritual bypassing research.", "structural_observation": "SN 22.59 and SN 22.95 explicitly authorize seeing, observing, examining, disenchantment, release, and the knowledge that the task is done. That is a staged investigative grammar. Huangbo repeatedly treats seeking Mind with mind, forming concepts of the Way, or making the Way into a road as the very distortion. Dogen's practice-realization unity blocks a simple cause-then-result reading, while Soto material also says Dogen emphasized active practice because realization is already present. The candidate's gate is textually plausible, but only if it codes the native practice grammar rather than broad tradition names."}, "recommended_scores": {"counterargument_quality": 0.91, "novelty": 0.36, "source_reliability": 0.77}, "run_ids": ["20260530-140914-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-", "20260530-140914-codex-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-"], "title": "Some Paths Refuse the Question of What Remains", "unlike_statement": "Unlike Huangbo, Dogen, Collingwood, Gadamer, VCE, and prior Lumenary no-management records, this idea's specific contribution is a precondition test before remainder coding: only ask what remains if the path first authorizes a self-negation event with an after."}

