reviews/originality/audits.jsonl:85:{"agent": "codex", "anomaly_probe": {"anomaly_candidate": "A radical no-seeking or direct-recognition setting where a practitioner matures ethically and relationally without any identifiable external correction holder, or where naming support itself reintroduces the very search, calculation, or self-effort the teaching cuts.", "confidence_effect": "Keeps the status at extended and prevents publication as doctrine. It demands native-source coding, valid-solitude categories, unsafe-holder categories, and practitioner interviews before any public teaching.", "why_it_breaks_or_strains_model": "If no-distance practice can function without codeable correction holders, or if the native warning is against every support-seeking gesture, then the candidate's support rule is an analyst imposition. A second anomaly is abusive correction: support can be the failure source rather than the remedy."}, "audit_id": "5e945a54e9681489", "claim_units": ["No-distance does not mean no support.", "Anti-ownership should be coded before remainder, residue, or completion variables.", "If practitioner ownership is refused, correction may be held by teacher, text, vow, practice form, community, conduct, ritual, ordinary duty, or clinical support.", "No-distance failures should cluster around privatization, passivity, performance, or loss of correction.", "The human-condition fit is stable over-managers and isolated practitioners who turn relief or insight into private performance.", "The claim is not for acute crisis, abusive teacher settings, severe depression, dissociation, addiction withdrawal, or cases needing direct clinical care or protection."], "confidence": 0.8, "created_at": "2026-05-30T14:03:30+02:00", "cross_domain_prediction": {"domain": "AI automation and operational governance", "prediction": "AI or automation systems marketed as autonomous will fail more safely when correction channels remain external and concrete. Teams that remove ownership and monitoring together will show more uncorrected drift, brittle confidence, and harder incident recovery.", "structural_translation": "A system that removes manual ownership or promises autonomous operation still needs observability, rollback, escalation, monitoring, and accountable maintenance. No manual path is not no care.", "would_count_against_it": "Fully autonomous systems without independent monitoring, escalation, rollback, or human accountability perform as safely and adaptively as systems with correction channels across drift, edge cases, and user harm."}, "exact_claim": "No-distance teachings may remove the private project of becoming spiritual, but they do not thereby remove care, correction, companionship, schedule, teacher, text, vow, or ordinary accountability. Before asking what remains after self-negation, code whether the path grants the practitioner ownership at all. If ownership is refused, the key question is where correction is held and whether failures cluster when students privatize the insight, abandon correction, become passive, or turn relief into performance.", "execution_id": "parallel-20260530-135009-20260530-135009", "falsifiable_predictions": [{"expected_observation": "Split-source coding of Dogen, Huangbo, Shinran, Dzogchen, and Mahamudra sources will find ownership refusal in one layer and held-out warnings, teacher checks, vow, practice form, text, community, conduct, or reentry rules in another.", "if_model_is_right": "No-distance teachings refuse private ownership but preserve some concrete correction or care holder.", "test_surface": "Pre-registered primary-text codebook with source layer, ownership, after, correction holder, support holder, warning, repair, and analyst-frame refusal.", "would_weaken_or_falsify": "Sources deny both private ownership and codeable correction holders, or coders cannot distinguish support from the mere existence of a tradition."}, {"expected_observation": "Practitioner and teacher reports should cluster around private certainty, passivity, social withdrawal, inflated no-practice claims, or turning relief into performance when healthy support is absent or rejected.", "if_model_is_right": "Loss of correction support predicts specific no-distance failures.", "test_surface": "Teacher interviews, Cheetah House or VCE-style adverse-event coding, retreat reentry reports, and no-distance online community case coding.", "would_weaken_or_falsify": "Failures are better explained by practice intensity, sleep loss, trauma, teacher abuse, clinical risk, social isolation, or doctrine alone, with no added value from support-holder loss."}, {"expected_observation": "Stable over-managers using the check after insight or relief report less private auditing, more reachability, and more concrete duty return than journaling-only controls, without increased dependency, shame, or self-monitoring.", "if_model_is_right": "The Support Check helps only the named modern cohort.", "test_surface": "Two-week low-risk pilot with stable self-directed practitioners, app meditators, and self-improvers, excluding acute crisis and clinical non-fit cases.", "would_weaken_or_falsify": "The check increases rumination, dependence, unsafe authority-seeking, avoidance, burden, or performs no better than ordinary social contact and rest."}, {"expected_observation": "Blind coders can use anti-ownership and correction-holder fields to predict held-out warnings and repairs in no-distance cases better than Keep What Can Correct You, Some Help Should Not Be Managed, tradition label, or generic VCE factors alone.", "if_model_is_right": "Anti-ownership support coding adds decision power beyond prior Lumenary records.", "test_surface": "A/B coding comparison on Dogen, Huangbo, Tannisho, Dzogchen, Mahamudra, Pure Land, and one causal Theravada path.", "would_weaken_or_falsify": "The new fields do not change decisions, or blind readers cannot state the difference from existing correction-holder and no-management